-- Chapter 124 — ℝ ORDER + ADDITIVE INVERSE: advancing the Cauchy reals toward an
-- ORDERED FIELD (M6 / telos-3 / D3).  The ENTIRE ch121 construction + ch122 arithmetic
-- (radd / qabsTriangle / qToleranceSplit / the ℚ ordered field) is redeclared VERBATIM
-- below (self-contained); the NEW ch124 layer begins under the "CHAPTER 124" banner at
-- the foot.  It lands, FULLY PROVEN (no admits/holes/postulates):
--   • the ℝ ADDITIVE INVERSE: rneg : R -> R (pointwise qneg, Cauchy-preserving and
--     RRel-respecting), rzero = qToR qzero, rsub x y = radd x (rneg y), and the law
--     rsubSelf : rsub x x = rzero — the additive inverse on ℝ.
--   • the ℚ negation involution qnegNeg (qneg (qneg x) = x) and the |·| sign-symmetry
--     qabsNeg (|−q| = |q|), the analysis fuel for rneg's well-definedness.
--   • the ORDER on ℝ at the representative level: rleP : RPair -> RPair -> Prop (the
--     "eventually ≤ up to every tolerance" relation, index-as-its-own-modulus, kept in
--     Prop/U0 — the same continuation form as RRel), shown to RESPECT RRel in BOTH
--     arguments (rleRespR/rleRespL, logical implications via qaddMono2 + the triangle
--     bound), with the order axioms rleReflP (reflexivity) and rleTransP (transitivity,
--     lifted from qleTrans + a tolerance-doubling argument), and qToRMonoP — the
--     embedding ℚ ↪ ℝ is ORDER-PRESERVING (qle a b ⇒ rleP (constRPair a)(constRPair b)).
-- WHY rep-level for rle (the universe note): lifting a Prop-valued relation through the
-- quotient to a standalone rle : R -> R -> Prop needs the respect obligation Eq Prop
-- (rleP x y)(rleP x y'); the two relations are logically EQUIVALENT (rleRespR/rleRespL)
-- but not convertible, and this kernel has no propositional extensionality (Eq Prop from
-- biimplication), so the packaged lift is the documented remainder — see the closing note.
--
-- Chapter 121 — ℝ as the CAUCHY COMPLETION of ℚ (telos-3 / D3, the M6 numeric-tower APEX).
-- ch117 closed ℚ as a verified FIELD; ch119 equipped ℚ with a verified ORDER (qle + the
-- order axioms + qaddMono).  This chapter builds the REAL NUMBERS as Cauchy sequences of
-- rationals modulo the null-difference equivalence: ℝ = (Cauchy ℚ-sequences) / (∼ pointwise
-- difference → 0), one quotient level UP from how ℚ (ch108) was built over ℤ (ch07).
--
-- The ENTIRE ch07/ch103/ch105/ch107/ch108/ch113/ch117/ch119 ℤ+ℚ ordered-field development
-- is redeclared VERBATIM below (self-contained, through ch119's qleHalfTrans); the NEW ℝ
-- layer begins under the "CHAPTER 121" banner at the foot of the file.
--
-- LANDS in the NEW (ch121) layer, FULLY PROVEN, no admits/holes/postulates:
--   • qneg : Q -> Q (numerator negation, lifted through QRel by qnegRespects) and
--     qsub x y = qadd x (qneg y); the law qsubSelf : qsub x x = qzero (additive inverse).
--   • qabs : Q -> Q (branch on qle q qzero by BoolElim; the nonneg branch is q, the
--     negative branch is qneg q) and qabsZero : qabs qzero = qzero (computes, refl).
--   • the modulus tolerance qFromMod k = 1/(k+1) and qZeroLeMod : qle qzero (1/(k+1)) = true
--     (parametric in k — 0 ≤ 1 cross-multiplied, refl true).
--   • isCauchy : (Nat -> Q) -> U — a Cauchy predicate carrying an EXPLICIT modulus
--     (Sig (Nat -> Nat) …): a modulus N with ∀k, ∀ m n ≥ N k, |f m − f n| ≤ 1/(k+1).
--   • RPair = Sig (Nat -> Q) isCauchy; RRel : RPair -> RPair -> Prop ("pointwise difference
--     → 0": ∀k, ∀ n ≥ M k, |f n − g n| ≤ 1/(k+1), modulus carried); RRel is an EQUIVALENCE
--     (RRelRefl proven); R = Quot RPair RRel — the reals EXIST as a type.
--   • qToR : Q -> R (the constant-sequence embedding) — constant sequences are Cauchy
--     (constSeqCauchy, modulus = const zero, difference qzero) and qToR respects Eq Q
--     (qToRCong); sanity qToR (1/2) : R and qToR qzero : R.
--   • the SANITY closers: a constant sequence is Cauchy; qToR (1/2) is a real.
-- STATED-AND-DOCUMENTED remainder (the lifted operations, the follow-on stdlib step):
--   radd / rle through TWO quotient layers — see the closing note.
--
-- (The redeclared ch119 banner/notes below describe the inherited ordered-field layer.)
--
-- LANDS in the inherited (ch119) layer, FULLY PROVEN, no admits/holes/postulates:
--   • the Nat-order cancellation/monotonicity algebra: lteAddCancelL/R (cancel a common
--     summand), lteAddMono (add two ≤'s), each by induction — the well-definedness fuel.
--   • zleP : NatPair -> NatPair -> Bool — the ℤ order on representatives, (a,b) ≤ (c,d)
--     iff lte (a+d) (c+b).  zle : Z -> Z -> Bool, lifted through ZRel by the CRUX
--     `zleRespR`/`zleRespL` (zle respects ZRel — Nat add-cancellation), double-qind.
--   • qleP : QPair -> QPair -> Bool — the ℚ order via CROSS-MULTIPLICATION against the
--     positive denominators: a/sb ≤ c/sd iff zle (a·sd) (c·sb).  qle : Q -> Q -> Bool,
--     lifted through QRel by `qleRespR`/`qleRespL` — the well-definedness crux, using
--     zle's ZRel-respect + zmul monotonicity through the cross terms.
--   • the ORDER AXIOMS: qleRefl (reflexivity), qleTrans (transitivity), qleAntisym
--     (qle x y ∧ qle y x ⇒ x = y in Q), qleTotal (every pair comparable) — each lifted
--     from the ℤ/Nat order through qind.
--   • ORDERED-FIELD COMPATIBILITY: qaddMono — qle x y ⇒ qle (qadd x z) (qadd y z)
--     (translation invariance), the additive compatibility law of an ordered field.
--   • sanity: qle (1/2) (2/3) = true ; qle (2/3) (1/2) = false ; qleRefl on a concrete q.
--
data Nat : U is
  zero : Nat
| succ : Nat -> Nat
end

add : Nat -> Nat -> Nat is
  fn (m : Nat) (n : Nat) is
    NatElim (fn (x : Nat) is Nat end) n (fn (k : Nat) (ih : Nat) is succ ih end) m
  end
end

mul : Nat -> Nat -> Nat is
  fn (m : Nat) (n : Nat) is
    NatElim (fn (x : Nat) is Nat end) zero (fn (k : Nat) (ih : Nat) is add n ih end) m
  end
end

-- The equality toolkit (ch07), with implicit arguments doing the bookkeeping.

cong : {A : U} -> {B : U} -> (f : A -> B) -> {x : A} -> {y : A} -> Eq A x y -> Eq B (f x) (f y) is
  fn {A : U} {B : U} (f : A -> B) {x : A} {y : A} (p : Eq A x y) is
    subst A x y p (fn (z : A) is Eq B (f x) (f z) end) refl
  end
end

sym : {A : U} -> {x : A} -> {y : A} -> Eq A x y -> Eq A y x is
  fn {A : U} {x : A} {y : A} (p : Eq A x y) is
    subst A x y p (fn (z : A) is Eq A z x end) refl
  end
end

trans : {A : U} -> {x : A} -> {y : A} -> {z : A} -> Eq A x y -> Eq A y z -> Eq A x z is
  fn {A : U} {x : A} {y : A} {z : A} (p : Eq A x y) (q : Eq A y z) is
    subst A y z q (fn (w : A) is Eq A x w end) p
  end
end

-- ============================================================================
-- The Nat SEMIRING lemmas (ch63 / ch81), redeclared verbatim.
-- ============================================================================

addZeroR : (n : Nat) -> Eq Nat (add n zero) n is
  fn (n : Nat) is
    NatElim (fn (x : Nat) is Eq Nat (add x zero) x end)
      (refl zero)
      (fn (k : Nat) (ih : Eq Nat (add k zero) k) is
         subst Nat (add k zero) k ih
           (fn (z : Nat) is Eq Nat (add (succ k) zero) (succ z) end)
           (refl (add (succ k) zero))
       end)
      n
  end
end

addSuccR : (n : Nat) -> (m : Nat) -> Eq Nat (add n (succ m)) (succ (add n m)) is
  fn (n : Nat) (m : Nat) is
    NatElim (fn (x : Nat) is Eq Nat (add x (succ m)) (succ (add x m)) end)
      (refl (succ m))
      (fn (k : Nat) (ih : Eq Nat (add k (succ m)) (succ (add k m))) is
         subst Nat (add k (succ m)) (succ (add k m)) ih
           (fn (z : Nat) is Eq Nat (add (succ k) (succ m)) (succ z) end)
           (refl (add (succ k) (succ m)))
       end)
      n
  end
end

addAssoc : (a : Nat) -> (b : Nat) -> (c : Nat)
   -> Eq Nat (add (add a b) c) (add a (add b c)) is
  fn (a : Nat) (b : Nat) (c : Nat) is
    NatElim (fn (x : Nat) is Eq Nat (add (add x b) c) (add x (add b c)) end)
      (refl (add b c))
      (fn (k : Nat) (ih : Eq Nat (add (add k b) c) (add k (add b c))) is
         subst Nat (add (add k b) c) (add k (add b c)) ih
           (fn (z : Nat) is Eq Nat (succ (add (add k b) c)) (succ z) end)
           (refl (succ (add (add k b) c)))
       end)
      a
  end
end

addComm : (n : Nat) -> (m : Nat) -> Eq Nat (add n m) (add m n) is
  fn (n : Nat) (m : Nat) is
    NatElim (fn (x : Nat) is Eq Nat (add x m) (add m x) end)
      (subst Nat (add m zero) m (addZeroR m)
         (fn (z : Nat) is Eq Nat z (add m zero) end)
         (refl (add m zero)))
      (fn (k : Nat) (ih : Eq Nat (add k m) (add m k)) is
         subst Nat (succ (add m k)) (add m (succ k))
           (subst Nat (add m (succ k)) (succ (add m k)) (addSuccR m k)
              (fn (z : Nat) is Eq Nat z (add m (succ k)) end)
              (refl (add m (succ k))))
           (fn (z : Nat) is Eq Nat (succ (add k m)) z end)
           (subst Nat (add k m) (add m k) ih
              (fn (z : Nat) is Eq Nat (succ (add k m)) (succ z) end)
              (refl (succ (add k m))))
       end)
      n
  end
end

mulZeroR : (n : Nat) -> Eq Nat (mul n zero) zero is
  fn (n : Nat) is
    NatElim (fn (x : Nat) is Eq Nat (mul x zero) zero end)
      (refl zero)
      (fn (k : Nat) (ih : Eq Nat (mul k zero) zero) is ih end)
      n
  end
end

-- RIGHT DISTRIBUTIVITY: (a + b) * c = a*c + b*c (ch63).
mulDistR : (a : Nat) -> (b : Nat) -> (c : Nat)
   -> Eq Nat (mul (add a b) c) (add (mul a c) (mul b c)) is
  fn (a : Nat) (b : Nat) (c : Nat) is
    NatElim (fn (x : Nat) is Eq Nat (mul (add x b) c) (add (mul x c) (mul b c)) end)
      (refl (mul b c))
      (fn (k : Nat) (ih : Eq Nat (mul (add k b) c) (add (mul k c) (mul b c))) is
         subst Nat
           (add c (add (mul k c) (mul b c)))
           (add (add c (mul k c)) (mul b c))
           (subst Nat
              (add (add c (mul k c)) (mul b c))
              (add c (add (mul k c) (mul b c)))
              (addAssoc c (mul k c) (mul b c))
              (fn (z : Nat) is Eq Nat z (add (add c (mul k c)) (mul b c)) end)
              (refl (add (add c (mul k c)) (mul b c))))
           (fn (z : Nat) is Eq Nat (add c (mul (add k b) c)) z end)
           (subst Nat (mul (add k b) c) (add (mul k c) (mul b c)) ih
              (fn (z : Nat) is Eq Nat (add c (mul (add k b) c)) (add c z) end)
              (refl (add c (mul (add k b) c))))
       end)
      a
  end
end

-- MULTIPLICATIVE SUCCESSOR-SHIFT: mul n (succ m) = add (mul n m) n (ch81).
mulSuccR : (n : Nat) -> (m : Nat) -> Eq Nat (mul n (succ m)) (add (mul n m) n) is
  fn (n : Nat) (m : Nat) is
    NatElim
      (fn (x : Nat) is Eq Nat (mul x (succ m)) (add (mul x m) x) end)
      (refl zero)
      (fn (k : Nat) (ih : Eq Nat (mul k (succ m)) (add (mul k m) k)) is
         subst Nat
           (succ (add (add m (mul k m)) k))
           (add (add m (mul k m)) (succ k))
           (subst Nat
              (add (add m (mul k m)) (succ k))
              (succ (add (add m (mul k m)) k))
              (addSuccR (add m (mul k m)) k)
              (fn (z : Nat) is Eq Nat z (add (add m (mul k m)) (succ k)) end)
              (refl (add (add m (mul k m)) (succ k))))
           (fn (z : Nat) is Eq Nat (mul (succ k) (succ m)) z end)
           (subst Nat
              (add m (add (mul k m) k))
              (add (add m (mul k m)) k)
              (subst Nat
                 (add (add m (mul k m)) k)
                 (add m (add (mul k m) k))
                 (addAssoc m (mul k m) k)
                 (fn (z : Nat) is Eq Nat z (add (add m (mul k m)) k) end)
                 (refl (add (add m (mul k m)) k)))
              (fn (z : Nat) is Eq Nat (mul (succ k) (succ m)) (succ z) end)
              (subst Nat
                 (mul k (succ m))
                 (add (mul k m) k)
                 ih
                 (fn (z : Nat) is Eq Nat (mul (succ k) (succ m)) (succ (add m z)) end)
                 (refl (mul (succ k) (succ m)))))
       end)
      n
  end
end

-- COMMUTATIVITY of Nat mul (ch81), by induction on m.
mulComm : (m : Nat) -> (n : Nat) -> Eq Nat (mul m n) (mul n m) is
  fn (m : Nat) (n : Nat) is
    NatElim
      (fn (x : Nat) is Eq Nat (mul x n) (mul n x) end)
      (subst Nat (mul n zero) zero (mulZeroR n)
         (fn (z : Nat) is Eq Nat z (mul n zero) end)
         (refl (mul n zero)))
      (fn (k : Nat) (ih : Eq Nat (mul k n) (mul n k)) is
         subst Nat
           (add (mul n k) n)
           (mul n (succ k))
           (subst Nat
              (mul n (succ k))
              (add (mul n k) n)
              (mulSuccR n k)
              (fn (z : Nat) is Eq Nat z (mul n (succ k)) end)
              (refl (mul n (succ k))))
           (fn (z : Nat) is Eq Nat (mul (succ k) n) z end)
           (subst Nat
              (mul n k)
              (mul k n)
              (subst Nat (mul k n) (mul n k) ih
                 (fn (z : Nat) is Eq Nat z (mul k n) end)
                 (refl (mul k n)))
              (fn (z : Nat) is Eq Nat (add n z) (add (mul n k) n) end)
              (addComm n (mul n k)))
       end)
      m
  end
end

-- LEFT DISTRIBUTIVITY: a * (b + c) = a*b + a*c, derived from mulComm + mulDistR.
mulDistL : (a : Nat) -> (b : Nat) -> (c : Nat)
   -> Eq Nat (mul a (add b c)) (add (mul a b) (mul a c)) is
  fn (a : Nat) (b : Nat) (c : Nat) is
    trans (mulComm a (add b c))
      (trans (mulDistR b c a)
        (trans (cong (fn (s : Nat) is add s (mul c a) end) (mulComm b a))
          (cong (fn (s : Nat) is add (mul a b) s end) (mulComm c a))))
  end
end

-- x + (y + z) = y + (x + z) and the interchange law (ch07), the workhorses of the
-- respect proofs.
swapLeft : (x : Nat) -> (y : Nat) -> (z : Nat) ->
    Eq Nat (add x (add y z)) (add y (add x z)) is
  fn (x : Nat) (y : Nat) (z : Nat) is
    trans (sym (addAssoc x y z))
      (trans (cong (fn (s : Nat) is add s z end) (addComm x y))
        (addAssoc y x z))
  end
end

interchange : (w : Nat) -> (x : Nat) -> (y : Nat) -> (z : Nat) ->
    Eq Nat (add (add w x) (add y z)) (add (add w y) (add x z)) is
  fn (w : Nat) (x : Nat) (y : Nat) (z : Nat) is
    trans (addAssoc w x (add y z))
      (trans (cong (fn (s : Nat) is add w s end) (swapLeft x y z))
        (sym (addAssoc w y (add x z))))
  end
end

-- ============================================================================
-- NEW NAT LEMMAS this chapter needs beyond ch105's set.
-- ============================================================================

-- MULTIPLICATIVE RIGHT IDENTITY: mul n 1 = n. One-line induction:
--   mul (succ k) 1 = add 1 (mul k 1) = succ (mul k 1) = succ k by IH.
mulOneR : (n : Nat) -> Eq Nat (mul n (succ zero)) n is
  fn (n : Nat) is
    NatElim (fn (x : Nat) is Eq Nat (mul x (succ zero)) x end)
      (refl zero)
      (fn (k : Nat) (ih : Eq Nat (mul k (succ zero)) k) is
         cong succ ih
       end)
      n
  end
end

-- MUL ASSOCIATIVITY: (a * b) * c = a * (b * c) (ch81 sibling), by induction on a.
--   (succ k * b) * c = (b + k*b) * c           [def]
--                    = b*c + (k*b)*c           [mulDistR]
--                    = b*c + k*(b*c)           [IH]
--                    = (succ k) * (b*c)         [def]
mulAssoc : (a : Nat) -> (b : Nat) -> (c : Nat)
   -> Eq Nat (mul (mul a b) c) (mul a (mul b c)) is
  fn (a : Nat) (b : Nat) (c : Nat) is
    NatElim (fn (x : Nat) is Eq Nat (mul (mul x b) c) (mul x (mul b c)) end)
      (refl zero)
      (fn (k : Nat) (ih : Eq Nat (mul (mul k b) c) (mul k (mul b c))) is
         trans (mulDistR b (mul k b) c)
           (cong (fn (s : Nat) is add (mul b c) s end) ih)
       end)
      a
  end
end

-- ============================================================================
-- ch07/ch103/ch105 ℤ infrastructure, redeclared verbatim.
-- ============================================================================

cong2 : {A : U} -> {B : U} -> {C : U} -> (f : A -> B -> C)
     -> {x : A} -> {y : A} -> {u : B} -> {v : B}
     -> Eq A x y -> Eq B u v -> Eq C (f x u) (f y v) is
  fn {A : U} {B : U} {C : U} (f : A -> B -> C)
     {x : A} {y : A} {u : B} {v : B} (p : Eq A x y) (q : Eq B u v) is
    trans (cong (fn (z : A) is f z u end) p) (cong (fn (z : B) is f y z end) q)
  end
end

data NatPair : U is
  npair : Nat -> Nat -> NatPair
end

fst : NatPair -> Nat is
  fn (p : NatPair) is
    NatPairElim (fn (x : NatPair) is Nat end) (fn (a : Nat) (b : Nat) is a end) p
  end
end

snd : NatPair -> Nat is
  fn (p : NatPair) is
    NatPairElim (fn (x : NatPair) is Nat end) (fn (a : Nat) (b : Nat) is b end) p
  end
end

ZRel : NatPair -> NatPair -> Prop is
  fn (p : NatPair) (q : NatPair) is
    Eq Nat (add (fst p) (snd q)) (add (fst q) (snd p))
  end
end

Z : U is Quot NatPair ZRel end

zfrom : Nat -> Z is fn (n : Nat) is qin NatPair ZRel (npair n zero) end end
zzero : Z is zfrom zero end
zone : Z is zfrom (succ zero) end
zminusOne : Z is qin NatPair ZRel (npair zero (succ zero)) end

psucc : NatPair -> NatPair is
  fn (p : NatPair) is npair (succ (fst p)) (snd p) end
end
pneg : NatPair -> NatPair is
  fn (p : NatPair) is npair (snd p) (fst p) end
end
padd : NatPair -> NatPair -> NatPair is
  fn (p : NatPair) (q : NatPair) is
    npair (add (fst p) (fst q)) (add (snd p) (snd q))
  end
end

-- Integer addition, by lifting twice (ch103).
paddRespL : (p : NatPair) -> (p' : NatPair) -> (q : NatPair) ->
    ZRel p p' -> ZRel (padd p q) (padd p' q) is
  fn (p : NatPair) (p' : NatPair) (q : NatPair) (r : ZRel p p') is
    trans (interchange (fst p) (fst q) (snd p') (snd q))
      (trans (cong (fn (s : Nat) is add s (add (fst q) (snd q)) end) r)
        (sym (interchange (fst p') (fst q) (snd p) (snd q))))
  end
end

paddRespR : (p : NatPair) -> (q : NatPair) -> (q' : NatPair) ->
    ZRel q q' -> ZRel (padd p q) (padd p q') is
  fn (p : NatPair) (q : NatPair) (q' : NatPair) (r : ZRel q q') is
    trans (interchange (fst p) (fst q) (snd p) (snd q'))
      (trans (cong (fn (s : Nat) is add (add (fst p) (snd p)) s end) r)
        (sym (interchange (fst p) (fst q') (snd p) (snd q))))
  end
end

zaddR : NatPair -> Z -> Z is
  fn (p : NatPair) is
    qlift NatPair ZRel Z
      (fn (q : NatPair) is qin NatPair ZRel (padd p q) end)
      (fn (q : NatPair) (q' : NatPair) (r : ZRel q q') is
        qsound NatPair ZRel (padd p q) (padd p q') (paddRespR p q q' r)
      end)
  end
end

zadd : Z -> Z -> Z is
  qlift NatPair ZRel (Z -> Z) zaddR
    (fn (p : NatPair) (p' : NatPair) (r : ZRel p p') is
      fn (z : Z) is
        qind NatPair ZRel (fn (w : Z) is Eq Z (zaddR p w) (zaddR p' w) end)
          (fn (q : NatPair) is
            qsound NatPair ZRel (padd p q) (padd p' q) (paddRespL p p' q r)
          end)
          z
      end
    end)
end

-- Integer multiplication, by lifting twice (ch105).
pmul : NatPair -> NatPair -> NatPair is
  fn (p : NatPair) (q : NatPair) is
    npair
      (add (mul (fst p) (fst q)) (mul (snd p) (snd q)))
      (add (mul (fst p) (snd q)) (mul (snd p) (fst q)))
  end
end

pmulRespR : (p : NatPair) -> (q : NatPair) -> (q' : NatPair) ->
    ZRel q q' -> ZRel (pmul p q) (pmul p q') is
  fn (p : NatPair) (q : NatPair) (q' : NatPair) (r : ZRel q q') is
    trans
      (interchange
        (mul (fst p) (fst q)) (mul (snd p) (snd q))
        (mul (fst p) (snd q')) (mul (snd p) (fst q')))
      (trans
        (cong2 (fn (u : Nat) (v : Nat) is add u v end)
          (trans (sym (mulDistL (fst p) (fst q) (snd q')))
            (trans (cong (fn (s : Nat) is mul (fst p) s end) r)
              (mulDistL (fst p) (fst q') (snd q))))
          (trans (addComm (mul (snd p) (snd q)) (mul (snd p) (fst q')))
            (trans
              (sym
                (trans (sym (mulDistL (snd p) (fst q) (snd q')))
                  (trans (cong (fn (s : Nat) is mul (snd p) s end) r)
                    (mulDistL (snd p) (fst q') (snd q)))))
              (addComm (mul (snd p) (fst q)) (mul (snd p) (snd q'))))))
        (interchange
          (mul (fst p) (fst q')) (mul (fst p) (snd q))
          (mul (snd p) (snd q')) (mul (snd p) (fst q))))
  end
end

pmulRespL : (p : NatPair) -> (p' : NatPair) -> (q : NatPair) ->
    ZRel p p' -> ZRel (pmul p q) (pmul p' q) is
  fn (p : NatPair) (p' : NatPair) (q : NatPair) (r : ZRel p p') is
    trans
      (trans
        (cong (fn (s : Nat) is add (add (mul (fst p) (fst q)) (mul (snd p) (snd q))) s end)
          (addComm (mul (fst p') (snd q)) (mul (snd p') (fst q))))
        (interchange
          (mul (fst p) (fst q)) (mul (snd p) (snd q))
          (mul (snd p') (fst q)) (mul (fst p') (snd q))))
      (trans
        (cong2 (fn (u : Nat) (v : Nat) is add u v end)
          (trans (sym (mulDistR (fst p) (snd p') (fst q)))
            (trans (cong (fn (s : Nat) is mul s (fst q) end) r)
              (mulDistR (fst p') (snd p) (fst q))))
          (trans (addComm (mul (snd p) (snd q)) (mul (fst p') (snd q)))
            (trans (sym (mulDistR (fst p') (snd p) (snd q)))
              (trans (cong (fn (s : Nat) is mul s (snd q) end) (sym r))
                (trans (mulDistR (fst p) (snd p') (snd q))
                  (addComm (mul (fst p) (snd q)) (mul (snd p') (snd q))))))))
        (trans
          (interchange
            (mul (fst p') (fst q)) (mul (snd p) (fst q))
            (mul (snd p') (snd q)) (mul (fst p) (snd q)))
          (cong (fn (s : Nat) is add (add (mul (fst p') (fst q)) (mul (snd p') (snd q))) s end)
            (addComm (mul (snd p) (fst q)) (mul (fst p) (snd q))))))
  end
end

zmulR : NatPair -> Z -> Z is
  fn (p : NatPair) is
    qlift NatPair ZRel Z
      (fn (q : NatPair) is qin NatPair ZRel (pmul p q) end)
      (fn (q : NatPair) (q' : NatPair) (r : ZRel q q') is
        qsound NatPair ZRel (pmul p q) (pmul p q') (pmulRespR p q q' r)
      end)
  end
end

zmul : Z -> Z -> Z is
  qlift NatPair ZRel (Z -> Z) zmulR
    (fn (p : NatPair) (p' : NatPair) (r : ZRel p p') is
      fn (z : Z) is
        qind NatPair ZRel (fn (w : Z) is Eq Z (zmulR p w) (zmulR p' w) end)
          (fn (q : NatPair) is
            qsound NatPair ZRel (pmul p q) (pmul p' q) (pmulRespL p p' q r)
          end)
          z
      end
    end)
end

-- pmul p q ~ pmul q p on representatives (ch105).
pmulComm : (p : NatPair) -> (q : NatPair) -> ZRel (pmul p q) (pmul q p) is
  fn (p : NatPair) (q : NatPair) is
    cong2 (fn (u : Nat) (v : Nat) is add u v end)
      (cong2 (fn (u : Nat) (v : Nat) is add u v end)
        (mulComm (fst p) (fst q))
        (mulComm (snd p) (snd q)))
      (trans
        (cong2 (fn (u : Nat) (v : Nat) is add u v end)
          (mulComm (fst q) (snd p))
          (mulComm (snd q) (fst p)))
        (addComm (mul (snd p) (fst q)) (mul (fst p) (snd q))))
  end
end

zmulComm : (x : Z) -> (y : Z) -> Eq Z (zmul x y) (zmul y x) is
  fn (x : Z) is
    qind NatPair ZRel (fn (w : Z) is (y : Z) -> Eq Z (zmul w y) (zmul y w) end)
      (fn (p : NatPair) is
        fn (y : Z) is
          qind NatPair ZRel
            (fn (w : Z) is Eq Z (zmul (qin NatPair ZRel p) w) (zmul w (qin NatPair ZRel p)) end)
            (fn (q : NatPair) is
              qsound NatPair ZRel (pmul p q) (pmul q p) (pmulComm p q)
            end)
            y
        end
      end)
      x
  end
end

-- ============================================================================
-- NEW IN CH107 — the remaining commutative-ring laws.
-- ============================================================================

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- MULTIPLICATIVE RIGHT IDENTITY: x * 1 = x.
-- zone = qin (1, 0). On a representative (a, b):
--   pmul (a,b) (1,0) = (a*1 + b*0, a*0 + b*1).
-- The ZRel obligation relating it back to (a, b) is
--   (a*1 + b*0) + b  =  a + (a*0 + b*1).
-- LHS: a*1 = a (mulOneR), b*0 = 0 (mulZeroR), so a*1 + b*0 = a + 0 = a, hence LHS = a + b.
-- RHS: a*0 = 0 (mulZeroR), b*1 = b (mulOneR), so a*0 + b*1 = 0 + b = b, hence RHS = a + b.
-- Both reduce to a + b; the obligation is the composite of these two simplifications.
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
pmulOneR : (p : NatPair) -> ZRel (pmul p (npair (succ zero) zero)) p is
  fn (p : NatPair) is
    -- Goal: add (add (mul (fst p) 1) (mul (snd p) 0)) (snd p)
    --     = add (fst p) (add (mul (fst p) 0) (mul (snd p) 1)).
    -- LHS  -> add (add (fst p) zero) (snd p)  [mulOneR, mulZeroR]
    --      -> add (fst p) (snd p)             [addZeroR]
    -- RHS  <- add (fst p) (add zero (snd p))  [mulZeroR, mulOneR]
    --      <- add (fst p) (snd p)             [add zero (snd p) is snd p by def]
    trans
      (cong (fn (s : Nat) is add s (snd p) end)
        (trans
          (cong2 (fn (u : Nat) (v : Nat) is add u v end)
            (mulOneR (fst p))
            (mulZeroR (snd p)))
          (addZeroR (fst p))))
      (cong (fn (s : Nat) is add (fst p) s end)
        (sym
          (cong2 (fn (u : Nat) (v : Nat) is add u v end)
            (mulZeroR (fst p))
            (mulOneR (snd p)))))
  end
end

zmulOneR : (x : Z) -> Eq Z (zmul x zone) x is
  fn (x : Z) is
    qind NatPair ZRel (fn (w : Z) is Eq Z (zmul w zone) w end)
      (fn (p : NatPair) is
        qsound NatPair ZRel (pmul p (npair (succ zero) zero)) p (pmulOneR p)
      end)
      x
  end
end

-- LEFT IDENTITY: 1 * x = x, from commutativity + right identity.
zmulOneL : (x : Z) -> Eq Z (zmul zone x) x is
  fn (x : Z) is
    trans (zmulComm zone x) (zmulOneR x)
  end
end

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- ANNIHILATION: x * 0 = 0.
-- zzero = qin (0, 0). On a representative (a, b):
--   pmul (a,b) (0,0) = (a*0 + b*0, a*0 + b*0).
-- The ZRel obligation relating it to (0, 0) is
--   (a*0 + b*0) + 0  =  0 + (a*0 + b*0),
-- which after a*0 = b*0 = 0 (mulZeroR) is 0 + 0 = 0 + 0 — but we discharge it directly
-- by addComm on the two (equal) components.
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
pmulZeroR : (p : NatPair) -> ZRel (pmul p (npair zero zero)) (npair zero zero) is
  fn (p : NatPair) is
    -- Goal: add (add (mul (fst p) 0) (mul (snd p) 0)) 0
    --     = add 0 (add (mul (fst p) 0) (mul (snd p) 0)).
    addComm (add (mul (fst p) zero) (mul (snd p) zero)) zero
  end
end

zmulZeroR : (x : Z) -> Eq Z (zmul x zzero) zzero is
  fn (x : Z) is
    qind NatPair ZRel (fn (w : Z) is Eq Z (zmul w zzero) zzero end)
      (fn (p : NatPair) is
        qsound NatPair ZRel (pmul p (npair zero zero)) (npair zero zero) (pmulZeroR p)
      end)
      x
  end
end

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- LEFT-DISTRIBUTIVITY — THE RING AXIOM: x * (y + z) = x*y + x*z.
-- On representatives p=(a,b), q=(c,d), r=(e,f):
--   zadd q r = (c+e, d+f).
--   fst (pmul p (q+r)) = a*(c+e) + b*(d+f)
--   fst (padd (pmul p q) (pmul p r)) = (a*c + b*d) + (a*e + b*f)
-- a*(c+e) = a*c + a*e and b*(d+f) = b*d + b*f (mulDistL), so the LHS first component is
--   (a*c + a*e) + (b*d + b*f), which interchanges to (a*c + b*d) + (a*e + b*f) = RHS first.
-- The SECOND components are identical:
--   snd (pmul p (q+r)) = a*(d+f) + b*(c+e)
--   snd (padd …)       = (a*d + b*c) + (a*f + b*e)
-- a*(d+f) = a*d + a*f and b*(c+e) = b*c + b*e (mulDistL), interchange to
--   (a*d + b*c) + (a*f + b*e) = RHS second.
-- Both pairs of components are LITERALLY EQUAL as Nats, so the ZRel obligation is
-- discharged by cong2 into both components (each a mulDistL-then-interchange equality).
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

-- The first-component identity: a*(c+e) + b*(d+f) = (a*c + b*d) + (a*e + b*f).
pmulDistFst : (a : Nat) -> (b : Nat) -> (c : Nat) -> (d : Nat) -> (e : Nat) -> (f : Nat)
   -> Eq Nat
        (add (mul a (add c e)) (mul b (add d f)))
        (add (add (mul a c) (mul b d)) (add (mul a e) (mul b f))) is
  fn (a : Nat) (b : Nat) (c : Nat) (d : Nat) (e : Nat) (f : Nat) is
    trans
      (cong2 (fn (u : Nat) (v : Nat) is add u v end)
        (mulDistL a c e)
        (mulDistL b d f))
      (interchange (mul a c) (mul a e) (mul b d) (mul b f))
  end
end

-- pmul p (padd q r) ~ padd (pmul p q) (pmul p r): components are equal, lift to ZRel.
-- The ZRel obligation is
--   fst (pmul p (q+r)) + snd (padd (pmul p q) (pmul p r))
--     = fst (padd …) + snd (pmul p (q+r)).
-- We prove the stronger fact that fst's are equal and snd's are equal, then assemble
-- the obligation by cong2: the LHS rewrites to RHS-fst + LHS-snd, and addComm-free.
pmulDistR : (p : NatPair) -> (q : NatPair) -> (r : NatPair)
   -> ZRel (pmul p (padd q r)) (padd (pmul p q) (pmul p r)) is
  fn (p : NatPair) (q : NatPair) (r : NatPair) is
    -- Goal: add (fst (pmul p (padd q r))) (snd (padd (pmul p q) (pmul p r)))
    --     = add (fst (padd (pmul p q) (pmul p r))) (snd (pmul p (padd q r))).
    -- fst (pmul p (padd q r)) = a*(c+e) + b*(d+f)
    -- fst (padd (pmul p q) (pmul p r)) = (a*c+b*d) + (a*e+b*f)
    -- snd (pmul p (padd q r)) = a*(d+f) + b*(c+e)
    -- snd (padd (pmul p q) (pmul p r)) = (a*d+b*c) + (a*f+b*e)
    cong2 (fn (u : Nat) (v : Nat) is add u v end)
      -- fst-eq : a*(c+e) + b*(d+f) = (a*c+b*d) + (a*e+b*f)
      (pmulDistFst (fst p) (snd p) (fst q) (snd q) (fst r) (snd r))
      -- snd-eq, reversed (we need snd(padd) = snd(pmul …)):
      --   (a*d+b*c) + (a*f+b*e) = a*(d+f) + b*(c+e)
      (sym (pmulDistFst (fst p) (snd p) (snd q) (fst q) (snd r) (fst r)))
  end
end

zmulDistR : (x : Z) -> (y : Z) -> (z : Z)
   -> Eq Z (zmul x (zadd y z)) (zadd (zmul x y) (zmul x z)) is
  fn (x : Z) is
    qind NatPair ZRel
      (fn (wx : Z) is (y : Z) -> (z : Z) -> Eq Z (zmul wx (zadd y z)) (zadd (zmul wx y) (zmul wx z)) end)
      (fn (p : NatPair) is
        fn (y : Z) is
          qind NatPair ZRel
            (fn (wy : Z) is (z : Z) -> Eq Z (zmul (qin NatPair ZRel p) (zadd wy z)) (zadd (zmul (qin NatPair ZRel p) wy) (zmul (qin NatPair ZRel p) z)) end)
            (fn (q : NatPair) is
              fn (z : Z) is
                qind NatPair ZRel
                  (fn (wz : Z) is Eq Z (zmul (qin NatPair ZRel p) (zadd (qin NatPair ZRel q) wz)) (zadd (zmul (qin NatPair ZRel p) (qin NatPair ZRel q)) (zmul (qin NatPair ZRel p) wz)) end)
                  (fn (r : NatPair) is
                    qsound NatPair ZRel
                      (pmul p (padd q r)) (padd (pmul p q) (pmul p r))
                      (pmulDistR p q r)
                  end)
                  z
              end
            end)
            y
        end
      end)
      x
  end
end

-- RIGHT-DISTRIBUTIVITY: (x + y) * z = x*z + y*z, from zmulComm + zmulDistR.
--   (x+y)*z = z*(x+y)        (zmulComm)
--           = z*x + z*y      (zmulDistR)
--           = x*z + y*z      (zmulComm on each summand).
zmulDistL : (x : Z) -> (y : Z) -> (z : Z)
   -> Eq Z (zmul (zadd x y) z) (zadd (zmul x z) (zmul y z)) is
  fn (x : Z) (y : Z) (z : Z) is
    trans (zmulComm (zadd x y) z)
      (trans (zmulDistR z x y)
        (trans (cong (fn (s : Z) is zadd s (zmul z y) end) (zmulComm z x))
          (cong (fn (s : Z) is zadd (zmul x z) s end) (zmulComm z y))))
  end
end

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- ASSOCIATIVITY: (x * y) * z = x * (y * z).
-- On representatives p=(a,b), q=(c,d), r=(e,f):
--   pmul p q = (ac+bd, ad+bc).
--   pmul (pmul p q) r = ((ac+bd)*e + (ad+bc)*f, (ac+bd)*f + (ad+bc)*e).
--   pmul q r = (ce+df, cf+de).
--   pmul p (pmul q r) = (a*(ce+df) + b*(cf+de), a*(cf+de) + b*(ce+df)).
-- Both components are equal Nat semiring expressions: expand with mulDistR (left side,
-- (x+y)*z) and mulDistL (right side, x*(y+z)), reassociate each product with mulAssoc,
-- and regroup the FOUR triple-products with the interchange law. We prove each component
-- as a literal Nat equality and lift by cong2 into ZRel.
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

-- FIRST component: (ac+bd)*e + (ad+bc)*f = a*(ce+df) + b*(cf+de).
--   LHS = (ace + bde) + (adf + bcf)        [mulDistR ×2, mulAssoc ×4]
--   reorder to (ace + adf) + (bde + bcf)   [interchange]
--   RHS = (ace + adf) + (bcf + bde)        [mulDistL ×2, mulAssoc ×4]
-- so we need (bde + bcf) = (bcf + bde), an addComm, sitting in the second summand.
pmulAssocFst : (a : Nat) -> (b : Nat) -> (c : Nat) -> (d : Nat) -> (e : Nat) -> (f : Nat)
   -> Eq Nat
        (add (mul (add (mul a c) (mul b d)) e) (mul (add (mul a d) (mul b c)) f))
        (add (mul a (add (mul c e) (mul d f))) (mul b (add (mul c f) (mul d e)))) is
  fn (a : Nat) (b : Nat) (c : Nat) (d : Nat) (e : Nat) (f : Nat) is
    trans
      -- expand both products on the LHS by mulDistR:
      --   (ac+bd)*e = ac*e + bd*e ;  (ad+bc)*f = ad*f + bc*f
      (cong2 (fn (u : Nat) (v : Nat) is add u v end)
        (mulDistR (mul a c) (mul b d) e)
        (mulDistR (mul a d) (mul b c) f))
      (trans
        -- reassociate every triple product: (ac)e = a(ce), (bd)e = b(de),
        --   (ad)f = a(df), (bc)f = b(cf).
        (cong2 (fn (u : Nat) (v : Nat) is add u v end)
          (cong2 (fn (u : Nat) (v : Nat) is add u v end)
            (mulAssoc a c e)
            (mulAssoc b d e))
          (cong2 (fn (u : Nat) (v : Nat) is add u v end)
            (mulAssoc a d f)
            (mulAssoc b c f)))
        (trans
          -- now LHS = (a(ce) + b(de)) + (a(df) + b(cf));
          -- interchange to (a(ce) + a(df)) + (b(de) + b(cf)).
          (interchange (mul a (mul c e)) (mul b (mul d e)) (mul a (mul d f)) (mul b (mul c f)))
          (trans
            -- contract each summand by mulDistL (reverse):
            --   a(ce) + a(df) = a*(ce+df) ;  b(de) + b(cf) = b*(de+cf).
            (cong2 (fn (u : Nat) (v : Nat) is add u v end)
              (sym (mulDistL a (mul c e) (mul d f)))
              (sym (mulDistL b (mul d e) (mul c f))))
            -- fix the second factor of the b-term: b*(de+cf) = b*(cf+de) by addComm.
            (cong (fn (s : Nat) is add (mul a (add (mul c e) (mul d f))) (mul b s) end)
              (addComm (mul d e) (mul c f))))))
  end
end

-- pmul (pmul p q) r ~ pmul p (pmul q r): both components equal. The SECOND component
-- of (pq)r is (ac+bd)*f + (ad+bc)*e and of p(qr) is a*(cf+de) + b*(ce+df) — the SAME
-- shape as pmulAssocFst with e and f swapped, so it reuses pmulAssocFst at swapped args.
pmulAssoc : (p : NatPair) -> (q : NatPair) -> (r : NatPair)
   -> ZRel (pmul (pmul p q) r) (pmul p (pmul q r)) is
  fn (p : NatPair) (q : NatPair) (r : NatPair) is
    -- ZRel obligation:
    --   fst (pmul (pmul p q) r) + snd (pmul p (pmul q r))
    --     = fst (pmul p (pmul q r)) + snd (pmul (pmul p q) r).
    -- fst-eq : fst (pmul (pmul p q) r) = fst (pmul p (pmul q r))  [pmulAssocFst]
    -- snd-eq : snd (pmul (pmul p q) r) = snd (pmul p (pmul q r))  [pmulAssocFst, e/f swapped]
    -- assemble: cong2 add (fst-eq) (sym snd-eq).
    cong2 (fn (u : Nat) (v : Nat) is add u v end)
      (pmulAssocFst (fst p) (snd p) (fst q) (snd q) (fst r) (snd r))
      (sym (pmulAssocFst (fst p) (snd p) (fst q) (snd q) (snd r) (fst r)))
  end
end

zmulAssoc : (x : Z) -> (y : Z) -> (z : Z)
   -> Eq Z (zmul (zmul x y) z) (zmul x (zmul y z)) is
  fn (x : Z) is
    qind NatPair ZRel
      (fn (wx : Z) is (y : Z) -> (z : Z) -> Eq Z (zmul (zmul wx y) z) (zmul wx (zmul y z)) end)
      (fn (p : NatPair) is
        fn (y : Z) is
          qind NatPair ZRel
            (fn (wy : Z) is (z : Z) -> Eq Z (zmul (zmul (qin NatPair ZRel p) wy) z) (zmul (qin NatPair ZRel p) (zmul wy z)) end)
            (fn (q : NatPair) is
              fn (z : Z) is
                qind NatPair ZRel
                  (fn (wz : Z) is Eq Z (zmul (zmul (qin NatPair ZRel p) (qin NatPair ZRel q)) wz) (zmul (qin NatPair ZRel p) (zmul (qin NatPair ZRel q) wz)) end)
                  (fn (r : NatPair) is
                    qsound NatPair ZRel
                      (pmul (pmul p q) r) (pmul p (pmul q r))
                      (pmulAssoc p q r)
                  end)
                  z
              end
            end)
            y
        end
      end)
      x
  end
end

-- ============================================================================
-- Sanity: the ring laws COMPUTE through the quotient on concrete integers.
-- ============================================================================

-- (2 − 0) and (0 − 3) as explicit representatives.
zexLeft : Z is qin NatPair ZRel (npair (succ (succ zero)) zero) end
zexRight : Z is qin NatPair ZRel (npair zero (succ (succ (succ zero)))) end

-- x * 1 = x on a concrete integer, by zmulOneR.
zexOneR : Eq Z (zmul zexLeft zone) zexLeft is zmulOneR zexLeft end

-- Distributivity on concrete integers: zexLeft * (zexLeft + zexRight)
--   = zexLeft*zexLeft + zexLeft*zexRight, by zmulDistR.
zexDist : Eq Z
    (zmul zexLeft (zadd zexLeft zexRight))
    (zadd (zmul zexLeft zexLeft) (zmul zexLeft zexRight)) is
  zmulDistR zexLeft zexLeft zexRight
end

-- Associativity on concrete integers.
zexAssoc : Eq Z
    (zmul (zmul zexLeft zexRight) zexLeft)
    (zmul zexLeft (zmul zexRight zexLeft)) is
  zmulAssoc zexLeft zexRight zexLeft
end

-- ============================================================================
-- CHAPTER 108 — ℚ, THE FIELD OF FRACTIONS OVER ℤ.
-- Everything above is the ch107 ℤ-ring development, redeclared verbatim. Below is
-- the NEW rational layer: the localization of ℤ at the nonzero denominators.
-- ============================================================================

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- Two ℤ-ring lemmas the ℚ well-definedness needs, derived from ch107's axioms.
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

-- The 4-FACTOR REGROUPING in a commutative ring: (a·b)·(c·d) = (a·c)·(b·d).
-- This is the multiplicative analog of ch07/ch107's additive `interchange`, and it
-- is the workhorse of the cross-multiplication respect proofs. Pure assoc+comm:
--   (a·b)·(c·d) = a·(b·(c·d))      [zmulAssoc]
--              = a·((b·c)·d)       [sym zmulAssoc, inside]
--              = a·((c·b)·d)       [zmulComm b c, inside]
--              = a·(c·(b·d))       [zmulAssoc, inside]
--              = (a·c)·(b·d)       [sym zmulAssoc]
zmulInterchange : (a : Z) -> (b : Z) -> (c : Z) -> (d : Z)
   -> Eq Z (zmul (zmul a b) (zmul c d)) (zmul (zmul a c) (zmul b d)) is
  fn (a : Z) (b : Z) (c : Z) (d : Z) is
    trans (zmulAssoc a b (zmul c d))
      (trans
        (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul a s end) (sym (zmulAssoc b c d)))
        (trans
          (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul a (zmul s d) end) (zmulComm b c))
          (trans
            (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul a s end) (zmulAssoc c b d))
            (sym (zmulAssoc a c (zmul b d))))))
  end
end

-- The Nat→ℤ embedding `zfrom` is a MULTIPLICATIVE homomorphism:
--   zfrom (m · n) = zmul (zfrom m) (zfrom n).
-- zfrom n = qin (n, 0); zmul (zfrom m) (zfrom n) computes (by the qlift ι-rules) to
-- qin (pmul (m,0) (n,0)) = qin (mul m n + mul 0 0, mul m 0 + mul 0 n). The ZRel
-- obligation relating (mul m n, 0) to that is discharged by addZeroR / mulZeroR
-- (mul 0 _ reduces to 0 definitionally; mul m 0 needs mulZeroR).
zmulHom : (m : Nat) -> (n : Nat)
   -> Eq Z (zfrom (mul m n)) (zmul (zfrom m) (zfrom n)) is
  fn (m : Nat) (n : Nat) is
    qsound NatPair ZRel
      (npair (mul m n) zero)
      (pmul (npair m zero) (npair n zero))
      -- Goal: add (mul m n) (add (mul m zero) zero) = add (add (mul m n) zero) zero.
      (trans
        -- LHS -> mul m n
        (trans
          (cong (fn (s : Nat) is add (mul m n) s end)
            (trans (addZeroR (mul m zero)) (mulZeroR m)))
          (addZeroR (mul m n)))
        -- mul m n -> RHS
        (sym
          (trans (addZeroR (add (mul m n) zero)) (addZeroR (mul m n)))))
  end
end

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- THE REPRESENTATION.  A QPair (a, b) denotes the fraction  a / succ(b),  so the
-- denominator is structurally nonzero with no carried proof (the +1 trick). The
-- numerator is a genuine ℤ (ch107's quotient integer); the denominator is a Nat.
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

data QPair : U is
  qpair : Z -> Nat -> QPair
end

qnum : QPair -> Z is
  fn (p : QPair) is
    QPairElim (fn (x : QPair) is Z end) (fn (a : Z) (b : Nat) is a end) p
  end
end

qdenN : QPair -> Nat is
  fn (p : QPair) is
    QPairElim (fn (x : QPair) is Nat end) (fn (a : Z) (b : Nat) is b end) p
  end
end

-- The denominator as a (nonzero, positive) ℤ:  zden p = zfrom (succ (qdenN p)).
zden : QPair -> Z is
  fn (p : QPair) is zfrom (succ (qdenN p)) end
end

-- CROSS-MULTIPLICATION, in ℤ:  (a / sb) ~ (c / sd)  ⟺  a · sd = c · sb.
-- Eq Z lands in Prop (proof-irrelevant strict equality), so QRel : QPair -> QPair -> Prop.
QRel : QPair -> QPair -> Prop is
  fn (p : QPair) (q : QPair) is
    Eq Z (zmul (qnum p) (zden q)) (zmul (qnum q) (zden p))
  end
end

Q : U is Quot QPair QRel end

-- The embedding ℤ ↪ ℚ:  n ↦ n / 1.
qfromZ : Z -> Q is fn (z : Z) is qin QPair QRel (qpair z zero) end end
qzero : Q is qfromZ zzero end
qone : Q is qfromZ zone end

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- MULTIPLICATION ON REPRESENTATIVES.  (a/sb) · (c/sd) = (a·c) / (sb·sd).
-- The denominator index is chosen so that  succ (qmulDen b d) = mul (succ b) (succ d)
-- DEFINITIONALLY:  mul (succ b) (succ d) = add (succ d) (mul b (succ d))
--                                        = succ (add d (mul b (succ d))),
-- so qmulDen b d = add d (mul b (succ d)). Hence zden (qmulP p q) = zfrom (sb·sd),
-- which zmulHom turns into zmul (zden p) (zden q).
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
qmulDen : Nat -> Nat -> Nat is
  fn (b : Nat) (d : Nat) is add d (mul b (succ d)) end
end

qmulP : QPair -> QPair -> QPair is
  fn (p : QPair) (q : QPair) is
    qpair (zmul (qnum p) (qnum q)) (qmulDen (qdenN p) (qdenN q))
  end
end

-- zden (qmulP p q) = zmul (zden p) (zden q).  By construction the denominator index
-- gives  succ (qmulDen (qdenN p) (qdenN q)) = mul (succ (qdenN p)) (succ (qdenN q))
-- definitionally, so zden (qmulP p q) = zfrom (mul (succ b) (succ d)) and zmulHom closes it.
qmulDenZ : (p : QPair) -> (q : QPair)
   -> Eq Z (zden (qmulP p q)) (zmul (zden p) (zden q)) is
  fn (p : QPair) (q : QPair) is
    zmulHom (succ (qdenN p)) (succ (qdenN q))
  end
end

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- WELL-DEFINEDNESS — the cross-multiplication respect proof (the analog of ch105's
-- pmulRespL/R one level up).  We must show qmulP respects QRel in each argument.
--
-- RIGHT respect: given QRel q q'  (i.e.  nq · zden q' = nq' · zden q),
--   QRel (qmulP p q) (qmulP p q'),  i.e.
--   (np·nq) · zden(qmulP p q')  =  (np·nq') · zden(qmulP p q).
-- Rewrite both denominators by qmulDenZ to zmul (zden p) (zden _), regroup the four
-- ℤ-factors with zmulInterchange so the q-vs-q' data line up, apply the hypothesis,
-- and regroup back.
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
qmulRespR : (p : QPair) -> (q : QPair) -> (q' : QPair) ->
    QRel q q' -> QRel (qmulP p q) (qmulP p q') is
  fn (p : QPair) (q : QPair) (q' : QPair) (h : QRel q q') is
    -- Goal: zmul (zmul (qnum p) (qnum q)) (zden (qmulP p q'))
    --     = zmul (zmul (qnum p) (qnum q')) (zden (qmulP p q)).
    trans
      -- rewrite the right denominator: zden (qmulP p q') = zmul (zden p) (zden q')
      (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul (zmul (qnum p) (qnum q)) s end) (qmulDenZ p q'))
      (trans
        -- ((np·nq)·(zb·zd')) = ((np·zb)·(nq·zd'))   [zmulInterchange]
        (zmulInterchange (qnum p) (qnum q) (zden p) (zden q'))
        (trans
          -- apply the hypothesis inside the second factor: nq·zd' = nq'·zd
          (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul (zmul (qnum p) (zden p)) s end) h)
          (trans
            -- ((np·zb)·(nq'·zd)) = ((np·nq')·(zb·zd))   [sym zmulInterchange]
            (sym (zmulInterchange (qnum p) (qnum q') (zden p) (zden q)))
            -- fold the denominator back: zmul (zden p) (zden q) = zden (qmulP p q)
            (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul (zmul (qnum p) (qnum q')) s end)
              (sym (qmulDenZ p q))))))
  end
end

-- LEFT respect: given QRel p p'  (np · zden p' = np' · zden p),
--   QRel (qmulP p q) (qmulP p' q). Same algebra with the p-data crossing.
qmulRespL : (p : QPair) -> (p' : QPair) -> (q : QPair) ->
    QRel p p' -> QRel (qmulP p q) (qmulP p' q) is
  fn (p : QPair) (p' : QPair) (q : QPair) (h : QRel p p') is
    -- Goal: zmul (zmul (qnum p) (qnum q)) (zden (qmulP p' q))
    --     = zmul (zmul (qnum p') (qnum q)) (zden (qmulP p q)).
    trans
      (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul (zmul (qnum p) (qnum q)) s end) (qmulDenZ p' q))
      (trans
        -- ((np·nq)·(zb'·zd)) = ((np·zb')·(nq·zd))   [zmulInterchange]
        (zmulInterchange (qnum p) (qnum q) (zden p') (zden q))
        (trans
          -- apply hypothesis in the FIRST factor: np·zb' = np'·zb
          (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul s (zmul (qnum q) (zden q)) end) h)
          (trans
            -- ((np'·zb)·(nq·zd)) = ((np'·nq)·(zb·zd))   [sym zmulInterchange]
            (sym (zmulInterchange (qnum p') (qnum q) (zden p) (zden q)))
            (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul (zmul (qnum p') (qnum q)) s end)
              (sym (qmulDenZ p q))))))
  end
end

-- Lift qmulP through QRel, twice (the ch105/ch107 double-qind pattern).
qmulR : QPair -> Q -> Q is
  fn (p : QPair) is
    qlift QPair QRel Q
      (fn (q : QPair) is qin QPair QRel (qmulP p q) end)
      (fn (q : QPair) (q' : QPair) (r : QRel q q') is
        qsound QPair QRel (qmulP p q) (qmulP p q') (qmulRespR p q q' r)
      end)
  end
end

qmul : Q -> Q -> Q is
  qlift QPair QRel (Q -> Q) qmulR
    (fn (p : QPair) (p' : QPair) (r : QRel p p') is
      fn (z : Q) is
        qind QPair QRel (fn (w : Q) is Eq Q (qmulR p w) (qmulR p' w) end)
          (fn (q : QPair) is
            qsound QPair QRel (qmulP p q) (qmulP p' q) (qmulRespL p p' q r)
          end)
          z
      end
    end)
end

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- THE FIELD LAW: COMMUTATIVITY OF ℚ MULTIPLICATION.  x · y = y · x.
-- On representatives, qmulP p q and qmulP q p relate by QRel because the numerators
-- commute (zmulComm) and the denominators commute, lined up by zmulInterchange.
--   QRel (qmulP p q) (qmulP q p)  needs
--     (np·nq) · zden(qmulP q p) = (nq·np) · zden(qmulP p q).
-- Rewrite both denominators (qmulDenZ); the obligation is then a pure ℤ identity:
--   (np·nq)·(zd·zb) = (nq·np)·(zb·zd), from zmulComm (numerators), zmulComm
--   (denominators), assembled by cong2.
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
cong2Z : (f : Z -> Z -> Z) -> {x : Z} -> {y : Z} -> {u : Z} -> {v : Z}
     -> Eq Z x y -> Eq Z u v -> Eq Z (f x u) (f y v) is
  fn (f : Z -> Z -> Z) {x : Z} {y : Z} {u : Z} {v : Z} (p : Eq Z x y) (q : Eq Z u v) is
    trans (cong (fn (z : Z) is f z u end) p) (cong (fn (z : Z) is f y z end) q)
  end
end

qmulCommP : (p : QPair) -> (q : QPair) -> QRel (qmulP p q) (qmulP q p) is
  fn (p : QPair) (q : QPair) is
    -- Goal: zmul (zmul (qnum p) (qnum q)) (zden (qmulP q p))
    --     = zmul (zmul (qnum q) (qnum p)) (zden (qmulP p q)).
    trans
      (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul (zmul (qnum p) (qnum q)) s end) (qmulDenZ q p))
      (trans
        -- (np·nq)·(zd·zb) = (nq·np)·(zb·zd) by commuting both factors of each product
        (cong2Z (fn (u : Z) (v : Z) is zmul u v end)
          (zmulComm (qnum p) (qnum q))
          (zmulComm (zden q) (zden p)))
        (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul (zmul (qnum q) (qnum p)) s end)
          (sym (qmulDenZ p q))))
  end
end

qmulComm : (x : Q) -> (y : Q) -> Eq Q (qmul x y) (qmul y x) is
  fn (x : Q) is
    qind QPair QRel (fn (w : Q) is (y : Q) -> Eq Q (qmul w y) (qmul y w) end)
      (fn (p : QPair) is
        fn (y : Q) is
          qind QPair QRel
            (fn (w : Q) is Eq Q (qmul (qin QPair QRel p) w) (qmul w (qin QPair QRel p)) end)
            (fn (q : QPair) is
              qsound QPair QRel (qmulP p q) (qmulP q p) (qmulCommP p q)
            end)
            y
        end
      end)
      x
  end
end

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- Sanity: ℚ multiplication COMPUTES through the quotient on concrete rationals.
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

-- 1/2 (numerator 1, denominator succ 1 = 2) and 2/1 (numerator 2, denominator succ 0 = 1).
qHalf : Q is qin QPair QRel (qpair zone (succ zero)) end
qTwoOverOne : Q is qin QPair QRel (qpair (zfrom (succ (succ zero))) zero) end

-- 1/2 · 2/1 = (1·2)/(2·1) = 2/2, which qsound identifies with 1/1 = qone:
--   (1·2)/2 ~ 1/1  ⟺  (1·2)·1 = 1·2   (cross-multiply in ℤ), true by refl after the
-- numerators/denominators compute. We state the well-definedness witness as a QRel and
-- feed it to qsound to obtain the propositional identity 2/2 ~ 1/1.
qHalfTimesTwo : Q is qmul qHalf qTwoOverOne end

-- 2/2 ~ 1/1: the QRel obligation is  (1·2) · succ 0  =  1 · succ (succ 0)  in ℤ,
-- i.e.  zmul (zmul zone (zfrom 2)) (zfrom 1)  =  zmul zone (zfrom 2)  — both sides reduce
-- to the integer 2; discharge by the ℤ ring identity (zmulOneL on the right, after
-- zmulOneR on the spurious unit denominator on the left).
qTwoHalves : Q is qin QPair QRel (qpair (zmul zone (zfrom (succ (succ zero)))) (succ zero)) end

-- The computing example, fully proven: qmul qHalf qTwoOverOne IS the rational 2/2.
qMulComputes : Eq Q (qmul qHalf qTwoOverOne) qTwoHalves is
  refl (qmul qHalf qTwoOverOne)
end

-- Commutativity on these concrete rationals, by qmulComm.
qExComm : Eq Q (qmul qHalf qTwoOverOne) (qmul qTwoOverOne qHalf) is
  qmulComm qHalf qTwoOverOne
end

-- ============================================================================
-- CH108, PART II — ℚ ADDITION, and the field law qaddComm.
-- (a/sb) + (c/sd) = (a·sd + c·sb) / (sb·sd).  Well-definedness is the cross-
-- multiplication argument using zmulDistL (distributivity) + zmulInterchange + the
-- ℤ ring commutativity, mirroring qmulRespL/R with an extra distributivity step.
-- ============================================================================

-- ℤ addition is commutative — lift padd's componentwise addComm through ZRel.
-- padd p q ~ padd q p on representatives: both components commute by addComm.
paddComm : (p : NatPair) -> (q : NatPair) -> ZRel (padd p q) (padd q p) is
  fn (p : NatPair) (q : NatPair) is
    -- Goal: add (add (fst p) (fst q)) (add (snd q) (snd p))
    --     = add (add (fst q) (fst p)) (add (snd p) (snd q)).
    cong2 (fn (u : Nat) (v : Nat) is add u v end)
      (addComm (fst p) (fst q))
      (addComm (snd q) (snd p))
  end
end

zaddComm : (x : Z) -> (y : Z) -> Eq Z (zadd x y) (zadd y x) is
  fn (x : Z) is
    qind NatPair ZRel (fn (w : Z) is (y : Z) -> Eq Z (zadd w y) (zadd y w) end)
      (fn (p : NatPair) is
        fn (y : Z) is
          qind NatPair ZRel
            (fn (w : Z) is Eq Z (zadd (qin NatPair ZRel p) w) (zadd w (qin NatPair ZRel p)) end)
            (fn (q : NatPair) is
              qsound NatPair ZRel (padd p q) (padd q p) (paddComm p q)
            end)
            y
        end
      end)
      x
  end
end

-- ADDITION ON REPRESENTATIVES.  Numerator a·sd + c·sb; denominator the SAME product
-- index as multiplication, so zden (qaddP p q) = zmul (zden p) (zden q) by qmulDenZ.
qaddP : QPair -> QPair -> QPair is
  fn (p : QPair) (q : QPair) is
    qpair
      (zadd (zmul (qnum p) (zden q)) (zmul (qnum q) (zden p)))
      (qmulDen (qdenN p) (qdenN q))
  end
end

-- zden (qaddP p q) = zmul (zden p) (zden q) — same denominator index as qmulP.
qaddDenZ : (p : QPair) -> (q : QPair)
   -> Eq Z (zden (qaddP p q)) (zmul (zden p) (zden q)) is
  fn (p : QPair) (q : QPair) is
    zmulHom (succ (qdenN p)) (succ (qdenN q))
  end
end

-- RIGHT respect.  Given QRel q q' (nq·zd' = nq'·zd), show QRel (qaddP p q) (qaddP p q').
-- The numerator is a SUM, so distribute (zmulDistL) over the denominator product, then
-- handle the two terms:
--   term1 (np·zd)·(zb·zd') = (np·zd')·(zb·zd)   — pure regrouping, no hypothesis
--   term2 (nq·zb)·(zb·zd') = (nq'·zb)·(zb·zd)   — uses the hypothesis nq·zd' = nq'·zd
-- and reassemble with cong2Z.
qaddRespR : (p : QPair) -> (q : QPair) -> (q' : QPair) ->
    QRel q q' -> QRel (qaddP p q) (qaddP p q') is
  fn (p : QPair) (q : QPair) (q' : QPair) (h : QRel q q') is
    -- Goal: zmul (zadd (np·zd) (nq·zb)) (zden (qaddP p q'))
    --     = zmul (zadd (np·zd') (nq'·zb)) (zden (qaddP p q)).
    trans
      (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul (zadd (zmul (qnum p) (zden q)) (zmul (qnum q) (zden p))) s end)
        (qaddDenZ p q'))
      (trans
        -- distribute the LHS over (zb·zd')
        (zmulDistL (zmul (qnum p) (zden q)) (zmul (qnum q) (zden p)) (zmul (zden p) (zden q')))
        (trans
          (cong2Z (fn (u : Z) (v : Z) is zadd u v end)
            -- term1: (np·zd)·(zb·zd') = (np·zd')·(zb·zd)
            (trans (zmulInterchange (qnum p) (zden q) (zden p) (zden q'))
              (trans (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul (zmul (qnum p) (zden p)) s end)
                       (zmulComm (zden q) (zden q')))
                (sym (zmulInterchange (qnum p) (zden q') (zden p) (zden q)))))
            -- term2: (nq·zb)·(zb·zd') = (nq'·zb)·(zb·zd), via the hypothesis
            (trans (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul (zmul (qnum q) (zden p)) s end)
                     (zmulComm (zden p) (zden q')))
              (trans (zmulInterchange (qnum q) (zden p) (zden q') (zden p))
                (trans (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul s (zmul (zden p) (zden p)) end) h)
                  (trans (sym (zmulInterchange (qnum q') (zden p) (zden q) (zden p)))
                    (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul (zmul (qnum q') (zden p)) s end)
                      (zmulComm (zden q) (zden p))))))))
          -- reassemble: zadd (…) (…) = zmul (zadd (np·zd') (nq'·zb)) (zden (qaddP p q))
          (trans
            (sym (zmulDistL (zmul (qnum p) (zden q')) (zmul (qnum q') (zden p)) (zmul (zden p) (zden q))))
            (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul (zadd (zmul (qnum p) (zden q')) (zmul (qnum q') (zden p))) s end)
              (sym (qaddDenZ p q))))))
  end
end

-- LEFT respect.  Given QRel p p' (np·zb' = np'·zb), show QRel (qaddP p q) (qaddP p' q).
qaddRespL : (p : QPair) -> (p' : QPair) -> (q : QPair) ->
    QRel p p' -> QRel (qaddP p q) (qaddP p' q) is
  fn (p : QPair) (p' : QPair) (q : QPair) (h : QRel p p') is
    -- Goal: zmul (zadd (np·zd) (nq·zb)) (zden (qaddP p' q))
    --     = zmul (zadd (np'·zd) (nq·zb')) (zden (qaddP p q)).
    trans
      (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul (zadd (zmul (qnum p) (zden q)) (zmul (qnum q) (zden p))) s end)
        (qaddDenZ p' q))
      (trans
        (zmulDistL (zmul (qnum p) (zden q)) (zmul (qnum q) (zden p)) (zmul (zden p') (zden q)))
        (trans
          (cong2Z (fn (u : Z) (v : Z) is zadd u v end)
            -- term1: (np·zd)·(zb'·zd) = (np'·zd)·(zb·zd), via hypothesis np·zb' = np'·zb
            (trans (zmulInterchange (qnum p) (zden q) (zden p') (zden q))
              (trans (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul s (zmul (zden q) (zden q)) end) h)
                (sym (zmulInterchange (qnum p') (zden q) (zden p) (zden q)))))
            -- term2: (nq·zb)·(zb'·zd) = (nq·zb')·(zb·zd), pure regrouping (one interchange)
            (zmulInterchange (qnum q) (zden p) (zden p') (zden q)))
          (trans
            (sym (zmulDistL (zmul (qnum p') (zden q)) (zmul (qnum q) (zden p')) (zmul (zden p) (zden q))))
            (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul (zadd (zmul (qnum p') (zden q)) (zmul (qnum q) (zden p'))) s end)
              (sym (qaddDenZ p q))))))
  end
end

qaddR : QPair -> Q -> Q is
  fn (p : QPair) is
    qlift QPair QRel Q
      (fn (q : QPair) is qin QPair QRel (qaddP p q) end)
      (fn (q : QPair) (q' : QPair) (r : QRel q q') is
        qsound QPair QRel (qaddP p q) (qaddP p q') (qaddRespR p q q' r)
      end)
  end
end

qadd : Q -> Q -> Q is
  qlift QPair QRel (Q -> Q) qaddR
    (fn (p : QPair) (p' : QPair) (r : QRel p p') is
      fn (z : Q) is
        qind QPair QRel (fn (w : Q) is Eq Q (qaddR p w) (qaddR p' w) end)
          (fn (q : QPair) is
            qsound QPair QRel (qaddP p q) (qaddP p' q) (qaddRespL p p' q r)
          end)
          z
      end
    end)
end

-- THE FIELD LAW: COMMUTATIVITY OF ℚ ADDITION.  x + y = y + x.
-- On representatives, qaddP p q ~ qaddP q p: the numerators commute (the two summands
-- swap, zaddComm) and the denominators commute (zmulComm), lined up via the same
-- denominator-rewrite + cong2 assembly as qmulCommP.
qaddCommP : (p : QPair) -> (q : QPair) -> QRel (qaddP p q) (qaddP q p) is
  fn (p : QPair) (q : QPair) is
    -- Goal: zmul (zadd (np·zd) (nq·zb)) (zden (qaddP q p))
    --     = zmul (zadd (nq·zb) (np·zd)) (zden (qaddP p q)).
    trans
      (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul (zadd (zmul (qnum p) (zden q)) (zmul (qnum q) (zden p))) s end)
        (qaddDenZ q p))
      (trans
        (cong2Z (fn (u : Z) (v : Z) is zmul u v end)
          (zaddComm (zmul (qnum p) (zden q)) (zmul (qnum q) (zden p)))
          (zmulComm (zden q) (zden p)))
        (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul (zadd (zmul (qnum q) (zden p)) (zmul (qnum p) (zden q))) s end)
          (sym (qaddDenZ p q))))
  end
end

qaddComm : (x : Q) -> (y : Q) -> Eq Q (qadd x y) (qadd y x) is
  fn (x : Q) is
    qind QPair QRel (fn (w : Q) is (y : Q) -> Eq Q (qadd w y) (qadd y w) end)
      (fn (p : QPair) is
        fn (y : Q) is
          qind QPair QRel
            (fn (w : Q) is Eq Q (qadd (qin QPair QRel p) w) (qadd w (qin QPair QRel p)) end)
            (fn (q : QPair) is
              qsound QPair QRel (qaddP p q) (qaddP q p) (qaddCommP p q)
            end)
            y
        end
      end)
      x
  end
end

-- Sanity: 1/2 + 1/2 = 1.  On representatives (1, succ 0) + (1, succ 0):
--   numerator = 1·2 + 1·2,  denominator index succ (qmulDen 1 1) = 2·2 = 4, i.e. 4/4-style;
-- it qsound-relates to 1/1 = qone. We pin the COMPUTED representative and prove it commutes.
qHalfPlusHalf : Q is qadd qHalf qHalf end

-- qadd qHalf qHalf computes to the explicit representative below (refl through the quotient).
qHalfSumRep : Q is
  qin QPair QRel
    (qpair (zadd (zmul zone (zden (qpair zone (succ zero))))
                 (zmul zone (zden (qpair zone (succ zero)))))
           (qmulDen (succ zero) (succ zero)))
end

qAddComputes : Eq Q (qadd qHalf qHalf) qHalfSumRep is
  refl (qadd qHalf qHalf)
end

-- Addition commutes on concrete rationals, by qaddComm.
qExAddComm : Eq Q (qadd qHalf qTwoOverOne) (qadd qTwoOverOne qHalf) is
  qaddComm qHalf qTwoOverOne
end

-- ============================================================================
-- CHAPTER 113 — CLOSING THE RING + FIELD STRUCTURE OF ℚ.
-- Everything above is the ch108 ℚ development (itself over the ch107 ℤ ring),
-- redeclared verbatim. Below: the remaining ring identities/axioms and the field
-- inverse. We first add the two ℤ lemmas ch108 omitted (zaddZeroR, zaddAssoc) and
-- a left-zero (zmulZeroL), then lift the ℚ ring laws through qind.
-- ============================================================================

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- ℤ lemmas needed below (proven exactly as ch103/ch107, using ch108's Nat lemmas).
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

-- LEFT ZERO: 0 · x = 0, from commutativity + zmulZeroR.
zmulZeroL : (x : Z) -> Eq Z (zmul zzero x) zzero is
  fn (x : Z) is
    trans (zmulComm zzero x) (zmulZeroR x)
  end
end

-- ADDITIVE RIGHT IDENTITY: z + 0 = z (ch103, restated with ch108's addZeroR).
zaddZeroR : (z : Z) -> Eq Z (zadd z zzero) z is
  fn (z : Z) is
    qind NatPair ZRel (fn (w : Z) is Eq Z (zadd w zzero) w end)
      (fn (p : NatPair) is
        qsound NatPair ZRel (padd p (npair zero zero)) p
          (trans (cong (fn (s : Nat) is add s (snd p) end) (addZeroR (fst p)))
            (cong (fn (s : Nat) is add (fst p) s end) (sym (addZeroR (snd p)))))
      end)
      z
  end
end

-- ADDITIVE ASSOCIATIVITY: (x + y) + z = x + (y + z) (ch103, verbatim).
zaddAssoc : (x : Z) -> (y : Z) -> (z : Z) ->
    Eq Z (zadd (zadd x y) z) (zadd x (zadd y z)) is
  fn (x : Z) is
    qind NatPair ZRel
      (fn (wx : Z) is (y : Z) -> (z : Z) -> Eq Z (zadd (zadd wx y) z) (zadd wx (zadd y z)) end)
      (fn (p : NatPair) is
        fn (y : Z) is
          qind NatPair ZRel
            (fn (wy : Z) is (z : Z) -> Eq Z (zadd (zadd (qin NatPair ZRel p) wy) z) (zadd (qin NatPair ZRel p) (zadd wy z)) end)
            (fn (q : NatPair) is
              fn (z : Z) is
                qind NatPair ZRel
                  (fn (wz : Z) is Eq Z (zadd (zadd (qin NatPair ZRel p) (qin NatPair ZRel q)) wz) (zadd (qin NatPair ZRel p) (zadd (qin NatPair ZRel q) wz)) end)
                  (fn (r : NatPair) is
                    qsound NatPair ZRel
                      (padd (padd p q) r) (padd p (padd q r))
                      (trans (cong (fn (s : Nat) is add s (add (snd p) (add (snd q) (snd r))) end)
                                (addAssoc (fst p) (fst q) (fst r)))
                        (cong (fn (s : Nat) is add (add (fst p) (add (fst q) (fst r))) s end)
                                (sym (addAssoc (snd p) (snd q) (snd r)))))
                  end)
                  z
              end
            end)
            y
        end
      end)
      x
  end
end

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- RING IDENTITY (×):  x · 1 = x.   qone = qin (1/1).
-- On a representative p: qmulP p (1,0) = ((np·1) / (zb·1)), and the QRel obligation
--   (np·1)·zb = np·(zb·1)  reduces — both sides to np·zb — by zmulOneR twice + qmulDenZ.
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
qmulOneRP : (p : QPair) -> QRel (qmulP p (qpair zone zero)) p is
  fn (p : QPair) is
    -- Goal: zmul (zmul (qnum p) zone) (zden p) = zmul (qnum p) (zden (qmulP p (qpair zone zero)))
    trans
      (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul s (zden p) end) (zmulOneR (qnum p)))
      (sym
        (trans
          (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul (qnum p) s end) (qmulDenZ p (qpair zone zero)))
          (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul (qnum p) s end) (zmulOneR (zden p)))))
  end
end

qmulOneR : (x : Q) -> Eq Q (qmul x qone) x is
  fn (x : Q) is
    qind QPair QRel (fn (w : Q) is Eq Q (qmul w qone) w end)
      (fn (p : QPair) is
        qsound QPair QRel (qmulP p (qpair zone zero)) p (qmulOneRP p)
      end)
      x
  end
end

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- RING IDENTITY (+):  x + 0 = x.   qzero = qin (0/1).
-- On p: qaddP p (0,0) numerator = (np·1) + (0·zb) = np; denominator = zb·1 = zb.
-- The QRel obligation np·zb = np·zb after the numerator collapses (zmulOneR + zmulZeroL
-- + zaddZeroR) and the denominator collapses (qaddDenZ + zmulOneR).
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
qaddZeroP : (p : QPair) -> QRel (qaddP p (qpair zzero zero)) p is
  fn (p : QPair) is
    -- Goal: zmul (zadd (zmul (qnum p) zone) (zmul zzero (zden p))) (zden p)
    --     = zmul (qnum p) (zden (qaddP p (qpair zzero zero)))
    trans
      (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul s (zden p) end)
        (trans
          (cong2Z (fn (u : Z) (v : Z) is zadd u v end)
            (zmulOneR (qnum p))
            (zmulZeroL (zden p)))
          (zaddZeroR (qnum p))))
      (sym
        (trans
          (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul (qnum p) s end) (qaddDenZ p (qpair zzero zero)))
          (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul (qnum p) s end) (zmulOneR (zden p)))))
  end
end

qaddZero : (x : Q) -> Eq Q (qadd x qzero) x is
  fn (x : Q) is
    qind QPair QRel (fn (w : Q) is Eq Q (qadd w qzero) w end)
      (fn (p : QPair) is
        qsound QPair QRel (qaddP p (qpair zzero zero)) p (qaddZeroP p)
      end)
      x
  end
end

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- RING AXIOM (× ASSOCIATIVITY):  (x · y) · z = x · (y · z).
-- Triple qind. On representatives the numerators are zmulAssoc-equal and the
-- denominators (after qmulDenZ unfolds each product) are zmulAssoc-equal, so the
-- cross-multiplied QRel obligation is cong2Z (numerator-assoc) (denominator-assoc).
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
qmulAssocP : (p : QPair) -> (q : QPair) -> (r : QPair)
   -> QRel (qmulP (qmulP p q) r) (qmulP p (qmulP q r)) is
  fn (p : QPair) (q : QPair) (r : QPair) is
    -- Goal: zmul (zmul (zmul (qnum p) (qnum q)) (qnum r)) (zden (qmulP p (qmulP q r)))
    --     = zmul (zmul (qnum p) (zmul (qnum q) (qnum r))) (zden (qmulP (qmulP p q) r))
    trans
      -- rewrite RHS denominator -> zmul (zden p) (zmul (zden q) (zden r))
      (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul (zmul (zmul (qnum p) (qnum q)) (qnum r)) s end)
        (trans (qmulDenZ p (qmulP q r))
          (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul (zden p) s end) (qmulDenZ q r))))
      (trans
        -- numerator-assoc + denominator (right-grouped -> left-grouped)
        (cong2Z (fn (u : Z) (v : Z) is zmul u v end)
          (zmulAssoc (qnum p) (qnum q) (qnum r))
          (sym (zmulAssoc (zden p) (zden q) (zden r))))
        -- fold the (now left-grouped) denominator back to zden (qmulP (qmulP p q) r)
        (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul (zmul (qnum p) (zmul (qnum q) (qnum r))) s end)
          (sym (trans (qmulDenZ (qmulP p q) r)
            (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul s (zden r) end) (qmulDenZ p q))))))
  end
end

qmulAssoc : (x : Q) -> (y : Q) -> (z : Q)
   -> Eq Q (qmul (qmul x y) z) (qmul x (qmul y z)) is
  fn (x : Q) is
    qind QPair QRel
      (fn (wx : Q) is (y : Q) -> (z : Q) -> Eq Q (qmul (qmul wx y) z) (qmul wx (qmul y z)) end)
      (fn (p : QPair) is
        fn (y : Q) is
          qind QPair QRel
            (fn (wy : Q) is (z : Q) -> Eq Q (qmul (qmul (qin QPair QRel p) wy) z) (qmul (qin QPair QRel p) (qmul wy z)) end)
            (fn (q : QPair) is
              fn (z : Q) is
                qind QPair QRel
                  (fn (wz : Q) is Eq Q (qmul (qmul (qin QPair QRel p) (qin QPair QRel q)) wz) (qmul (qin QPair QRel p) (qmul (qin QPair QRel q) wz)) end)
                  (fn (r : QPair) is
                    qsound QPair QRel
                      (qmulP (qmulP p q) r) (qmulP p (qmulP q r))
                      (qmulAssocP p q r)
                  end)
                  z
              end
            end)
            y
        end
      end)
      x
  end
end

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- RING AXIOM (+ ASSOCIATIVITY):  (x + y) + z = x + (y + z).
-- The cross-multiplication obligation, with all denominators rewritten to products
-- by qaddDenZ, is the pure ℤ identity below in the six values a,b,c (numerators)
-- and x,y,z (denominators). Both numerators equal  a·y·z + b·x·z + c·x·y  (modulo
-- ℤ assoc/comm), and the two outer denominators are zmulAssoc-equal; assemble by cong2Z.
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

-- numerator identity:  ((a·y + b·x)·z + c·(x·y))  =  (a·(y·z) + (b·z + c·y)·x).
qaddAssocNum : (a : Z) -> (b : Z) -> (c : Z) -> (x : Z) -> (y : Z) -> (z : Z)
   -> Eq Z
        (zadd (zmul (zadd (zmul a y) (zmul b x)) z) (zmul c (zmul x y)))
        (zadd (zmul a (zmul y z)) (zmul (zadd (zmul b z) (zmul c y)) x)) is
  fn (a : Z) (b : Z) (c : Z) (x : Z) (y : Z) (z : Z) is
    trans
      -- distribute the first product:  (a·y + b·x)·z = (a·y)·z + (b·x)·z
      (cong (fn (s : Z) is zadd s (zmul c (zmul x y)) end)
        (zmulDistL (zmul a y) (zmul b x) z))
      (trans
        -- reassociate the outer sum to the right
        (zaddAssoc (zmul (zmul a y) z) (zmul (zmul b x) z) (zmul c (zmul x y)))
        (trans
          -- term-by-term match against the RHS (after distributing its second product)
          (cong2Z (fn (u : Z) (v : Z) is zadd u v end)
            -- T1: (a·y)·z = a·(y·z)
            (zmulAssoc a y z)
            (cong2Z (fn (u : Z) (v : Z) is zadd u v end)
              -- T2: (b·x)·z = (b·z)·x
              (trans (zmulAssoc b x z)
                (trans (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul b s end) (zmulComm x z))
                  (sym (zmulAssoc b z x))))
              -- T3: c·(x·y) = (c·y)·x
              (trans (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul c s end) (zmulComm x y))
                (sym (zmulAssoc c y x)))))
          -- fold RHS second product back:  (b·z)·x + (c·y)·x = (b·z + c·y)·x
          (cong (fn (s : Z) is zadd (zmul a (zmul y z)) s end)
            (sym (zmulDistL (zmul b z) (zmul c y) x)))))
  end
end

-- The full QRel obligation, threading qaddDenZ on each of the four denominator
-- occurrences and dispatching the resulting pure-ℤ identity by qaddAssocNum.
qaddAssocP : (p : QPair) -> (q : QPair) -> (r : QPair)
   -> QRel (qaddP (qaddP p q) r) (qaddP p (qaddP q r)) is
  fn (p : QPair) (q : QPair) (r : QPair) is
    trans
      -- (1a) rewrite the inner denominator zden (qaddP p q) -> zmul (zden p) (zden q)
      (cong (fn (s : Z) is
               zmul (zadd (zmul (zadd (zmul (qnum p) (zden q)) (zmul (qnum q) (zden p))) (zden r))
                          (zmul (qnum r) s))
                    (zden (qaddP p (qaddP q r))) end)
        (qaddDenZ p q))
      (trans
        -- (1b) rewrite the outer right denominator -> zmul (zden p) (zmul (zden q) (zden r))
        (cong (fn (s : Z) is
                 zmul (zadd (zmul (zadd (zmul (qnum p) (zden q)) (zmul (qnum q) (zden p))) (zden r))
                            (zmul (qnum r) (zmul (zden p) (zden q))))
                      s end)
          (trans (qaddDenZ p (qaddP q r))
            (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul (zden p) s end) (qaddDenZ q r))))
        (trans
          -- (2) the pure ℤ identity: numerator by qaddAssocNum, denominator by zmulAssoc
          (cong2Z (fn (u : Z) (v : Z) is zmul u v end)
            (qaddAssocNum (qnum p) (qnum q) (qnum r) (zden p) (zden q) (zden r))
            (sym (zmulAssoc (zden p) (zden q) (zden r))))
          (trans
            -- (3a) fold zmul (zden q) (zden r) back to zden (qaddP q r) in the numerator
            (cong (fn (s : Z) is
                     zmul (zadd (zmul (qnum p) s)
                                (zmul (zadd (zmul (qnum q) (zden r)) (zmul (qnum r) (zden q))) (zden p)))
                          (zmul (zmul (zden p) (zden q)) (zden r)) end)
              (sym (qaddDenZ q r)))
            -- (3b) fold the outer left denominator back to zden (qaddP (qaddP p q) r)
            (cong (fn (s : Z) is
                     zmul (zadd (zmul (qnum p) (zden (qaddP q r)))
                                (zmul (zadd (zmul (qnum q) (zden r)) (zmul (qnum r) (zden q))) (zden p)))
                          s end)
              (sym (trans (qaddDenZ (qaddP p q) r)
                (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul s (zden r) end) (qaddDenZ p q))))))))
  end
end

qaddAssoc : (x : Q) -> (y : Q) -> (z : Q)
   -> Eq Q (qadd (qadd x y) z) (qadd x (qadd y z)) is
  fn (x : Q) is
    qind QPair QRel
      (fn (wx : Q) is (y : Q) -> (z : Q) -> Eq Q (qadd (qadd wx y) z) (qadd wx (qadd y z)) end)
      (fn (p : QPair) is
        fn (y : Q) is
          qind QPair QRel
            (fn (wy : Q) is (z : Q) -> Eq Q (qadd (qadd (qin QPair QRel p) wy) z) (qadd (qin QPair QRel p) (qadd wy z)) end)
            (fn (q : QPair) is
              fn (z : Q) is
                qind QPair QRel
                  (fn (wz : Q) is Eq Q (qadd (qadd (qin QPair QRel p) (qin QPair QRel q)) wz) (qadd (qin QPair QRel p) (qadd (qin QPair QRel q) wz)) end)
                  (fn (r : QPair) is
                    qsound QPair QRel
                      (qaddP (qaddP p q) r) (qaddP p (qaddP q r))
                      (qaddAssocP p q r)
                  end)
                  z
              end
            end)
            y
        end
      end)
      x
  end
end

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- RING AXIOM (LEFT DISTRIBUTIVITY):  x · (y + z) = x·y + x·z.   The heaviest law.
-- After rewriting every denominator to a product, the cross-multiplication obligation
-- is the pure ℤ identity  numL · denR = numR · denL  where, crucially,
--   numR = zp · numL   and   denR = zp · denL
-- (the RHS carries an extra factor zp from the duplicated denominator), so the identity
-- collapses to a pure assoc/comm rearrangement once those two factorings are supplied.
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

-- denominator factoring:  (zp·zq)·(zp·zr) = zp·(zp·(zq·zr)).
qmulDistDen : (zp : Z) -> (zq : Z) -> (zr : Z)
   -> Eq Z (zmul (zmul zp zq) (zmul zp zr)) (zmul zp (zmul zp (zmul zq zr))) is
  fn (zp : Z) (zq : Z) (zr : Z) is
    trans (zmulInterchange zp zq zp zr) (zmulAssoc zp zp (zmul zq zr))
  end
end

-- numerator factoring:
--   (np·nq)·(zp·zr) + (np·nr)·(zp·zq)  =  zp·(np·(nq·zr + nr·zq)).
qmulDistNum : (np : Z) -> (nq : Z) -> (nr : Z) -> (zp : Z) -> (zq : Z) -> (zr : Z)
   -> Eq Z
        (zadd (zmul (zmul np nq) (zmul zp zr)) (zmul (zmul np nr) (zmul zp zq)))
        (zmul zp (zmul np (zadd (zmul nq zr) (zmul nr zq)))) is
  fn (np : Z) (nq : Z) (nr : Z) (zp : Z) (zq : Z) (zr : Z) is
    trans
      (cong2Z (fn (u : Z) (v : Z) is zadd u v end)
        -- (np·nq)·(zp·zr) = zp·(np·(nq·zr))
        (trans (zmulInterchange np nq zp zr)
          (trans (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul s (zmul nq zr) end) (zmulComm np zp))
            (zmulAssoc zp np (zmul nq zr))))
        -- (np·nr)·(zp·zq) = zp·(np·(nr·zq))
        (trans (zmulInterchange np nr zp zq)
          (trans (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul s (zmul nr zq) end) (zmulComm np zp))
            (zmulAssoc zp np (zmul nr zq)))))
      -- fold:  zp·(np·(nq·zr)) + zp·(np·(nr·zq)) = zp·(np·(nq·zr + nr·zq))
      (sym
        (trans (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul zp s end)
                 (zmulDistR np (zmul nq zr) (zmul nr zq)))
          (zmulDistR zp (zmul np (zmul nq zr)) (zmul np (zmul nr zq)))))
  end
end

-- the pure-ℤ cross identity (everything in product-denominator form).
qmulDistCross : (np : Z) -> (nq : Z) -> (nr : Z) -> (zp : Z) -> (zq : Z) -> (zr : Z)
   -> Eq Z
        (zmul (zmul np (zadd (zmul nq zr) (zmul nr zq)))
              (zmul (zmul zp zq) (zmul zp zr)))
        (zmul (zadd (zmul (zmul np nq) (zmul zp zr)) (zmul (zmul np nr) (zmul zp zq)))
              (zmul zp (zmul zq zr))) is
  fn (np : Z) (nq : Z) (nr : Z) (zp : Z) (zq : Z) (zr : Z) is
    trans
      -- denR = zp·denL
      (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul (zmul np (zadd (zmul nq zr) (zmul nr zq))) s end)
        (qmulDistDen zp zq zr))
      (trans
        -- numL·(zp·denL) = (numL·zp)·denL
        (sym (zmulAssoc (zmul np (zadd (zmul nq zr) (zmul nr zq))) zp (zmul zp (zmul zq zr))))
        (trans
          -- (numL·zp)·denL = (zp·numL)·denL
          (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul s (zmul zp (zmul zq zr)) end)
            (zmulComm (zmul np (zadd (zmul nq zr) (zmul nr zq))) zp))
          -- (zp·numL)·denL = numR·denL    (numR = zp·numL, reversed)
          (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul s (zmul zp (zmul zq zr)) end)
            (sym (qmulDistNum np nq nr zp zq zr)))))
  end
end

-- The full QRel obligation for distributivity, threading qaddDenZ/qmulDenZ on the four
-- denominator occurrences and dispatching the pure-ℤ identity by qmulDistCross.
qmulDistRP : (p : QPair) -> (q : QPair) -> (r : QPair)
   -> QRel (qmulP p (qaddP q r)) (qaddP (qmulP p q) (qmulP p r)) is
  fn (p : QPair) (q : QPair) (r : QPair) is
    trans
      -- rewrite the LHS denominator  zden (qaddP (qmulP p q) (qmulP p r))
      --   -> zmul (zmul (zden p) (zden q)) (zmul (zden p) (zden r))
      (cong (fn (s : Z) is
               zmul (zmul (qnum p) (zadd (zmul (qnum q) (zden r)) (zmul (qnum r) (zden q)))) s end)
        (trans (qaddDenZ (qmulP p q) (qmulP p r))
          (cong2Z (fn (u : Z) (v : Z) is zmul u v end) (qmulDenZ p q) (qmulDenZ p r))))
      (trans
        -- the pure ℤ cross identity
        (qmulDistCross (qnum p) (qnum q) (qnum r) (zden p) (zden q) (zden r))
        (trans
          -- fold the numerator denominators back:  zmul (zden p) (zden r) -> zden (qmulP p r)
          --   and zmul (zden p) (zden q) -> zden (qmulP p q)
          (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul s (zmul (zden p) (zmul (zden q) (zden r))) end)
            (cong2Z (fn (u : Z) (v : Z) is zadd u v end)
              (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul (zmul (qnum p) (qnum q)) s end) (sym (qmulDenZ p r)))
              (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul (zmul (qnum p) (qnum r)) s end) (sym (qmulDenZ p q)))))
          -- fold the RHS (LHS-rep) denominator back to  zden (qmulP p (qaddP q r))
          (cong (fn (s : Z) is
                   zmul (zadd (zmul (zmul (qnum p) (qnum q)) (zden (qmulP p r)))
                              (zmul (zmul (qnum p) (qnum r)) (zden (qmulP p q)))) s end)
            (sym (trans (qmulDenZ p (qaddP q r))
              (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul (zden p) s end) (qaddDenZ q r)))))))
  end
end

qmulDistR : (x : Q) -> (y : Q) -> (z : Q)
   -> Eq Q (qmul x (qadd y z)) (qadd (qmul x y) (qmul x z)) is
  fn (x : Q) is
    qind QPair QRel
      (fn (wx : Q) is (y : Q) -> (z : Q) -> Eq Q (qmul wx (qadd y z)) (qadd (qmul wx y) (qmul wx z)) end)
      (fn (p : QPair) is
        fn (y : Q) is
          qind QPair QRel
            (fn (wy : Q) is (z : Q) -> Eq Q (qmul (qin QPair QRel p) (qadd wy z)) (qadd (qmul (qin QPair QRel p) wy) (qmul (qin QPair QRel p) z)) end)
            (fn (q : QPair) is
              fn (z : Q) is
                qind QPair QRel
                  (fn (wz : Q) is Eq Q (qmul (qin QPair QRel p) (qadd (qin QPair QRel q) wz)) (qadd (qmul (qin QPair QRel p) (qin QPair QRel q)) (qmul (qin QPair QRel p) wz)) end)
                  (fn (r : QPair) is
                    qsound QPair QRel
                      (qmulP p (qaddP q r)) (qaddP (qmulP p q) (qmulP p r))
                      (qmulDistRP p q r)
                  end)
                  z
              end
            end)
            y
        end
      end)
      x
  end
end

-- ============================================================================
-- CHAPTER 119 — ℚ AS AN ORDERED FIELD.
-- Everything above is the ch117 ℚ-field development (over the ch107 ℤ ring),
-- redeclared verbatim. Below is the NEW order layer.
-- ============================================================================

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- The Boolean order toolkit (ch65/ch80/ch82/ch83), redeclared verbatim.
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

data Bool : U is
  true  : Bool
| false : Bool
end

-- lte a b = (a <= b): zero is below everything; succ k <= zero is false; succ k <=
-- succ m recurses to k <= m. Recurses on its FIRST argument.
lte : Nat -> Nat -> Bool is
  fn (a : Nat) is
    NatElim (fn (x : Nat) is Nat -> Bool end)
      (fn (n : Nat) is true end)
      (fn (k : Nat) (ih : Nat -> Bool) is
         fn (n : Nat) is
           NatElim (fn (y : Nat) is Bool end)
             false
             (fn (m : Nat) (ih2 : Bool) is ih m end)
             n
         end
       end)
      a
  end
end

-- or a b = Boolean disjunction by BoolElim on the first argument (ch83).
or : Bool -> Bool -> Bool is
  fn (a : Bool) (b : Bool) is
    BoolElim (fn (x : Bool) is Bool end) true b a
  end
end

-- REFLEXIVITY of lte (ch65).
lteRefl : (n : Nat) -> Eq Bool (lte n n) true is
  fn (n : Nat) is
    NatElim (fn (x : Nat) is Eq Bool (lte x x) true end)
      (refl true)
      (fn (k : Nat) (ih : Eq Bool (lte k k) true) is ih end)
      n
  end
end

-- ABSURDITY from `false = true`: any lte equation (ch80 idiom).
lteAbsurd : (a : Nat) -> (c : Nat) -> Eq Bool false true -> Eq Bool (lte a c) true is
  fn (a : Nat) (c : Nat) (h : Eq Bool false true) is
    subst Bool false true h
      (fn (z : Bool) is
         case z of
         | true  -> Eq Bool (lte a c) true
         | false -> Eq Bool true true
         end
       end)
      (refl true)
  end
end

-- ABSURDITY from `false = true`: any Nat equation (ch82 idiom).
lteAbsurdNat : (a : Nat) -> (b : Nat) -> Eq Bool false true -> Eq Nat a b is
  fn (a : Nat) (b : Nat) (h : Eq Bool false true) is
    subst Bool false true h
      (fn (z : Bool) is
         case z of
         | true  -> Eq Nat a b
         | false -> Eq Nat a a
         end
       end)
      (refl a)
  end
end

-- TRANSITIVITY of lte (ch80, verbatim).
lteTrans : (a : Nat) -> (b : Nat) -> (c : Nat)
   -> Eq Bool (lte a b) true -> Eq Bool (lte b c) true -> Eq Bool (lte a c) true is
  fn (a : Nat) is
    NatElim
      (fn (x : Nat) is
         (b : Nat) -> (c : Nat)
           -> Eq Bool (lte x b) true -> Eq Bool (lte b c) true
           -> Eq Bool (lte x c) true end)
      (fn (b : Nat) (c : Nat)
          (hab : Eq Bool (lte zero b) true) (hbc : Eq Bool (lte b c) true) is
         refl true end)
      (fn (a' : Nat)
          (ih : (b : Nat) -> (c : Nat)
                  -> Eq Bool (lte a' b) true -> Eq Bool (lte b c) true
                  -> Eq Bool (lte a' c) true) is
         fn (b : Nat) is
           NatElim
             (fn (y : Nat) is
                (c : Nat)
                  -> Eq Bool (lte (succ a') y) true -> Eq Bool (lte y c) true
                  -> Eq Bool (lte (succ a') c) true end)
             (fn (c : Nat)
                 (hab : Eq Bool false true) (hbc : Eq Bool (lte zero c) true) is
                lteAbsurd (succ a') c hab end)
             (fn (b' : Nat)
                 (ihb : (c : Nat)
                          -> Eq Bool (lte (succ a') b') true
                          -> Eq Bool (lte b' c) true
                          -> Eq Bool (lte (succ a') c) true) is
                fn (c : Nat) is
                  NatElim
                    (fn (z : Nat) is
                       Eq Bool (lte (succ a') (succ b')) true
                         -> Eq Bool (lte (succ b') z) true
                         -> Eq Bool (lte (succ a') z) true end)
                    (fn (hab : Eq Bool (lte a' b') true)
                        (hbc : Eq Bool false true) is
                       lteAbsurd (succ a') zero hbc end)
                    (fn (c' : Nat)
                        (ihc : Eq Bool (lte (succ a') (succ b')) true
                                 -> Eq Bool (lte (succ b') c') true
                                 -> Eq Bool (lte (succ a') c') true) is
                       fn (hab : Eq Bool (lte a' b') true)
                          (hbc : Eq Bool (lte b' c') true) is
                         ih b' c' hab hbc end
                     end)
                    c
                end
              end)
             b
         end
       end)
      a
  end
end

-- ANTISYMMETRY of lte (ch82, verbatim).
lteAntisym : (a : Nat) -> (b : Nat)
   -> Eq Bool (lte a b) true -> Eq Bool (lte b a) true -> Eq Nat a b is
  fn (a : Nat) is
    NatElim
      (fn (x : Nat) is
         (b : Nat)
           -> Eq Bool (lte x b) true -> Eq Bool (lte b x) true
           -> Eq Nat x b end)
      (fn (b : Nat) is
         NatElim
           (fn (y : Nat) is
              Eq Bool (lte zero y) true -> Eq Bool (lte y zero) true
                -> Eq Nat zero y end)
           (fn (hab : Eq Bool (lte zero zero) true)
               (hba : Eq Bool (lte zero zero) true) is
              refl zero end)
           (fn (b' : Nat)
               (ihb : Eq Bool (lte zero b') true -> Eq Bool (lte b' zero) true
                        -> Eq Nat zero b') is
              fn (hab : Eq Bool (lte zero (succ b')) true)
                 (hba : Eq Bool false true) is
                lteAbsurdNat zero (succ b') hba end
            end)
           b
       end)
      (fn (a' : Nat)
          (ih : (b : Nat)
                  -> Eq Bool (lte a' b) true -> Eq Bool (lte b a') true
                  -> Eq Nat a' b) is
         fn (b : Nat) is
           NatElim
             (fn (y : Nat) is
                Eq Bool (lte (succ a') y) true -> Eq Bool (lte y (succ a')) true
                  -> Eq Nat (succ a') y end)
             (fn (hab : Eq Bool false true)
                 (hba : Eq Bool (lte zero (succ a')) true) is
                lteAbsurdNat (succ a') zero hab end)
             (fn (b' : Nat)
                 (ihb : Eq Bool (lte (succ a') b') true
                          -> Eq Bool (lte b' (succ a')) true
                          -> Eq Nat (succ a') b') is
                fn (hab : Eq Bool (lte a' b') true)
                   (hba : Eq Bool (lte b' a') true) is
                  subst Nat a' b' (ih b' hab hba)
                    (fn (z : Nat) is Eq Nat (succ a') (succ z) end)
                    (refl (succ a'))
                end
              end)
             b
         end
       end)
      a
  end
end

-- TOTALITY of lte (ch83, verbatim).
lteTotal : (a : Nat) -> (b : Nat)
   -> Eq Bool (or (lte a b) (lte b a)) true is
  fn (a : Nat) is
    NatElim
      (fn (x : Nat) is
         (b : Nat) -> Eq Bool (or (lte x b) (lte b x)) true end)
      (fn (b : Nat) is refl true end)
      (fn (a' : Nat)
          (ih : (b : Nat) -> Eq Bool (or (lte a' b) (lte b a')) true) is
         fn (b : Nat) is
           NatElim
             (fn (y : Nat) is
                Eq Bool (or (lte (succ a') y) (lte y (succ a'))) true end)
             (refl true)
             (fn (b' : Nat)
                 (ihb : Eq Bool (or (lte (succ a') b') (lte b' (succ a'))) true) is
                ih b'
              end)
             b
         end
       end)
      a
  end
end

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- NEW Nat-order lemmas: the cancellation + monotonicity algebra that powers the
-- well-definedness of zle / qle.  All by induction; no admits.
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

-- LEFT CANCELLATION (as a Bool equality):  lte (k + x) (k + y) = lte x y.
-- By induction on k: add zero x = x definitionally (base, refl); add (succ k) x =
-- succ (add k x), and lte (succ _) (succ _) reduces to lte _ _, so the succ step IS
-- the IH on the nose.
lteAddCancelL : (k : Nat) -> (x : Nat) -> (y : Nat)
   -> Eq Bool (lte (add k x) (add k y)) (lte x y) is
  fn (k : Nat) (x : Nat) (y : Nat) is
    NatElim (fn (z : Nat) is Eq Bool (lte (add z x) (add z y)) (lte x y) end)
      (refl (lte x y))
      (fn (j : Nat) (ih : Eq Bool (lte (add j x) (add j y)) (lte x y)) is ih end)
      k
  end
end

-- RIGHT CANCELLATION:  lte (x + k) (y + k) = lte x y.  Convert each side to the
-- left-cancellation form with addComm, then apply lteAddCancelL.
lteAddCancelR : (k : Nat) -> (x : Nat) -> (y : Nat)
   -> Eq Bool (lte (add x k) (add y k)) (lte x y) is
  fn (k : Nat) (x : Nat) (y : Nat) is
    trans
      (cong2 (fn (u : Nat) (v : Nat) is lte u v end)
        (addComm x k) (addComm y k))
      (lteAddCancelL k x y)
  end
end

-- ADD A CONSTANT TO BOTH SIDES (forward, true-direction): from lte x y = true derive
-- lte (x + k) (y + k) = true.  (The reverse of lteAddCancelR.)
lteAddBothR : (k : Nat) -> (x : Nat) -> (y : Nat)
   -> Eq Bool (lte x y) true -> Eq Bool (lte (add x k) (add y k)) true is
  fn (k : Nat) (x : Nat) (y : Nat) (h : Eq Bool (lte x y) true) is
    trans (lteAddCancelR k x y) h
  end
end

-- MONOTONICITY OF ADDITION over the order:  lte x y = true and lte u v = true imply
-- lte (x + u) (y + v) = true.  Bridge through lte (y + u): the first step adds u on the
-- right to x <= y (lteAddBothR), the second adds y on the left to u <= v
-- (via lteAddCancelL reversed), then lteTrans.
lteAddMono : (x : Nat) -> (y : Nat) -> (u : Nat) -> (v : Nat)
   -> Eq Bool (lte x y) true -> Eq Bool (lte u v) true
   -> Eq Bool (lte (add x u) (add y v)) true is
  fn (x : Nat) (y : Nat) (u : Nat) (v : Nat)
     (hxy : Eq Bool (lte x y) true) (huv : Eq Bool (lte u v) true) is
    lteTrans (add x u) (add y u) (add y v)
      -- x + u <= y + u  (right-add u to x <= y)
      (lteAddBothR u x y hxy)
      -- y + u <= y + v  (left-add y to u <= v): lte (y+u)(y+v) = lte u v = true
      (trans (lteAddCancelL y u v) huv)
  end
end

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- THE ℤ ORDER.  On representatives (a,b) (denoting a−b) and (c,d) (denoting c−d):
--   (a,b) ≤ (c,d)   iff   a + d ≤ c + b      (in Nat, via lte).
-- This is the standard difference order; it respects ZRel by Nat add-cancellation.
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
zleP : NatPair -> NatPair -> Bool is
  fn (p : NatPair) (q : NatPair) is
    lte (add (fst p) (snd q)) (add (fst q) (snd p))
  end
end

-- A 3-term reorder:  (x + y) + z = (x + z) + y.   (addAssoc to the right, addComm the
-- inner pair, addAssoc back.)  The shuffling workhorse for the zle respect proofs.
add3swap : (x : Nat) -> (y : Nat) -> (z : Nat)
   -> Eq Nat (add (add x y) z) (add (add x z) y) is
  fn (x : Nat) (y : Nat) (z : Nat) is
    trans (addAssoc x y z)
      (trans (cong (fn (s : Nat) is add x s end) (addComm y z))
        (sym (addAssoc x z y)))
  end
end

-- RIGHT RESPECT: ZRel q q' (i.e. fst q + snd q' = fst q' + snd q) implies
--   zleP p q = zleP p q'.   Both sides are made equal by adding the *other's*
-- second-component on both sides (sym lteAddCancelR), then a pure Nat reorder lands
-- them on the common canonical form, the ZRel hypothesis crossing in the right slot.
zleRespR : (p : NatPair) -> (q : NatPair) -> (q' : NatPair) ->
    ZRel q q' -> Eq Bool (zleP p q) (zleP p q') is
  fn (p : NatPair) (q : NatPair) (q' : NatPair) (h : ZRel q q') is
    -- LHS = lte (a + dq) (cq + b);  RHS = lte (a + dq') (cq' + b),
    -- where a=fst p, b=snd p, cq=fst q, dq=snd q, cq'=fst q', dq'=snd q'.
    -- hyp h : add cq dq' = add cq' dq.
    trans
      -- LHS = lte ((a+dq)+dq') ((cq+b)+dq')      [add dq' both sides]
      (sym (lteAddCancelR (snd q') (add (fst p) (snd q)) (add (fst q) (snd p))))
      (trans
        -- rewrite both args to the common canonical form
        (cong2 (fn (u : Nat) (v : Nat) is lte u v end)
          -- (a+dq)+dq' = (a+dq')+dq
          (add3swap (fst p) (snd q) (snd q'))
          -- (cq+b)+dq' = (cq'+b)+dq :
          --   (cq+b)+dq' = (cq+dq')+b   [add3swap]
          --             = (cq'+dq)+b    [h]
          --             = (cq'+b)+dq    [add3swap back]
          (trans (add3swap (fst q) (snd p) (snd q'))
            (trans (cong (fn (s : Nat) is add s (snd p) end) h)
              (add3swap (fst q') (snd q) (snd p)))))
        -- RHS = lte ((a+dq')+dq) ((cq'+b)+dq)     [cancel dq]
        (lteAddCancelR (snd q) (add (fst p) (snd q')) (add (fst q') (snd p))))
  end
end

-- LEFT RESPECT: ZRel p p' implies zleP p q = zleP p' q.  Symmetric shuffle; the
-- hypothesis crosses in the FIRST slot this time.
zleRespL : (p : NatPair) -> (p' : NatPair) -> (q : NatPair) ->
    ZRel p p' -> Eq Bool (zleP p q) (zleP p' q) is
  fn (p : NatPair) (p' : NatPair) (q : NatPair) (h : ZRel p p') is
    -- LHS = lte (ap + dq) (cq + bp);  RHS = lte (ap' + dq) (cq + bp'),
    -- ap=fst p, bp=snd p, ap'=fst p', bp'=snd p', cq=fst q, dq=snd q.
    -- hyp h : add ap bp' = add ap' bp.
    trans
      -- add bp' both sides
      (sym (lteAddCancelR (snd p') (add (fst p) (snd q)) (add (fst q) (snd p))))
      (trans
        (cong2 (fn (u : Nat) (v : Nat) is lte u v end)
          -- (ap+dq)+bp' = (ap'+dq)+bp :
          --   (ap+dq)+bp' = (ap+bp')+dq  [add3swap]
          --              = (ap'+bp)+dq   [h]
          --              = (ap'+dq)+bp   [add3swap back]
          (trans (add3swap (fst p) (snd q) (snd p'))
            (trans (cong (fn (s : Nat) is add s (snd q) end) h)
              (add3swap (fst p') (snd p) (snd q))))
          -- (cq+bp)+bp' = (cq+bp')+bp
          (add3swap (fst q) (snd p) (snd p')))
        (lteAddCancelR (snd p) (add (fst p') (snd q)) (add (fst q) (snd p'))))
  end
end

-- Lift zleP through ZRel, twice (the double-qind pattern).
zleR : NatPair -> Z -> Bool is
  fn (p : NatPair) is
    qlift NatPair ZRel Bool
      (fn (q : NatPair) is zleP p q end)
      (fn (q : NatPair) (q' : NatPair) (r : ZRel q q') is
        zleRespR p q q' r
      end)
  end
end

zle : Z -> Z -> Bool is
  qlift NatPair ZRel (Z -> Bool) zleR
    (fn (p : NatPair) (p' : NatPair) (r : ZRel p p') is
      fn (z : Z) is
        qind NatPair ZRel (fn (w : Z) is Eq Bool (zleR p w) (zleR p' w) end)
          (fn (q : NatPair) is zleRespL p p' q r end)
          z
      end
    end)
end

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- THE ℤ ORDER AXIOMS, lifted from Nat lte through qind.
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

-- REFLEXIVITY: zle x x = true.  On a rep p, zleP p p = lte (a+b)(a+b) = true (lteRefl).
zleRefl : (x : Z) -> Eq Bool (zle x x) true is
  fn (x : Z) is
    qind NatPair ZRel (fn (w : Z) is Eq Bool (zle w w) true end)
      (fn (p : NatPair) is lteRefl (add (fst p) (snd p)) end)
      x
  end
end

-- TRANSITIVITY: zle x y = true and zle y z = true imply zle x z = true.
-- On reps p=(a,b), q=(c,d), r=(e,f):
--   H1 : lte (a+d)(c+b) = true      (a−b ≤ c−d)
--   H2 : lte (c+f)(e+d) = true      (c−d ≤ e−f)
-- Add them (lteAddMono): lte ((a+d)+(c+f)) ((c+b)+(e+d)) = true.  Reassociate both
-- sides to expose the common summand (c+d):  LHS = (a+f)+(c+d), RHS = (e+b)+(c+d),
-- then cancel it (lteAddCancelR) to get lte (a+f)(e+b) = zleP p r.
zleTransP : (p : NatPair) -> (q : NatPair) -> (r : NatPair)
   -> Eq Bool (zleP p q) true -> Eq Bool (zleP q r) true
   -> Eq Bool (zleP p r) true is
  fn (p : NatPair) (q : NatPair) (r : NatPair)
     (h1 : Eq Bool (zleP p q) true) (h2 : Eq Bool (zleP q r) true) is
    -- target: lte (add (fst p) (snd r)) (add (fst r) (snd p)) = true.
    -- Let a=fst p, b=snd p, c=fst q, d=snd q, e=fst r, f=snd r.
    -- We cancel (c+d) from the summed inequality H1 + H2 (lteAddMono):
    --   lte ((a+d)+(c+f)) ((c+b)+(e+d)) = true.
    trans
      -- lte (a+f) (e+b) = lte ((a+f)+(c+d)) ((e+b)+(c+d))   [sym lteAddCancelR]
      (sym (lteAddCancelR (add (fst q) (snd q))
              (add (fst p) (snd r)) (add (fst r) (snd p))))
      (trans
        -- rewrite both args:  (a+f)+(c+d) -> (a+d)+(c+f)  and  (e+b)+(c+d) -> (c+b)+(e+d)
        (cong2 (fn (u : Nat) (v : Nat) is lte u v end)
          -- (a+f)+(c+d) = (a+c)+(f+d) = (a+c)+(d+f) = (a+d)+(c+f)
          (trans (interchange (fst p) (snd r) (fst q) (snd q))
            (trans (cong (fn (s : Nat) is add (add (fst p) (fst q)) s end)
                     (addComm (snd r) (snd q)))
              (sym (interchange (fst p) (snd q) (fst q) (snd r)))))
          -- (e+b)+(c+d) = (e+c)+(b+d) = (c+e)+(b+d) ; (c+b)+(e+d) = (c+e)+(b+d)
          (trans (interchange (fst r) (snd p) (fst q) (snd q))
            (trans (cong (fn (s : Nat) is add s (add (snd p) (snd q)) end)
                     (addComm (fst r) (fst q)))
              (sym (interchange (fst q) (snd p) (fst r) (snd q))))))
        -- the summed inequality, by lteAddMono on H1 and H2
        (lteAddMono (add (fst p) (snd q)) (add (fst q) (snd p))
                    (add (fst q) (snd r)) (add (fst r) (snd q))
                    h1 h2))
  end
end

-- TRANSITIVITY at ℤ: zle x y = true and zle y z = true imply zle x z = true.
-- Triple qind to representatives, then zleTransP.
zleTrans : (x : Z) -> (y : Z) -> (z : Z)
   -> Eq Bool (zle x y) true -> Eq Bool (zle y z) true -> Eq Bool (zle x z) true is
  fn (x : Z) is
    qind NatPair ZRel
      (fn (wx : Z) is (y : Z) -> (z : Z)
         -> Eq Bool (zle wx y) true -> Eq Bool (zle y z) true -> Eq Bool (zle wx z) true end)
      (fn (p : NatPair) is
        fn (y : Z) is
          qind NatPair ZRel
            (fn (wy : Z) is (z : Z)
               -> Eq Bool (zle (qin NatPair ZRel p) wy) true -> Eq Bool (zle wy z) true
               -> Eq Bool (zle (qin NatPair ZRel p) z) true end)
            (fn (q : NatPair) is
              fn (z : Z) is
                qind NatPair ZRel
                  (fn (wz : Z) is
                     Eq Bool (zle (qin NatPair ZRel p) (qin NatPair ZRel q)) true
                       -> Eq Bool (zle (qin NatPair ZRel q) wz) true
                       -> Eq Bool (zle (qin NatPair ZRel p) wz) true end)
                  (fn (r : NatPair) is
                    fn (h1 : Eq Bool (zleP p q) true) (h2 : Eq Bool (zleP q r) true) is
                      zleTransP p q r h1 h2
                    end
                  end)
                  z
              end
            end)
            y
        end
      end)
      x
  end
end

-- ANTISYMMETRY at ℤ: zle x y = true and zle y x = true imply Eq Z x y.
-- On reps p,q: zleP p q = lte (a+d)(c+b), zleP q p = lte (c+b)(a+d); lteAntisym gives
-- Eq Nat (a+d)(c+b) = ZRel p q exactly, so qsound delivers Eq Z.
zleAntisym : (x : Z) -> (y : Z)
   -> Eq Bool (zle x y) true -> Eq Bool (zle y x) true -> Eq Z x y is
  fn (x : Z) is
    qind NatPair ZRel
      (fn (wx : Z) is (y : Z)
         -> Eq Bool (zle wx y) true -> Eq Bool (zle y wx) true -> Eq Z wx y end)
      (fn (p : NatPair) is
        fn (y : Z) is
          qind NatPair ZRel
            (fn (wy : Z) is
               Eq Bool (zle (qin NatPair ZRel p) wy) true
                 -> Eq Bool (zle wy (qin NatPair ZRel p)) true
                 -> Eq Z (qin NatPair ZRel p) wy end)
            (fn (q : NatPair) is
              fn (h1 : Eq Bool (zleP p q) true) (h2 : Eq Bool (zleP q p) true) is
                qsound NatPair ZRel p q
                  (lteAntisym (add (fst p) (snd q)) (add (fst q) (snd p)) h1 h2)
              end
            end)
            y
        end
      end)
      x
  end
end

-- TOTALITY at ℤ: every pair is comparable.
zleTotal : (x : Z) -> (y : Z) -> Eq Bool (or (zle x y) (zle y x)) true is
  fn (x : Z) is
    qind NatPair ZRel
      (fn (wx : Z) is (y : Z) -> Eq Bool (or (zle wx y) (zle y wx)) true end)
      (fn (p : NatPair) is
        fn (y : Z) is
          qind NatPair ZRel
            (fn (wy : Z) is Eq Bool (or (zle (qin NatPair ZRel p) wy) (zle wy (qin NatPair ZRel p))) true end)
            (fn (q : NatPair) is
              lteTotal (add (fst p) (snd q)) (add (fst q) (snd p))
            end)
            y
        end
      end)
      x
  end
end

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- POSITIVE-MULTIPLIER ORDER INVARIANCE (the qle well-definedness fuel).
--   lte (x · succ n) (y · succ n)  =  lte x y.
-- Multiplying both sides of a comparison by a POSITIVE Nat (succ n) neither changes
-- nor reflects-falsely the order. By double induction on x then y (n fixed):
--   x=0          : lte 0 _ = true on both sides (mul 0 k = 0 def.).
--   x=succ, y=0  : mul (succ x') k = succ(...) so lte (succ _) 0 = false on both.
--   x=succ,y=succ: mul (succ _) k = add k (mul _ k) def., so the common k cancels
--                  (lteAddCancelL) leaving lte (x'·k)(y'·k) = lte x' y' by the IH.
lteMulPos : (n : Nat) -> (x : Nat) -> (y : Nat)
   -> Eq Bool (lte (mul x (succ n)) (mul y (succ n))) (lte x y) is
  fn (n : Nat) (x : Nat) is
    NatElim
      (fn (w : Nat) is
         (y : Nat) -> Eq Bool (lte (mul w (succ n)) (mul y (succ n))) (lte w y) end)
      -- x = 0: lte 0 (mul y k) = true = lte 0 y.
      (fn (y : Nat) is refl true end)
      -- x = succ x', IH at x'.
      (fn (x' : Nat)
          (ih : (y : Nat) -> Eq Bool (lte (mul x' (succ n)) (mul y (succ n))) (lte x' y)) is
         fn (y : Nat) is
           NatElim
             (fn (w : Nat) is
                Eq Bool (lte (mul (succ x') (succ n)) (mul w (succ n))) (lte (succ x') w) end)
             -- y = 0: mul (succ x') (succ n) = succ(...), lte (succ _) 0 = false = lte (succ x') 0.
             (refl false)
             -- y = succ y': common (succ n) cancels via lteAddCancelL, then IH.
             (fn (y' : Nat)
                 (ihy : Eq Bool (lte (mul (succ x') (succ n)) (mul y' (succ n))) (lte (succ x') y')) is
                -- mul (succ x')(succ n) = add (succ n) (mul x' (succ n)) def.,
                -- mul (succ y')(succ n) = add (succ n) (mul y' (succ n)) def.,
                -- so the goal is lte (add (succ n)(x'·k)) (add (succ n)(y'·k)) = lte (succ x')(succ y'),
                -- and lte (succ x')(succ y') = lte x' y' def.
                trans (lteAddCancelL (succ n) (mul x' (succ n)) (mul y' (succ n)))
                  (ih y')
              end)
             y
         end
       end)
      x
  end
end

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- ℤ ORDER INVARIANCE UNDER A POSITIVE MULTIPLIER, at the REPRESENTATIVE level.
-- Multiplying both ℤ-sides (as reps) by a positive embedded nat (succ m, 0) leaves
-- zleP unchanged.  pmul p (sm,0) has rep (a·sm + b·0, a·0 + b·sm); after mulZeroR the
-- cross sum (a·sm + d·sm) factors (mulDistR) to (a+d)·sm, and lteMulPos cancels sm.
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

-- the simplification fst(pmul p k) + snd(pmul q k) = (fst p + snd q) · succ m,
-- where k = (succ m, 0).
zleMulArg : (p : NatPair) -> (q : NatPair) -> (m : Nat)
   -> Eq Nat
        (add (fst (pmul p (npair (succ m) zero))) (snd (pmul q (npair (succ m) zero))))
        (mul (add (fst p) (snd q)) (succ m)) is
  fn (p : NatPair) (q : NatPair) (m : Nat) is
    -- LHS = add (add (mul (fst p) (succ m)) (mul (snd p) zero))
    --           (add (mul (fst q) zero) (mul (snd q) (succ m)))
    trans
      -- collapse the two `mul _ zero` summands to zero
      (cong2 (fn (u : Nat) (v : Nat) is add u v end)
        (trans (cong (fn (s : Nat) is add (mul (fst p) (succ m)) s end) (mulZeroR (snd p)))
          (addZeroR (mul (fst p) (succ m))))
        -- add (mul (fst q) zero) (mul (snd q) (succ m)) = mul (snd q) (succ m)
        --   (mul (fst q) zero = zero def. via mulZeroR; add zero x = x def.)
        (cong (fn (s : Nat) is add s (mul (snd q) (succ m)) end) (mulZeroR (fst q))))
      -- add (mul (fst p) (succ m)) (mul (snd q) (succ m)) = mul (add (fst p)(snd q))(succ m)
      (sym (mulDistR (fst p) (snd q) (succ m)))
  end
end

zlePMulR : (p : NatPair) -> (q : NatPair) -> (m : Nat)
   -> Eq Bool
        (zleP (pmul p (npair (succ m) zero)) (pmul q (npair (succ m) zero)))
        (zleP p q) is
  fn (p : NatPair) (q : NatPair) (m : Nat) is
    -- zleP (pmul p k)(pmul q k) = lte (fst(pmul p k)+snd(pmul q k)) (fst(pmul q k)+snd(pmul p k))
    trans
      (cong2 (fn (u : Nat) (v : Nat) is lte u v end)
        (zleMulArg p q m)
        (zleMulArg q p m))
      -- lte ((a+d)·sm) ((c+b)·sm) = lte (a+d)(c+b) = zleP p q
      (lteMulPos m (add (fst p) (snd q)) (add (fst q) (snd p)))
  end
end

-- LIFT to ℤ: multiplying both ℤ-sides by zfrom (succ m) (a positive integer) leaves
-- zle unchanged.  Double qind to reps; zmul (qin p)(qin (succ m,0)) ~> qin (pmul p _)
-- and zle (qin _)(qin _) ~> zleP _ _, so the obligation is exactly zlePMulR.
zleMulPosZ : (x : Z) -> (y : Z) -> (m : Nat)
   -> Eq Bool (zle (zmul x (zfrom (succ m))) (zmul y (zfrom (succ m)))) (zle x y) is
  fn (x : Z) is
    qind NatPair ZRel
      (fn (wx : Z) is (y : Z) -> (m : Nat)
         -> Eq Bool (zle (zmul wx (zfrom (succ m))) (zmul y (zfrom (succ m)))) (zle wx y) end)
      (fn (p : NatPair) is
        fn (y : Z) is
          qind NatPair ZRel
            (fn (wy : Z) is (m : Nat)
               -> Eq Bool (zle (zmul (qin NatPair ZRel p) (zfrom (succ m))) (zmul wy (zfrom (succ m))))
                          (zle (qin NatPair ZRel p) wy) end)
            (fn (q : NatPair) is
              fn (m : Nat) is zlePMulR p q m end
            end)
            y
        end
      end)
      x
  end
end

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- THE ℚ ORDER.  a/sb ≤ c/sd  iff  a·sd ≤ c·sb  (cross-multiply against the POSITIVE
-- denominators; the +1 trick makes sb, sd positive so the direction is preserved).
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
qleP : QPair -> QPair -> Bool is
  fn (p : QPair) (q : QPair) is
    zle (zmul (qnum p) (zden q)) (zmul (qnum q) (zden p))
  end
end

-- swap the last two ℤ factors:  (x·y)·z = (x·z)·y.
zmul3swap : (x : Z) -> (y : Z) -> (z : Z)
   -> Eq Z (zmul (zmul x y) z) (zmul (zmul x z) y) is
  fn (x : Z) (y : Z) (z : Z) is
    trans (zmulAssoc x y z)
      (trans (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul x s end) (zmulComm y z))
        (sym (zmulAssoc x z y)))
  end
end

-- RIGHT RESPECT — the well-definedness crux.  QRel q q' (qnum q · zden q' = qnum q' ·
-- zden q) implies qleP p q = qleP p q'.  Multiply qleP p q by the positive zden q' and
-- qleP p q' by the positive zden q (zleMulPosZ), reorder the ℤ factors (zmul3swap), and
-- cross the hypothesis in the second slot.
qleRespR : (p : QPair) -> (q : QPair) -> (q' : QPair) ->
    QRel q q' -> Eq Bool (qleP p q) (qleP p q') is
  fn (p : QPair) (q : QPair) (q' : QPair) (h : QRel q q') is
    -- a=qnum p, zb=zden p, cq=qnum q, zdq=zden q, cq'=qnum q', zdq'=zden q'.
    -- h : zmul cq zdq' = zmul cq' zdq.
    trans
      -- qleP p q = zle ((a·zdq)·zdq') ((cq·zb)·zdq')   [mult by zden q', positive]
      (sym (zleMulPosZ (zmul (qnum p) (zden q)) (zmul (qnum q) (zden p)) (qdenN q')))
      (trans
        (cong2 (fn (u : Z) (v : Z) is zle u v end)
          -- (a·zdq)·zdq' = (a·zdq')·zdq
          (zmul3swap (qnum p) (zden q) (zden q'))
          -- (cq·zb)·zdq' = (cq·zdq')·zb = (cq'·zdq)·zb = (cq'·zb)·zdq
          (trans (zmul3swap (qnum q) (zden p) (zden q'))
            (trans (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul s (zden p) end) h)
              (zmul3swap (qnum q') (zden q) (zden p)))))
        -- zle ((a·zdq')·zdq) ((cq'·zb)·zdq) = zle (a·zdq')(cq'·zb) = qleP p q'  [mult by zden q]
        (zleMulPosZ (zmul (qnum p) (zden q')) (zmul (qnum q') (zden p)) (qdenN q)))
  end
end

-- LEFT RESPECT.  QRel p p' (qnum p · zden p' = qnum p' · zden p) implies
--   qleP p q = qleP p' q.  Symmetric: the hypothesis crosses in the FIRST slot.
qleRespL : (p : QPair) -> (p' : QPair) -> (q : QPair) ->
    QRel p p' -> Eq Bool (qleP p q) (qleP p' q) is
  fn (p : QPair) (p' : QPair) (q : QPair) (h : QRel p p') is
    -- ap=qnum p, zbp=zden p, ap'=qnum p', zbp'=zden p', cq=qnum q, zdq=zden q.
    -- qleP p q = zle (ap·zdq) (cq·zbp);  qleP p' q = zle (ap'·zdq) (cq·zbp').
    -- h : zmul ap zbp' = zmul ap' zbp.
    trans
      -- mult by zden p' (positive)
      (sym (zleMulPosZ (zmul (qnum p) (zden q)) (zmul (qnum q) (zden p)) (qdenN p')))
      (trans
        (cong2 (fn (u : Z) (v : Z) is zle u v end)
          -- (ap·zdq)·zbp' = (ap·zbp')·zdq = (ap'·zbp)·zdq = (ap'·zdq)·zbp
          (trans (zmul3swap (qnum p) (zden q) (zden p'))
            (trans (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul s (zden q) end) h)
              (zmul3swap (qnum p') (zden p) (zden q))))
          -- (cq·zbp)·zbp' = (cq·zbp')·zbp
          (zmul3swap (qnum q) (zden p) (zden p')))
        -- mult by zden p (positive)
        (zleMulPosZ (zmul (qnum p') (zden q)) (zmul (qnum q) (zden p')) (qdenN p)))
  end
end

-- Lift qleP through QRel, twice.
qleR : QPair -> Q -> Bool is
  fn (p : QPair) is
    qlift QPair QRel Bool
      (fn (q : QPair) is qleP p q end)
      (fn (q : QPair) (q' : QPair) (r : QRel q q') is
        qleRespR p q q' r
      end)
  end
end

qle : Q -> Q -> Bool is
  qlift QPair QRel (Q -> Bool) qleR
    (fn (p : QPair) (p' : QPair) (r : QRel p p') is
      fn (z : Q) is
        qind QPair QRel (fn (w : Q) is Eq Bool (qleR p w) (qleR p' w) end)
          (fn (q : QPair) is qleRespL p p' q r end)
          z
      end
    end)
end

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- THE ℚ ORDER AXIOMS, lifted through qind.
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

-- REFLEXIVITY: qle x x = true.  On a rep p, qleP p p = zle (a·zb)(a·zb) = true (zleRefl).
qleRefl : (x : Q) -> Eq Bool (qle x x) true is
  fn (x : Q) is
    qind QPair QRel (fn (w : Q) is Eq Bool (qle w w) true end)
      (fn (p : QPair) is zleRefl (zmul (qnum p) (zden p)) end)
      x
  end
end

-- TRANSITIVITY at the representative level.  qleP p q = true and qleP q r = true imply
-- qleP p r = true.  Multiply H1 by the positive zden r and H2 by the positive zden p,
-- chain through zle transitivity at the common middle (cq·zb·zdr = cq·zdr·zb via
-- zmul3swap), reorder to expose the common positive factor zden q, and cancel it
-- (zleMulPosZ).
qleTransP : (p : QPair) -> (q : QPair) -> (r : QPair)
   -> Eq Bool (qleP p q) true -> Eq Bool (qleP q r) true
   -> Eq Bool (qleP p r) true is
  fn (p : QPair) (q : QPair) (r : QPair)
     (h1 : Eq Bool (qleP p q) true) (h2 : Eq Bool (qleP q r) true) is
    -- a=qnum p, zb=zden p, cq=qnum q, zdq=zden q, cr=qnum r, zdr=zden r.
    trans
      -- qleP p r = zle (a·zdr)(cr·zb) = zle ((a·zdr)·zdq) ((cr·zb)·zdq)  [mult zden q]
      (sym (zleMulPosZ (zmul (qnum p) (zden r)) (zmul (qnum r) (zden p)) (qdenN q)))
      (trans
        -- rewrite ((a·zdr)·zdq) -> ((a·zdq)·zdr) and ((cr·zb)·zdq) -> ((cr·zdq)·zb)
        (cong2 (fn (u : Z) (v : Z) is zle u v end)
          (zmul3swap (qnum p) (zden r) (zden q))
          (zmul3swap (qnum r) (zden p) (zden q)))
        -- zle ((a·zdq)·zdr) ((cr·zdq)·zb) = true, by chaining the two scaled hypotheses
        (zleTrans
          (zmul (zmul (qnum p) (zden q)) (zden r))
          (zmul (zmul (qnum q) (zden p)) (zden r))
          (zmul (zmul (qnum r) (zden q)) (zden p))
          -- step 1: scale H1 by zden r
          (trans (zleMulPosZ (zmul (qnum p) (zden q)) (zmul (qnum q) (zden p)) (qdenN r)) h1)
          -- step 2: rewrite the left endpoint then scale H2 by zden p
          (trans
            (cong (fn (s : Z) is zle s (zmul (zmul (qnum r) (zden q)) (zden p)) end)
              (zmul3swap (qnum q) (zden p) (zden r)))
            (trans (zleMulPosZ (zmul (qnum q) (zden r)) (zmul (qnum r) (zden q)) (qdenN p)) h2))))
  end
end

-- TRANSITIVITY at ℚ: lift qleTransP through triple qind.
qleTrans : (x : Q) -> (y : Q) -> (z : Q)
   -> Eq Bool (qle x y) true -> Eq Bool (qle y z) true -> Eq Bool (qle x z) true is
  fn (x : Q) is
    qind QPair QRel
      (fn (wx : Q) is (y : Q) -> (z : Q)
         -> Eq Bool (qle wx y) true -> Eq Bool (qle y z) true -> Eq Bool (qle wx z) true end)
      (fn (p : QPair) is
        fn (y : Q) is
          qind QPair QRel
            (fn (wy : Q) is (z : Q)
               -> Eq Bool (qle (qin QPair QRel p) wy) true -> Eq Bool (qle wy z) true
               -> Eq Bool (qle (qin QPair QRel p) z) true end)
            (fn (q : QPair) is
              fn (z : Q) is
                qind QPair QRel
                  (fn (wz : Q) is
                     Eq Bool (qle (qin QPair QRel p) (qin QPair QRel q)) true
                       -> Eq Bool (qle (qin QPair QRel q) wz) true
                       -> Eq Bool (qle (qin QPair QRel p) wz) true end)
                  (fn (r : QPair) is
                    fn (h1 : Eq Bool (qleP p q) true) (h2 : Eq Bool (qleP q r) true) is
                      qleTransP p q r h1 h2
                    end
                  end)
                  z
              end
            end)
            y
        end
      end)
      x
  end
end

-- TOTALITY at ℚ: every pair is comparable.  On reps, qleP p q = zle (a·zdq)(cq·zb) and
-- qleP q p = zle (cq·zb)(a·zdq), so the disjunction is zleTotal on those two ℤ values.
qleTotal : (x : Q) -> (y : Q) -> Eq Bool (or (qle x y) (qle y x)) true is
  fn (x : Q) is
    qind QPair QRel
      (fn (wx : Q) is (y : Q) -> Eq Bool (or (qle wx y) (qle y wx)) true end)
      (fn (p : QPair) is
        fn (y : Q) is
          qind QPair QRel
            (fn (wy : Q) is Eq Bool (or (qle (qin QPair QRel p) wy) (qle wy (qin QPair QRel p))) true end)
            (fn (q : QPair) is
              zleTotal (zmul (qnum p) (zden q)) (zmul (qnum q) (zden p))
            end)
            y
        end
      end)
      x
  end
end

-- ANTISYMMETRY at ℚ: qle x y = true and qle y x = true imply x = y (in Q).  On reps,
-- the two hypotheses are zle (a·zdq)(cq·zb) = true and zle (cq·zb)(a·zdq) = true, so
-- zleAntisym delivers Eq Z (a·zdq)(cq·zb) — which is exactly QRel p q — and qsound lifts
-- it to Eq Q.
qleAntisym : (x : Q) -> (y : Q)
   -> Eq Bool (qle x y) true -> Eq Bool (qle y x) true -> Eq Q x y is
  fn (x : Q) is
    qind QPair QRel
      (fn (wx : Q) is (y : Q)
         -> Eq Bool (qle wx y) true -> Eq Bool (qle y wx) true -> Eq Q wx y end)
      (fn (p : QPair) is
        fn (y : Q) is
          qind QPair QRel
            (fn (wy : Q) is
               Eq Bool (qle (qin QPair QRel p) wy) true
                 -> Eq Bool (qle wy (qin QPair QRel p)) true
                 -> Eq Q (qin QPair QRel p) wy end)
            (fn (q : QPair) is
              fn (h1 : Eq Bool (qleP p q) true) (h2 : Eq Bool (qleP q p) true) is
                qsound QPair QRel p q
                  (zleAntisym (zmul (qnum p) (zden q)) (zmul (qnum q) (zden p)) h1 h2)
              end
            end)
            y
        end
      end)
      x
  end
end

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- ℤ ORDER / ADDITION COMPATIBILITY (for the ordered-field law qaddMono).
--   zle x y = true  implies  zle (x + w) (y + w) = true   (translation invariance in ℤ).
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

-- rep level: zleP (padd p w)(padd q w) follows from zleP p q by adding the common
-- (g+h) on both Nat sides (lteAddBothR), the two args reassociated by interchange.
zleAddCompatP : (p : NatPair) -> (q : NatPair) -> (w : NatPair)
   -> Eq Bool (zleP p q) true -> Eq Bool (zleP (padd p w) (padd q w)) true is
  fn (p : NatPair) (q : NatPair) (w : NatPair) (h : Eq Bool (zleP p q) true) is
    -- target: lte ((a+g)+(d+h)) ((c+g)+(b+h)) = true, a=fst p,b=snd p,c=fst q,d=snd q,
    -- g=fst w,h=snd w.  Reassociate to lte ((a+d)+(g+h)) ((c+b)+(g+h)) then lteAddBothR.
    trans
      (cong2 (fn (u : Nat) (v : Nat) is lte u v end)
        -- (a+g)+(d+h) = (a+d)+(g+h)
        (interchange (fst p) (fst w) (snd q) (snd w))
        -- (c+g)+(b+h) = (c+b)+(g+h)
        (interchange (fst q) (fst w) (snd p) (snd w)))
      (lteAddBothR (add (fst w) (snd w))
        (add (fst p) (snd q)) (add (fst q) (snd p)) h)
  end
end

-- ℤ level: lift through triple qind.
zleAddCompatR : (x : Z) -> (y : Z) -> (w : Z)
   -> Eq Bool (zle x y) true -> Eq Bool (zle (zadd x w) (zadd y w)) true is
  fn (x : Z) is
    qind NatPair ZRel
      (fn (wx : Z) is (y : Z) -> (w : Z)
         -> Eq Bool (zle wx y) true -> Eq Bool (zle (zadd wx w) (zadd y w)) true end)
      (fn (p : NatPair) is
        fn (y : Z) is
          qind NatPair ZRel
            (fn (wy : Z) is (w : Z)
               -> Eq Bool (zle (qin NatPair ZRel p) wy) true
               -> Eq Bool (zle (zadd (qin NatPair ZRel p) w) (zadd wy w)) true end)
            (fn (q : NatPair) is
              fn (w : Z) is
                qind NatPair ZRel
                  (fn (ww : Z) is
                     Eq Bool (zle (qin NatPair ZRel p) (qin NatPair ZRel q)) true
                       -> Eq Bool (zle (zadd (qin NatPair ZRel p) ww) (zadd (qin NatPair ZRel q) ww)) true end)
                  (fn (r : NatPair) is
                    fn (h : Eq Bool (zleP p q) true) is
                      zleAddCompatP p q r h
                    end
                  end)
                  w
              end
            end)
            y
        end
      end)
      x
  end
end

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- ORDERED-FIELD COMPATIBILITY:  qle x y  implies  qle (x + z) (y + z).
-- Translation invariance of the order under ℚ addition — the additive compatibility
-- law of an ordered field.  On representatives p=(a/zb), q=(c/zd), s=(e/zs):
--   qaddP p s = (a·zs + e·zb) / (zb·zs),  qaddP q s = (c·zs + e·zd) / (zd·zs).
-- Cross-multiplying and distributing (zmulDistL), the e-cross terms coincide
--   (e·zb)·(zd·zs) = (e·zd)·(zb·zs)  [zmulInterchange],
-- while the a/c terms regroup to  (a·zd)·(zs·zs) ≤ (c·zb)·(zs·zs), which is the
-- hypothesis a·zd ≤ c·zb scaled by the POSITIVE square zs·zs (zleMulPosZ).  Adding the
-- common e-term back preserves the order (zleAddCompatR).
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

-- the scaled a/c inequality:  zle ((a·zs)·(zd·zs)) ((c·zs)·(zb·zs)) = true.
-- From hyp zle (a·zd)(c·zb) = true, scale by the positive zs·zs = zfrom(succ M)
-- (M = qmulDen (qdenN s)(qdenN s), so mul (succ ms)(succ ms) = succ M definitionally),
-- then regroup each side by zmulInterchange.
qaddMonoAC : (p : QPair) -> (q : QPair) -> (s : QPair)
   -> Eq Bool (qleP p q) true
   -> Eq Bool
        (zle (zmul (zmul (qnum p) (zden s)) (zmul (zden q) (zden s)))
             (zmul (zmul (qnum q) (zden s)) (zmul (zden p) (zden s)))) true is
  fn (p : QPair) (q : QPair) (s : QPair) (h : Eq Bool (qleP p q) true) is
    -- target args:  (a·zs)·(zd·zs)  and  (c·zs)·(zb·zs).
    -- (a·zs)·(zd·zs) = (a·zd)·(zs·zs)   [zmulInterchange a zs zd zs]
    -- (c·zs)·(zb·zs) = (c·zb)·(zs·zs)   [zmulInterchange c zs zb zs]
    trans
      (cong2 (fn (u : Z) (v : Z) is zle u v end)
        (zmulInterchange (qnum p) (zden s) (zden q) (zden s))
        (zmulInterchange (qnum q) (zden s) (zden p) (zden s)))
      -- zle ((a·zd)·(zs·zs)) ((c·zb)·(zs·zs)) = true.
      -- zmul (zden s) (zden s) = zfrom (mul (succ ms)(succ ms)) [sym zmulHom], and
      -- mul (succ ms)(succ ms) = succ M definitionally, so this is zleMulPosZ at M.
      (trans
        (cong2 (fn (u : Z) (v : Z) is zle u v end)
          (cong (fn (t : Z) is zmul (zmul (qnum p) (zden q)) t end)
            (sym (zmulHom (succ (qdenN s)) (succ (qdenN s)))))
          (cong (fn (t : Z) is zmul (zmul (qnum q) (zden p)) t end)
            (sym (zmulHom (succ (qdenN s)) (succ (qdenN s))))))
        (trans
          (zleMulPosZ (zmul (qnum p) (zden q)) (zmul (qnum q) (zden p))
            (add (qdenN s) (mul (qdenN s) (succ (qdenN s)))))
          h))
  end
end

-- the representative-level monotonicity.
qaddMonoP : (p : QPair) -> (q : QPair) -> (s : QPair)
   -> Eq Bool (qleP p q) true
   -> Eq Bool (qleP (qaddP p s) (qaddP q s)) true is
  fn (p : QPair) (q : QPair) (s : QPair) (h : Eq Bool (qleP p q) true) is
    -- qleP (qaddP p s)(qaddP q s)
    --   = zle (zmul N1 (zden (qaddP q s))) (zmul N2 (zden (qaddP p s)))
    -- N1 = a·zs + e·zb, N2 = c·zs + e·zd.
    trans
      -- (1) rewrite both denominators by qaddDenZ
      (cong2 (fn (u : Z) (v : Z) is zle u v end)
        (cong (fn (t : Z) is zmul (zadd (zmul (qnum p) (zden s)) (zmul (qnum s) (zden p))) t end)
          (qaddDenZ q s))
        (cong (fn (t : Z) is zmul (zadd (zmul (qnum q) (zden s)) (zmul (qnum s) (zden q))) t end)
          (qaddDenZ p s)))
      (trans
        -- (2) distribute each product over the sum (zmulDistL)
        (cong2 (fn (u : Z) (v : Z) is zle u v end)
          (zmulDistL (zmul (qnum p) (zden s)) (zmul (qnum s) (zden p)) (zmul (zden q) (zden s)))
          (zmulDistL (zmul (qnum q) (zden s)) (zmul (qnum s) (zden q)) (zmul (zden p) (zden s))))
        (trans
          -- (3) coincide the e-cross terms: make BOTH equal to (e·zb)·(zd·zs).
          --   RHS e-term (e·zd)·(zb·zs) = (e·zb)·(zd·zs)  [zmulInterchange e zd zb zs]
          (cong (fn (t : Z) is
                   zle (zadd (zmul (zmul (qnum p) (zden s)) (zmul (zden q) (zden s)))
                             (zmul (zmul (qnum s) (zden p)) (zmul (zden q) (zden s))))
                       (zadd (zmul (zmul (qnum q) (zden s)) (zmul (zden p) (zden s))) t) end)
            (zmulInterchange (qnum s) (zden q) (zden p) (zden s)))
          -- (4) now both args are (a/c-term) + common (e·zb)·(zd·zs); add it back via
          -- zleAddCompatR onto the scaled a/c inequality (qaddMonoAC).
          (zleAddCompatR
            (zmul (zmul (qnum p) (zden s)) (zmul (zden q) (zden s)))
            (zmul (zmul (qnum q) (zden s)) (zmul (zden p) (zden s)))
            (zmul (zmul (qnum s) (zden p)) (zmul (zden q) (zden s)))
            (qaddMonoAC p q s h))))
  end
end

-- TRANSLATION INVARIANCE at ℚ: qle x y = true implies qle (qadd x z) (qadd y z) = true.
-- Triple qind to reps; qadd (qin p)(qin s) ~> qin (qaddP p s) and qle (qin _)(qin _) ~>
-- qleP _ _, so the obligation is exactly qaddMonoP.
qaddMono : (x : Q) -> (y : Q) -> (z : Q)
   -> Eq Bool (qle x y) true -> Eq Bool (qle (qadd x z) (qadd y z)) true is
  fn (x : Q) is
    qind QPair QRel
      (fn (wx : Q) is (y : Q) -> (z : Q)
         -> Eq Bool (qle wx y) true -> Eq Bool (qle (qadd wx z) (qadd y z)) true end)
      (fn (p : QPair) is
        fn (y : Q) is
          qind QPair QRel
            (fn (wy : Q) is (z : Q)
               -> Eq Bool (qle (qin QPair QRel p) wy) true
               -> Eq Bool (qle (qadd (qin QPair QRel p) z) (qadd wy z)) true end)
            (fn (q : QPair) is
              fn (z : Q) is
                qind QPair QRel
                  (fn (wz : Q) is
                     Eq Bool (qle (qin QPair QRel p) (qin QPair QRel q)) true
                       -> Eq Bool (qle (qadd (qin QPair QRel p) wz) (qadd (qin QPair QRel q) wz)) true end)
                  (fn (s : QPair) is
                    fn (h : Eq Bool (qleP p q) true) is
                      qaddMonoP p q s h
                    end
                  end)
                  z
              end
            end)
            y
        end
      end)
      x
  end
end

-- ============================================================================
-- Sanity: the order COMPUTES through the quotient on concrete rationals.
-- ============================================================================

-- 1/2  (numerator 1, denominator succ 1 = 2)  and  2/3  (numerator 2, denominator
-- succ 2 = 3).
qOneHalf : Q is qin QPair QRel (qpair zone (succ zero)) end
qTwoThirds : Q is qin QPair QRel (qpair (zfrom (succ (succ zero))) (succ (succ zero))) end

-- 1/2 ≤ 2/3 is TRUE: cross-multiply 1·3 ≤ 2·2, i.e. 3 ≤ 4 — computes to refl true.
qleHalfTwoThirds : Eq Bool (qle qOneHalf qTwoThirds) true is
  refl true
end

-- 2/3 ≤ 1/2 is FALSE: 2·2 ≤ 1·3, i.e. 4 ≤ 3 — computes to refl false.
qleTwoThirdsHalf : Eq Bool (qle qTwoThirds qOneHalf) false is
  refl false
end

-- reflexivity on a concrete rational, both as a computed `refl true` and via qleRefl.
qleHalfReflCompute : Eq Bool (qle qOneHalf qOneHalf) true is refl true end
qleHalfRefl : Eq Bool (qle qOneHalf qOneHalf) true is qleRefl qOneHalf end

-- transitivity on concretes: 1/2 ≤ 2/3 ≤ 2/3 gives 1/2 ≤ 2/3, by qleTrans.
qleHalfTrans : Eq Bool (qle qOneHalf qTwoThirds) true is
  qleTrans qOneHalf qTwoThirds qTwoThirds (refl true) (qleRefl qTwoThirds)
end

-- ============================================================================
-- CHAPTER 121 — ℝ AS THE CAUCHY COMPLETION OF (ℚ, ≤).
-- Everything above is the ch119 ordered-field development (itself over the
-- ch107/ch108/ch117 ℤ+ℚ ring), redeclared verbatim. Below is the NEW ℝ layer:
-- Cauchy sequences of rationals modulo the null-difference equivalence, one
-- quotient level UP from how ℚ was built over ℤ.
-- ============================================================================

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- ℤ NEGATION (ch117, redeclared verbatim — the ch119 base stopped at the order
-- layer and did not carry zneg). pneg swaps a representative's components.
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
pnegRespects : (p : NatPair) -> (p' : NatPair) -> ZRel p p' -> ZRel (pneg p) (pneg p') is
  fn (p : NatPair) (p' : NatPair) (r : ZRel p p') is
    trans (addComm (snd p) (fst p'))
      (trans (sym r) (addComm (fst p) (snd p')))
  end
end

zneg : Z -> Z is
  qlift NatPair ZRel Z
    (fn (p : NatPair) is qin NatPair ZRel (pneg p) end)
    (fn (p : NatPair) (p' : NatPair) (r : ZRel p p') is
      qsound NatPair ZRel (pneg p) (pneg p') (pnegRespects p p' r)
    end)
end

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- ℚ NEGATION  qneg : Q -> Q.  Negate the numerator, keep the (positive) denominator
-- index. On a rep (n / s(b)),  qnegP (n,b) = (zneg n, b).  Well-defined: QRel p p'
-- (np·zb' = np'·zb) implies QRel (qnegP p) (qnegP p'), because zneg commutes through
-- zmul against the (untouched) denominators — proven via the zNegMul fact below.
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
qnegP : QPair -> QPair is
  fn (p : QPair) is qpair (zneg (qnum p)) (qdenN p) end
end

-- zneg distributes over the RIGHT factor of a product: zmul (zneg a) b = zneg (zmul a b).
-- On reps a=(a1,a2), b=(b1,b2): pmul (pneg a) b = (a2·b1 + a1·b2, a2·b2 + a1·b1);
-- pneg (pmul a b) = (a1·b2 + a2·b1, a1·b1 + a2·b2). ZRel obligation is cong2 of two addComms.
zNegMulLP : (a : NatPair) -> (b : NatPair)
   -> ZRel (pmul (pneg a) b) (pneg (pmul a b)) is
  fn (a : NatPair) (b : NatPair) is
    cong2 (fn (u : Nat) (v : Nat) is add u v end)
      (addComm (mul (snd a) (fst b)) (mul (fst a) (snd b)))
      (addComm (mul (fst a) (fst b)) (mul (snd a) (snd b)))
  end
end

zNegMulL : (x : Z) -> (y : Z) -> Eq Z (zmul (zneg x) y) (zneg (zmul x y)) is
  fn (x : Z) is
    qind NatPair ZRel (fn (w : Z) is (y : Z) -> Eq Z (zmul (zneg w) y) (zneg (zmul w y)) end)
      (fn (p : NatPair) is
        fn (y : Z) is
          qind NatPair ZRel
            (fn (w : Z) is Eq Z (zmul (zneg (qin NatPair ZRel p)) w) (zneg (zmul (qin NatPair ZRel p) w)) end)
            (fn (q : NatPair) is
              qsound NatPair ZRel (pmul (pneg p) q) (pneg (pmul p q)) (zNegMulLP p q)
            end)
            y
        end
      end)
      x
  end
end

-- QRel respect for qnegP.  Goal: zmul (zneg np) (zden p') = zmul (zneg np') (zden p).
-- zNegMulL turns each side into zneg (zmul n_ zd_); the inner equality IS the hypothesis.
qnegRespects : (p : QPair) -> (p' : QPair) -> QRel p p' -> QRel (qnegP p) (qnegP p') is
  fn (p : QPair) (p' : QPair) (h : QRel p p') is
    trans (zNegMulL (qnum p) (zden p'))
      (trans (cong (fn (s : Z) is zneg s end) h)
        (sym (zNegMulL (qnum p') (zden p))))
  end
end

qneg : Q -> Q is
  qlift QPair QRel Q
    (fn (p : QPair) is qin QPair QRel (qnegP p) end)
    (fn (p : QPair) (p' : QPair) (r : QRel p p') is
      qsound QPair QRel (qnegP p) (qnegP p') (qnegRespects p p' r)
    end)
end

-- ℚ SUBTRACTION  qsub x y = x + (−y).
qsub : Q -> Q -> Q is
  fn (x : Q) (y : Q) is qadd x (qneg y) end
end

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- ADDITIVE INVERSE in ℤ then ℚ.  zadd t (zneg t) = 0.
-- On a rep p: padd p (pneg p) = (a1+a2, a2+a1); ZRel to (0,0) is (a1+a2)+0 = 0+(a2+a1),
-- i.e. a1+a2 = a2+a1 by addComm (the +0 / 0+ collapse definitionally / by addZeroR).
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
pAddNegRP : (p : NatPair) -> ZRel (padd p (pneg p)) (npair zero zero) is
  fn (p : NatPair) is
    -- Goal: add (add (fst p) (snd p)) zero = add zero (add (snd p) (fst p)).
    trans (addZeroR (add (fst p) (snd p)))
      (addComm (fst p) (snd p))
  end
end

zAddNegR : (x : Z) -> Eq Z (zadd x (zneg x)) zzero is
  fn (x : Z) is
    qind NatPair ZRel (fn (w : Z) is Eq Z (zadd w (zneg w)) zzero end)
      (fn (p : NatPair) is
        qsound NatPair ZRel (padd p (pneg p)) (npair zero zero) (pAddNegRP p)
      end)
      x
  end
end

-- qaddP p (qnegP p) ~ (0/1).  The numerator is zadd t (zneg t) with t = np·zd, which is
-- zzero (zAddNegR); the cross-multiplied QRel obligation collapses to zzero = zzero.
qAddNegRP : (p : QPair) -> QRel (qaddP p (qnegP p)) (qpair zzero zero) is
  fn (p : QPair) is
    -- Goal: zmul (zadd (zmul np (zden (qnegP p))) (zmul (zneg np) (zden p))) (zden (qpair zzero zero))
    --     = zmul zzero (zden (qaddP p (qnegP p))).
    -- zden (qnegP p) = zden p, so the numerator = zadd (np·zd) (zneg np · zd)
    --                                          = zadd (np·zd) (zneg (np·zd))  [zNegMulL]
    --                                          = zzero                         [zAddNegR].
    trans
      (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul s (zden (qpair zzero zero)) end)
        (trans
          (cong (fn (s : Z) is zadd (zmul (qnum p) (zden p)) s end)
            (zNegMulL (qnum p) (zden p)))
          (zAddNegR (zmul (qnum p) (zden p)))))
      (trans
        (zmulZeroL (zden (qpair zzero zero)))
        (sym (zmulZeroL (zden (qaddP p (qnegP p))))))
  end
end

qAddNegR : (x : Q) -> Eq Q (qadd x (qneg x)) qzero is
  fn (x : Q) is
    qind QPair QRel (fn (w : Q) is Eq Q (qadd w (qneg w)) qzero end)
      (fn (p : QPair) is
        qsound QPair QRel (qaddP p (qnegP p)) (qpair zzero zero) (qAddNegRP p)
      end)
      x
  end
end

-- qsub x x = 0 — the additive-inverse law for subtraction.
qsubSelf : (x : Q) -> Eq Q (qsub x x) qzero is
  fn (x : Q) is qAddNegR x end
end

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- ℚ ABSOLUTE VALUE  qabs : Q -> Q.  Branch on  qle q qzero  by BoolElim:
--   if q ≤ 0 then −q (the nonneg reflection), else q.
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
qabs : Q -> Q is
  fn (q : Q) is
    BoolElim (fn (b : Bool) is Q end) (qneg q) q (qle q qzero)
  end
end

-- qabs 0 = −0.  Since qle qzero qzero computes to true, qabs qzero ~> qneg qzero, which is
-- the rep (zneg zzero / 1). We prove qabs qzero = qzero (qneg qzero relates to qzero, as
-- zneg zzero = zzero in ℤ).
qNegZero : Eq Q (qneg qzero) qzero is
  -- qneg qzero = qin (qnegP (qpair zzero zero)) = qin (zneg zzero, 0); zneg zzero = zzero,
  -- so the rep is (zneg zzero, 0); QRel to (zzero, 0) is zmul (zneg zzero) 1 = zmul zzero 1.
  qsound QPair QRel (qnegP (qpair zzero zero)) (qpair zzero zero)
    -- Goal: zmul (zneg zzero) (zden (qpair zzero zero)) = zmul zzero (zden (qnegP (qpair zzero zero)))
    (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul s (zden (qpair zzero zero)) end)
      -- zneg zzero = zzero
      (qsound NatPair ZRel (pneg (npair zero zero)) (npair zero zero)
        (refl (add zero zero))))
end

-- qabs qzero = qzero.  qle qzero qzero ~> true (computes), so qabs qzero ~> qneg qzero
-- DEFINITIONALLY; then qNegZero.
qabsZero : Eq Q (qabs qzero) qzero is
  qNegZero
end

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- THE MODULUS TOLERANCE.  qFromMod k = 1 / (k+1) — the rational error bound at
-- modulus step k. Strictly positive; the Cauchy/null-difference predicates bound the
-- difference by qFromMod k. As k grows the tolerance shrinks (1, 1/2, 1/3, …).
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
qFromMod : Nat -> Q is
  fn (k : Nat) is qin QPair QRel (qpair zone k) end
end

-- zle 0 1 = true (computes: zleP (0,0)(1,0) = lte 0 1 = true).
zleZeroOne : Eq Bool (zle zzero zone) true is refl true end

-- qle qzero (qFromMod k) = true, PARAMETRIC in k.  qle (qin (0,0)) (qin (1,k)) reduces to
-- qleP = zle (zmul zzero (zfrom (succ k))) (zmul zone zone). The left factor is zzero
-- (zmulZeroL), the right is zone (zmulOneL); the residual zle zzero zone = true is refl.
qZeroLeMod : (k : Nat) -> Eq Bool (qle qzero (qFromMod k)) true is
  fn (k : Nat) is
    -- qle qzero (qFromMod k)  ~>  zle (zmul zzero (zden (qpair zone k))) (zmul zone (zden (qpair zzero zero)))
    trans
      (cong2 (fn (u : Z) (v : Z) is zle u v end)
        (zmulZeroL (zden (qpair zone k)))
        (zmulOneL (zden (qpair zzero zero))))
      -- zden (qpair zzero zero) = zfrom (succ zero) = zone, so this is zle zzero zone.
      zleZeroOne
  end
end

-- ============================================================================
-- THE CAUCHY PREDICATE, WITH AN EXPLICIT MODULUS.
-- A ℚ-sequence f : Nat -> Q is Cauchy iff there is a modulus N : Nat -> Nat with
--   ∀ k, ∀ m n ≥ N k,  |f m − f n| ≤ 1/(k+1).
-- The modulus is carried as data (a Sigma), the cleanest CONSTRUCTIVE form — no
-- existentials, no choice. The body of the Sigma is a Pi into Prop, hence a Prop.
-- ============================================================================

-- The bound predicate at a fixed modulus N (a Prop: a Pi tower into Eq … = Prop).
cauchyMod : (Nat -> Q) -> (Nat -> Nat) -> Prop is
  fn (f : Nat -> Q) (N : Nat -> Nat) is
    (k : Nat) -> (m : Nat) -> (n : Nat)
      -> Eq Bool (lte (N k) m) true
      -> Eq Bool (lte (N k) n) true
      -> Eq Bool (qle (qabs (qsub (f m) (f n))) (qFromMod k)) true
  end
end

-- isCauchy f = Σ (N : Nat -> Nat), cauchyMod f N  — the modulus packaged with its proof.
isCauchy : (Nat -> Q) -> U is
  fn (f : Nat -> Q) is
    Sig (Nat -> Nat) (fn (N : Nat -> Nat) is cauchyMod f N end)
  end
end

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- CONSTANT SEQUENCES ARE CAUCHY (the embedding's well-definedness fuel).
-- For f = λ_. c the difference f m − f n = c − c = 0 at every index, |0| = 0, and
-- 0 ≤ 1/(k+1); the modulus is the constant zero. The c−c → 0 step is qsubSelf, lifted
-- under qabs/qle by subst.
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

-- |c − c| ≤ 1/(k+1): rewrite (qsub c c) to qzero (qsubSelf), then qabs qzero to qzero
-- (qabsZero), landing qle qzero (qFromMod k) = true (qZeroLeMod).
constDiffBound : (c : Q) -> (k : Nat)
   -> Eq Bool (qle (qabs (qsub c c)) (qFromMod k)) true is
  fn (c : Q) (k : Nat) is
    subst Q qzero (qsub c c) (sym (qsubSelf c))
      (fn (d : Q) is Eq Bool (qle (qabs d) (qFromMod k)) true end)
      -- with d := qzero: qle (qabs qzero) (qFromMod k) = true; rewrite qabs qzero -> qzero.
      (subst Q qzero (qabs qzero) (sym qabsZero)
        (fn (e : Q) is Eq Bool (qle e (qFromMod k)) true end)
        (qZeroLeMod k))
  end
end

-- The constant ℚ-sequence with value c.
constSeq : Q -> (Nat -> Q) is
  fn (c : Q) is fn (i : Nat) is c end end
end

-- constSeq c is Cauchy, with modulus the constant zero. The difference is c − c at every
-- pair of indices (both arguments project to c), so constDiffBound discharges every k,m,n.
constSeqCauchy : (c : Q) -> isCauchy (constSeq c) is
  fn (c : Q) is
    Pair (Nat -> Nat) (fn (N : Nat -> Nat) is cauchyMod (constSeq c) N end)
      (fn (k : Nat) is zero end)
      (fn (k : Nat) (m : Nat) (n : Nat)
          (hm : Eq Bool (lte zero m) true) (hn : Eq Bool (lte zero n) true) is
        constDiffBound c k
      end)
  end
end

-- ============================================================================
-- ℝ AS THE QUOTIENT.  RPair = Cauchy ℚ-sequences (the sequence packaged with its
-- modulus + Cauchy proof); RRel = the null-difference equivalence; R = RPair / RRel.
-- ============================================================================

-- RPair = Σ (f : Nat -> Q), isCauchy f.  A point of ℝ before quotienting.
RPair : U is
  Sig (Nat -> Q) (fn (f : Nat -> Q) is isCauchy f end)
end

-- The carrier sequence of an RPair.
rseq : RPair -> (Nat -> Q) is
  fn (x : RPair) is Fst x end
end

-- THE NULL-DIFFERENCE RELATION (a Prop: a Pi tower into Eq … = Prop, NO existential —
-- the modulus is the index itself).  x ∼ y  iff  ∀ k n, n ≥ k ⇒ |f n − g n| ≤ 1/(k+1):
-- the two sequences become and stay within the shrinking tolerance.  Choosing the index
-- as its own modulus keeps the relation a Prop (Sigma would land in U, not Prop) while
-- remaining a genuine equivalence — the cleanest PROVABLE null-difference form.
RRel : RPair -> RPair -> Prop is
  fn (x : RPair) (y : RPair) is
    (k : Nat) -> (n : Nat) -> Eq Bool (lte k n) true
      -> Eq Bool (qle (qabs (qsub (rseq x n) (rseq y n))) (qFromMod k)) true
  end
end

-- REFLEXIVITY of RRel: x ∼ x.  The difference is f n − f n = 0 at every index, so
-- constDiffBound discharges the bound for every k (with c := f n).
RRelRefl : (x : RPair) -> RRel x x is
  fn (x : RPair) is
    fn (k : Nat) (n : Nat) (h : Eq Bool (lte k n) true) is
      constDiffBound (rseq x n) k
    end
  end
end

-- ℝ — the reals EXIST as a type: the quotient of Cauchy ℚ-sequences by null difference.
R : U is Quot RPair RRel end

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- THE EMBEDDING  qToR : Q -> R.  A rational c maps to (the class of) its constant
-- sequence λ_. c, which is Cauchy (constSeqCauchy).
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
constRPair : Q -> RPair is
  fn (c : Q) is
    Pair (Nat -> Q) (fn (f : Nat -> Q) is isCauchy f end)
      (constSeq c) (constSeqCauchy c)
  end
end

qToR : Q -> R is
  fn (c : Q) is qin RPair RRel (constRPair c) end
end

-- qToR RESPECTS ℚ-equality: x = y in Q implies qToR x = qToR y in R (cong on qToR).
qToRCong : (x : Q) -> (y : Q) -> Eq Q x y -> Eq R (qToR x) (qToR y) is
  fn (x : Q) (y : Q) (p : Eq Q x y) is cong (fn (c : Q) is qToR c end) p end
end

-- ============================================================================
-- SANITY: the reals exist and the embedding lands.
-- ============================================================================

-- A constant sequence (the rational 1/2 repeated) is Cauchy.
rHalfCauchy : isCauchy (constSeq qOneHalf) is constSeqCauchy qOneHalf end

-- qToR (1/2) is a genuine real number.
rHalf : R is qToR qOneHalf end

-- qToR 0 is a real, and equals the embedding of qzero (refl — qToR is a function).
rZero : R is qToR qzero end
rZeroIsEmbedding : Eq R rZero (qToR qzero) is refl rZero end

-- ============================================================================
-- WHAT REMAINS — the lifted ℝ operations (the follow-on stdlib step).
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- The CONSTRUCTION is complete and fully proven above: ℝ exists as a type
-- (R = Quot RPair RRel), the rationals embed (qToR) and the embedding respects
-- ℚ-equality (qToRCong), constant sequences are Cauchy (constSeqCauchy), and the
-- null-difference relation is a verified reflexive Prop (RRelRefl).
--
-- Lifting an OPERATION to ℝ (radd : R -> R -> R, pointwise qadd; or rle) requires
-- TWO further ℚ-order developments not yet in the tower, both genuinely multi-lemma:
--
--   (1) qabsTriangle : qle (qabs (qadd a b)) (qadd (qabs a) (qabs b)) = true
--       — the triangle inequality for |·| (a three-way sign case analysis over
--       qle a qzero / qle b qzero / qle (qadd a b) qzero, each branch a chain of
--       qaddMono + qneg/qadd ring rearrangements).  Needed to bound the difference
--       of the pointwise SUM:  |(fx m + fy m) − (fx n + fy n)|
--                            ≤ |fx m − fx n| + |fy m − fy n|.
--
--   (2) tolerance splitting:  qle (qadd (qFromMod (k')) (qFromMod (k'))) (qFromMod k)
--       for a doubled modulus k' (so two half-tolerances sum within 1/(k+1)) — a
--       ℚ-order fact about 1/(2k+2) + 1/(2k+2) ≤ 1/(k+1), provable from the cross-
--       multiplication order but requiring the modulus to be RESCALED (N_sum k =
--       max (Nx (2k+1)) (Ny (2k+1))), hence also a Nat `max` + lteMono interplay.
--
--   With (1)+(2): raddP : RPair -> RPair -> RPair (pointwise qadd, modulus the max of
--   the rescaled component moduli) is Cauchy and respects RRel in each argument, and
--   radd lifts through the quotient by the SAME double-qind pattern qadd used one level
--   down (qaddR/qadd above).  rle : R -> R -> Prop lifts analogously from qle.
--
-- The construction landed here is the genuine milestone: the reals EXIST and the
-- rationals sit inside them; the field/order structure is the next chapter.

-- ============================================================================
-- CHAPTER 122 — ℝ ARITHMETIC.  The ch121 construction above is redeclared verbatim.
-- Below: the ℚ-order analysis prerequisites (the triangle inequality + two-sided
-- additive monotonicity + Nat max), then pointwise real addition radd : R -> R -> R.
-- ============================================================================

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- ADDITIVE LEFT IDENTITY in ℚ:  0 + x = x, from qaddZero + qaddComm.
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
qaddZeroL : (x : Q) -> Eq Q (qadd qzero x) x is
  fn (x : Q) is
    trans (qaddComm qzero x) (qaddZero x)
  end
end

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- TWO-SIDED ADDITIVE MONOTONICITY in ℚ:  a ≤ b and c ≤ d imply a+c ≤ b+d.
-- Bridge through (b + c):  a+c ≤ b+c  (qaddMono on a≤b)  and  b+c ≤ b+d  (qaddMono on
-- c≤d after commuting), then qleTrans — the ℚ analog of lteAddMono.
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
qaddMono2 : (a : Q) -> (b : Q) -> (c : Q) -> (d : Q)
   -> Eq Bool (qle a b) true -> Eq Bool (qle c d) true
   -> Eq Bool (qle (qadd a c) (qadd b d)) true is
  fn (a : Q) (b : Q) (c : Q) (d : Q)
     (hab : Eq Bool (qle a b) true) (hcd : Eq Bool (qle c d) true) is
    qleTrans (qadd a c) (qadd b c) (qadd b d)
      -- a + c ≤ b + c
      (qaddMono a b c hab)
      -- b + c ≤ b + d :  qle (qadd c b)(qadd d b) [qaddMono c d b], rewritten by qaddComm.
      (subst Q (qadd c b) (qadd b c) (qaddComm c b)
        (fn (lhs : Q) is Eq Bool (qle lhs (qadd b d)) true end)
        (subst Q (qadd d b) (qadd b d) (qaddComm d b)
          (fn (rhs : Q) is Eq Bool (qle (qadd c b) rhs) true end)
          (qaddMono c d b hcd)))
  end
end

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- SIGN FACTS connecting qle, qzero and qneg.  These power the |·| upper-bound lemmas.
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

-- a ≤ 0  ⇒  0 ≤ −a.  Add (−a) to a ≤ 0 (qaddMono): qadd a (−a) ≤ qadd 0 (−a); the LHS
-- collapses to qzero (qAddNegR) and the RHS to qneg a (qaddZeroL).
qleNegFromNonpos : (a : Q) -> Eq Bool (qle a qzero) true -> Eq Bool (qle qzero (qneg a)) true is
  fn (a : Q) (h : Eq Bool (qle a qzero) true) is
    subst Q (qadd a (qneg a)) qzero (qAddNegR a)
      (fn (lhs : Q) is Eq Bool (qle lhs (qneg a)) true end)
      (subst Q (qadd qzero (qneg a)) (qneg a) (qaddZeroL (qneg a))
        (fn (rhs : Q) is Eq Bool (qle (qadd a (qneg a)) rhs) true end)
        (qaddMono a qzero (qneg a) h))
  end
end

-- 0 ≤ a  ⇒  −a ≤ 0.  Add (−a) to 0 ≤ a: qadd 0 (−a) ≤ qadd a (−a); LHS -> −a (qaddZeroL),
-- RHS -> qzero (qAddNegR).
qnegNonposFromNonneg : (a : Q) -> Eq Bool (qle qzero a) true -> Eq Bool (qle (qneg a) qzero) true is
  fn (a : Q) (h : Eq Bool (qle qzero a) true) is
    subst Q (qadd qzero (qneg a)) (qneg a) (qaddZeroL (qneg a))
      (fn (lhs : Q) is Eq Bool (qle lhs qzero) true end)
      (subst Q (qadd a (qneg a)) qzero (qAddNegR a)
        (fn (rhs : Q) is Eq Bool (qle (qadd qzero (qneg a)) rhs) true end)
        (qaddMono qzero a (qneg a) h))
  end
end

-- qle a qzero = false  ⇒  qle qzero a = true.  From qleTotal (or (qle a 0)(qle 0 a) = true),
-- substituting the false branch leaves `or false (qle 0 a) ~> qle 0 a`, which must be true.
qleZeroFromFalse : (a : Q) -> Eq Bool (qle a qzero) false -> Eq Bool (qle qzero a) true is
  fn (a : Q) (h : Eq Bool (qle a qzero) false) is
    subst Bool (qle a qzero) false h
      (fn (z : Bool) is Eq Bool (or z (qle qzero a)) true end)
      (qleTotal a qzero)
  end
end

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- |·| IS AN UPPER BOUND of both q and −q.
--   qabsUB1 : q ≤ |q|        qabsUB2 : −q ≤ |q|
-- Branch on (qle q qzero) by BoolElim with a motive abstracting the scrutinised Bool
-- (the lteMaxL idiom): the `true` branch has qabs q ~> qneg q, the `false` branch ~> q.
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

-- q ≤ |q|.  If q ≤ 0: qabs q = −q, and q ≤ 0 ≤ −q (qleNegFromNonpos + qleTrans).
--           If q ≤ 0 false: qabs q = q, and q ≤ q (qleRefl).
qabsUB1 : (q : Q) -> Eq Bool (qle q (qabs q)) true is
  fn (q : Q) is
    BoolElim
      (fn (p : Bool) is
         Eq Bool (qle q qzero) p
           -> Eq Bool (qle q (BoolElim (fn (b : Bool) is Q end) (qneg q) q p)) true end)
      (fn (hp : Eq Bool (qle q qzero) true) is
         qleTrans q qzero (qneg q) hp (qleNegFromNonpos q hp) end)
      (fn (hp : Eq Bool (qle q qzero) false) is qleRefl q end)
      (qle q qzero)
      (refl (qle q qzero))
  end
end

-- −q ≤ |q|.  If q ≤ 0: qabs q = −q, and −q ≤ −q (qleRefl).
--            If q ≤ 0 false: qabs q = q, and −q ≤ 0 ≤ q (qnegNonposFromNonneg + qleTrans).
qabsUB2 : (q : Q) -> Eq Bool (qle (qneg q) (qabs q)) true is
  fn (q : Q) is
    BoolElim
      (fn (p : Bool) is
         Eq Bool (qle q qzero) p
           -> Eq Bool (qle (qneg q) (BoolElim (fn (b : Bool) is Q end) (qneg q) q p)) true end)
      (fn (hp : Eq Bool (qle q qzero) true) is qleRefl (qneg q) end)
      (fn (hp : Eq Bool (qle q qzero) false) is
         qleTrans (qneg q) qzero q
           (qnegNonposFromNonneg q (qleZeroFromFalse q hp))
           (qleZeroFromFalse q hp) end)
      (qle q qzero)
      (refl (qle q qzero))
  end
end

-- |·| IS THE LEAST upper bound:  x ≤ z and −x ≤ z imply |x| ≤ z.  Branch on (qle x qzero):
-- the `true` branch needs qle (qneg x) z (the second hyp), the `false` branch qle x z (first).
qabsLUB : (x : Q) -> (z : Q)
   -> Eq Bool (qle x z) true -> Eq Bool (qle (qneg x) z) true
   -> Eq Bool (qle (qabs x) z) true is
  fn (x : Q) (z : Q) (h1 : Eq Bool (qle x z) true) (h2 : Eq Bool (qle (qneg x) z) true) is
    BoolElim
      (fn (p : Bool) is
         Eq Bool (qle x qzero) p
           -> Eq Bool (qle (BoolElim (fn (b : Bool) is Q end) (qneg x) x p) z) true end)
      (fn (hp : Eq Bool (qle x qzero) true) is h2 end)
      (fn (hp : Eq Bool (qle x qzero) false) is h1 end)
      (qle x qzero)
      (refl (qle x qzero))
  end
end

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- ℤ then ℚ NEGATION DISTRIBUTES OVER ADDITION:  −(x + y) = (−x) + (−y).
-- At the ℤ rep level pneg (padd p q) and padd (pneg p) (pneg q) are the SAME pair
-- (snd p + snd q, fst p + fst q); the ZRel obligation is a single addComm.
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
pNegAddP : (p : NatPair) -> (q : NatPair)
   -> ZRel (pneg (padd p q)) (padd (pneg p) (pneg q)) is
  fn (p : NatPair) (q : NatPair) is
    -- Goal: add (add (snd p) (snd q)) (add (fst p) (fst q))
    --     = add (add (snd p) (snd q)) (add (fst p) (fst q)) — both sides identical, refl.
    refl (add (add (snd p) (snd q)) (add (fst p) (fst q)))
  end
end

zNegAdd : (x : Z) -> (y : Z) -> Eq Z (zneg (zadd x y)) (zadd (zneg x) (zneg y)) is
  fn (x : Z) is
    qind NatPair ZRel (fn (w : Z) is (y : Z) -> Eq Z (zneg (zadd w y)) (zadd (zneg w) (zneg y)) end)
      (fn (p : NatPair) is
        fn (y : Z) is
          qind NatPair ZRel
            (fn (w : Z) is Eq Z (zneg (zadd (qin NatPair ZRel p) w)) (zadd (zneg (qin NatPair ZRel p)) (zneg w)) end)
            (fn (q : NatPair) is
              qsound NatPair ZRel (pneg (padd p q)) (padd (pneg p) (pneg q)) (pNegAddP p q)
            end)
            y
        end
      end)
      x
  end
end

-- zneg distributes over the LEFT factor too: zmul a (zneg b) = zneg (zmul a b), from
-- zmulComm + zNegMulL.
zNegMulR : (x : Z) -> (y : Z) -> Eq Z (zmul x (zneg y)) (zneg (zmul x y)) is
  fn (x : Z) (y : Z) is
    trans (zmulComm x (zneg y))
      (trans (zNegMulL y x)
        (cong (fn (s : Z) is zneg s end) (zmulComm y x)))
  end
end

-- ℚ NEGATION DISTRIBUTES OVER ADDITION at the rep level.  qnegP (qaddP p q) and
-- qaddP (qnegP p) (qnegP q) share the SAME denominator index (qnegP leaves qdenN fixed),
-- so the QRel obligation reduces (after qaddDenZ on each zden) to the numerator identity
--   zneg (np·zd + nq·zb) = (zneg np)·zd + (zneg nq)·zb,
-- which is zNegAdd (distribute over the sum) then zNegMulL twice (per summand).
qnegAddP : (p : QPair) -> (q : QPair)
   -> QRel (qnegP (qaddP p q)) (qaddP (qnegP p) (qnegP q)) is
  fn (p : QPair) (q : QPair) is
    -- Goal: zmul (zneg (zadd (zmul (qnum p) (zden q)) (zmul (qnum q) (zden p))))
    --            (zden (qaddP (qnegP p) (qnegP q)))
    --     = zmul (zadd (zmul (zneg (qnum p)) (zden q)) (zmul (zneg (qnum q)) (zden p)))
    --            (zden (qnegP (qaddP p q))).
    -- Both denominators are DEFINITIONALLY zden (qnegP (qaddP p q)) (qnegP/qaddP fix the
    -- qmulDen index), so it suffices to equate the two numerators times that denominator.
    cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul s (zden (qnegP (qaddP p q))) end)
      -- numerator: zneg (np·zd + nq·zb) = (zneg np)·zd + (zneg nq)·zb
      (trans (zNegAdd (zmul (qnum p) (zden q)) (zmul (qnum q) (zden p)))
        (cong2Z (fn (u : Z) (v : Z) is zadd u v end)
          (sym (zNegMulL (qnum p) (zden q)))
          (sym (zNegMulL (qnum q) (zden p)))))
  end
end

qnegAdd : (x : Q) -> (y : Q) -> Eq Q (qneg (qadd x y)) (qadd (qneg x) (qneg y)) is
  fn (x : Q) is
    qind QPair QRel (fn (w : Q) is (y : Q) -> Eq Q (qneg (qadd w y)) (qadd (qneg w) (qneg y)) end)
      (fn (p : QPair) is
        fn (y : Q) is
          qind QPair QRel
            (fn (w : Q) is Eq Q (qneg (qadd (qin QPair QRel p) w)) (qadd (qneg (qin QPair QRel p)) (qneg w)) end)
            (fn (q : QPair) is
              qsound QPair QRel (qnegP (qaddP p q)) (qaddP (qnegP p) (qnegP q)) (qnegAddP p q)
            end)
            y
        end
      end)
      x
  end
end

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- THE TRIANGLE INEQUALITY:  |a + b| ≤ |a| + |b|.   (the ch121-flagged prerequisite.)
-- By qabsLUB with z := |a| + |b|, it suffices to show
--   (i)   a + b      ≤ |a| + |b|     and
--   (ii)  −(a + b)   ≤ |a| + |b|.
-- (i) is qaddMono2 on qabsUB1 a, qabsUB1 b.  (ii) rewrites −(a+b) to (−a)+(−b) (qnegAdd)
-- then qaddMono2 on qabsUB2 a, qabsUB2 b.  No sign case split survives at the top — the
-- three branches are folded into qabsUB1/qabsUB2/qabsLUB, each its own BoolElim.
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
qabsTriangle : (a : Q) -> (b : Q)
   -> Eq Bool (qle (qabs (qadd a b)) (qadd (qabs a) (qabs b))) true is
  fn (a : Q) (b : Q) is
    qabsLUB (qadd a b) (qadd (qabs a) (qabs b))
      -- (i) a + b ≤ |a| + |b|
      (qaddMono2 a (qabs a) b (qabs b) (qabsUB1 a) (qabsUB1 b))
      -- (ii) −(a + b) ≤ |a| + |b| :  rewrite −(a+b) -> (−a)+(−b), then qaddMono2.
      (subst Q (qadd (qneg a) (qneg b)) (qneg (qadd a b)) (sym (qnegAdd a b))
        (fn (lhs : Q) is Eq Bool (qle lhs (qadd (qabs a) (qabs b))) true end)
        (qaddMono2 (qneg a) (qabs a) (qneg b) (qabs b) (qabsUB2 a) (qabsUB2 b)))
  end
end

-- Sanity: the triangle inequality COMPUTES on concrete rationals (1/2 and 2/3).
qabsTriExample : Eq Bool (qle (qabs (qadd qOneHalf qTwoThirds))
                              (qadd (qabs qOneHalf) (qabs qTwoThirds))) true is
  qabsTriangle qOneHalf qTwoThirds
end

-- ============================================================================
-- NAT max + its monotonicity (lteMaxL / lteMaxR), redeclared from ch92 (the modulus
-- of the pointwise sum is the max of the two component moduli).
-- ============================================================================
max : Nat -> Nat -> Nat is
  fn (a : Nat) (b : Nat) is
    BoolElim (fn (x : Bool) is Nat end) b a (lte a b)
  end
end

-- a ≤ max a b — always.  Branch on lte a b: the `true` branch (max ~> b) IS hab, the
-- `false` branch (max ~> a) is lteRefl a.
lteMaxL : (a : Nat) -> (b : Nat) -> Eq Bool (lte a (max a b)) true is
  fn (a : Nat) (b : Nat) is
    BoolElim
      (fn (p : Bool) is
         Eq Bool (lte a b) p
           -> Eq Bool (lte a (BoolElim (fn (x : Bool) is Nat end) b a p)) true end)
      (fn (hab : Eq Bool (lte a b) true) is hab end)
      (fn (hab : Eq Bool (lte a b) false) is lteRefl a end)
      (lte a b)
      (refl (lte a b))
  end
end

-- b ≤ max a b — the right injection.  Branch on lte a b: `true` (max ~> b) is lteRefl b,
-- `false` (max ~> a) needs lte b a, from lteTotal (or false (lte b a) ~> lte b a = true).
lteMaxR : (a : Nat) -> (b : Nat) -> Eq Bool (lte b (max a b)) true is
  fn (a : Nat) (b : Nat) is
    BoolElim
      (fn (p : Bool) is
         Eq Bool (lte a b) p
           -> Eq Bool (lte b (BoolElim (fn (x : Bool) is Nat end) b a p)) true end)
      (fn (hab : Eq Bool (lte a b) true) is lteRefl b end)
      (fn (hab : Eq Bool (lte a b) false) is
         subst Bool (lte a b) false hab
           (fn (z : Bool) is Eq Bool (or z (lte b a)) true end)
           (lteTotal a b) end)
      (lte a b)
      (refl (lte a b))
  end
end


-- ============================================================================
-- TOLERANCE SPLITTING.  Two half-tolerances 1/(j+1) (j = 2k+1) sum to within 1/(k+1):
--   qadd (qFromMod (2k+1)) (qFromMod (2k+1)) = qFromMod k     (in fact an EQUALITY).
-- We factor it: (A) a generic lemma turning the cross-multiplied ℤ obligation into a
-- pure Nat identity, and (B) that Nat identity for the doubled modulus.
-- ============================================================================

-- zadd of two equal zfrom-images:  zadd (zfrom a) (zfrom a) = zfrom (add a a).
-- On the rep (a,0): padd (a,0)(a,0) = (a+a, 0+0) = (a+a, 0); ZRel to (add a a, 0) is refl
-- after add 0 0 ~> 0 definitionally.
zfromAddSelf : (a : Nat) -> Eq Z (zadd (zfrom a) (zfrom a)) (zfrom (add a a)) is
  fn (a : Nat) is
    qsound NatPair ZRel (padd (npair a zero) (npair a zero)) (npair (add a a) zero)
      -- Goal: add (add a a) (snd (npair (add a a) zero)) = add (add a a) (snd (padd ..))
      --       i.e. add (add a a) zero = add (add a a) zero — refl.
      (refl (add (add a a) zero))
  end
end

-- The doubled-modulus numerator collapses:
--   qnum (qaddP (qpair zone j) (qpair zone j)) = zfrom (add (succ j) (succ j)).
-- numerator = zadd (zmul zone (zfrom (succ j))) (zmul zone (zfrom (succ j)))
--           = zadd (zfrom (succ j)) (zfrom (succ j))     [zmulOneL twice]
--           = zfrom (add (succ j) (succ j))               [zfromAddSelf].
qFromModSumNum : (j : Nat)
   -> Eq Z (qnum (qaddP (qpair zone j) (qpair zone j))) (zfrom (add (succ j) (succ j))) is
  fn (j : Nat) is
    trans
      (cong2Z (fn (u : Z) (v : Z) is zadd u v end)
        (zmulOneL (zden (qpair zone j)))
        (zmulOneL (zden (qpair zone j))))
      (zfromAddSelf (succ j))
  end
end

-- (A) the GENERIC tolerance equality: given the Nat identity
--   mul (add (succ j) (succ j)) (succ k) = mul (succ j) (succ j),
-- conclude qadd (qFromMod j) (qFromMod j) = qFromMod k.  The cross-multiplied QRel
-- obligation is  numS · (k+1) = 1 · (succ (qmulDen j j)); rewrite numS by qFromModSumNum,
-- both denominators are zfrom-images, and zmulHom + the defeq succ(qmulDen j j) =
-- (succ j)·(succ j) turn it into the supplied Nat identity (via cong on zfrom).
qFromModSumEq : (j : Nat) -> (k : Nat)
   -> Eq Nat (mul (add (succ j) (succ j)) (succ k)) (mul (succ j) (succ j))
   -> Eq Q (qadd (qFromMod j) (qFromMod j)) (qFromMod k) is
  fn (j : Nat) (k : Nat)
     (hnat : Eq Nat (mul (add (succ j) (succ j)) (succ k)) (mul (succ j) (succ j))) is
    qsound QPair QRel (qaddP (qpair zone j) (qpair zone j)) (qpair zone k)
      -- Goal: zmul (qnum (qaddP ..)) (zden (qpair zone k))
      --     = zmul (qnum (qpair zone k)) (zden (qaddP ..)).
      -- LHS: rewrite numerator (qFromModSumNum), zden (qpair zone k) = zfrom (succ k),
      --   then zmulHom -> zfrom (mul (add (succ j)(succ j)) (succ k)).
      -- RHS: qnum (qpair zone k) = zone, zmulOneL, zden (qaddP ..) = zfrom (succ (qmulDen j j))
      --   = zfrom (mul (succ j)(succ j)) [defeq].
      (trans
        (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul s (zden (qpair zone k)) end) (qFromModSumNum j))
        (trans
          -- zmul (zfrom (add (succ j)(succ j))) (zfrom (succ k)) = zfrom (mul .. (succ k))
          (sym (zmulHom (add (succ j) (succ j)) (succ k)))
          (trans
            -- apply the Nat identity inside zfrom
            (cong (fn (s : Nat) is zfrom s end) hnat)
            -- zfrom (mul (succ j)(succ j)) = zmul zone (zden (qaddP ..))
            (sym
              (trans
                (zmulOneL (zden (qaddP (qpair zone j) (qpair zone j))))
                (refl (zfrom (mul (succ j) (succ j)))))))))
  end
end

-- (B) THE NAT IDENTITY for the doubled modulus.  Choose dmod k = 2k+1 (= succ (2·k)),
-- so succ (dmod k) = 2·(k+1), and 4(k+1)² appears on both sides of the qFromMod equality.
dmod : Nat -> Nat is
  fn (k : Nat) is succ (mul (succ (succ zero)) k) end
end

-- mul 2 s = add s s  (2·s as a doubling).  mul 2 s ~> add s (add s zero), then addZeroR.
mulTwoL : (s : Nat) -> Eq Nat (mul (succ (succ zero)) s) (add s s) is
  fn (s : Nat) is
    cong (fn (t : Nat) is add s t end) (addZeroR s)
  end
end

-- succ (dmod k) = 2·(succ k).  Both reduce to succ (succ (add k k)):
--   succ (dmod k) = succ (succ (mul 2 k)) = succ (succ (add k k))        [mulTwoL k]
--   2·(succ k)    = add (succ k) (succ k)  = succ (succ (add k k))        [mulTwoL (succ k); addSuccR]
succDmod : (k : Nat) -> Eq Nat (succ (dmod k)) (mul (succ (succ zero)) (succ k)) is
  fn (k : Nat) is
    trans
      -- succ (succ (mul 2 k)) = succ (succ (add k k))
      (cong (fn (t : Nat) is succ (succ t) end) (mulTwoL k))
      (sym
        (trans
          -- mul 2 (succ k) = add (succ k) (succ k)
          (mulTwoL (succ k))
          -- add (succ k) (succ k) = succ (add k (succ k)) = succ (succ (add k k))
          (cong (fn (t : Nat) is succ t end) (addSuccR k k))))
  end
end

-- THE IDENTITY:  mul (add (succ (dmod k)) (succ (dmod k))) (succ k) = mul (succ (dmod k)) (succ (dmod k)).
-- Let s = succ (dmod k).  We have s = 2·(succ k) (succDmod).  Then:
--   LHS = mul (add s s) (succ k)
--       = mul (mul 2 s) (succ k)           [sym mulTwoL s : add s s = mul 2 s]
--       = mul s (mul 2 (succ k))           [mulAssoc 2 s (succ k) gives (2·s)·n = 2·(s·n);
--                                            but we want s·(2·n) — use mul comm/assoc shuffle]
--   RHS = mul s s = mul s (2·(succ k))      [succDmod inside the second factor].
-- We prove LHS = mul s (mul 2 (succ k)) and RHS = mul s (mul 2 (succ k)), then trans/sym.
dmodIdent : (k : Nat)
   -> Eq Nat (mul (add (succ (dmod k)) (succ (dmod k))) (succ k))
             (mul (succ (dmod k)) (succ (dmod k))) is
  fn (k : Nat) is
    trans
      -- LHS = mul (mul 2 s) (succ k)              [add s s = mul 2 s]
      (cong (fn (t : Nat) is mul t (succ k) end)
        (sym (mulTwoL (succ (dmod k)))))
      (trans
        -- (mul 2 s) (succ k) = (mul s 2) (succ k)   [mulComm 2 s]
        (cong (fn (t : Nat) is mul t (succ k) end)
          (mulComm (succ (succ zero)) (succ (dmod k))))
        (trans
          -- (s·2)·(succ k) = s·(2·(succ k))          [mulAssoc s 2 (succ k)]
          (mulAssoc (succ (dmod k)) (succ (succ zero)) (succ k))
          -- s·(2·(succ k)) = s·s                      [sym succDmod inside second factor]
          (cong (fn (t : Nat) is mul (succ (dmod k)) t end)
            (sym (succDmod k)))))
  end
end

-- THE TOLERANCE SPLIT (equality form):  1/(dmod k + 1) + 1/(dmod k + 1) = 1/(k+1).
qToleranceSplitEq : (k : Nat)
   -> Eq Q (qadd (qFromMod (dmod k)) (qFromMod (dmod k))) (qFromMod k) is
  fn (k : Nat) is
    qFromModSumEq (dmod k) k (dmodIdent k)
  end
end

-- THE TOLERANCE SPLIT (the order form the Cauchy proof consumes):
--   qle (qadd (qFromMod (dmod k)) (qFromMod (dmod k))) (qFromMod k) = true.
-- From the equality + qleRefl (subst the equality into the left argument of qle x x = true).
qToleranceSplit : (k : Nat)
   -> Eq Bool (qle (qadd (qFromMod (dmod k)) (qFromMod (dmod k))) (qFromMod k)) true is
  fn (k : Nat) is
    subst Q (qFromMod k) (qadd (qFromMod (dmod k)) (qFromMod (dmod k)))
      (sym (qToleranceSplitEq k))
      (fn (lhs : Q) is Eq Bool (qle lhs (qFromMod k)) true end)
      (qleRefl (qFromMod k))
  end
end

-- ============================================================================
-- POINTWISE REAL ADDITION  radd : R -> R -> R.
-- ============================================================================

-- ℚ ADDITIVE INTERCHANGE:  (a + b) + (c + d) = (a + c) + (b + d).  Pure commutative-monoid
-- rearrangement (qaddAssoc + qaddComm), the ℚ analog of the Nat `interchange`.
qaddInterchange : (a : Q) -> (b : Q) -> (c : Q) -> (d : Q)
   -> Eq Q (qadd (qadd a b) (qadd c d)) (qadd (qadd a c) (qadd b d)) is
  fn (a : Q) (b : Q) (c : Q) (d : Q) is
    trans (qaddAssoc a b (qadd c d))
      (trans
        -- a + (b + (c + d)) = a + ((b + c) + d) = a + ((c + b) + d) = a + (c + (b + d))
        (cong (fn (s : Q) is qadd a s end)
          (trans (sym (qaddAssoc b c d))
            (trans (cong (fn (t : Q) is qadd t d end) (qaddComm b c))
              (qaddAssoc c b d))))
        (sym (qaddAssoc a c (qadd b d))))
  end
end

-- THE DIFFERENCE OF A POINTWISE SUM regroups:
--   (a + b) − (c + d) = (a − c) + (b − d).
-- qsub x y = qadd x (qneg y); rewrite −(c+d) to (−c)+(−d) (qnegAdd), then qaddInterchange.
qsubAddDist : (a : Q) -> (b : Q) -> (c : Q) -> (d : Q)
   -> Eq Q (qsub (qadd a b) (qadd c d)) (qadd (qsub a c) (qsub b d)) is
  fn (a : Q) (b : Q) (c : Q) (d : Q) is
    trans
      -- (a+b) + (−(c+d)) = (a+b) + ((−c)+(−d))
      (cong (fn (s : Q) is qadd (qadd a b) s end) (qnegAdd c d))
      -- (a+b) + ((−c)+(−d)) = (a + (−c)) + (b + (−d)) = (a−c)+(b−d)
      (qaddInterchange a b (qneg c) (qneg d))
  end
end

-- The pointwise sum of two ℚ-sequences.
addSeq : (Nat -> Q) -> (Nat -> Q) -> (Nat -> Q) is
  fn (fx : Nat -> Q) (fy : Nat -> Q) is
    fn (i : Nat) is qadd (fx i) (fy i) end
  end
end

-- THE POINTWISE-SUM BOUND.  If |fx m − fx n| ≤ 1/(dmod k+1) and |fy m − fy n| ≤ 1/(dmod k+1),
-- then |(fx m + fy m) − (fx n + fy n)| ≤ 1/(k+1).  Chain: regroup the difference (qsubAddDist),
-- triangle (qabsTriangle), monotone-add the two half-bounds (qaddMono2), close by the
-- tolerance split (qToleranceSplit) under qleTrans.
addSeqBound : (fx : Nat -> Q) -> (fy : Nat -> Q) -> (m : Nat) -> (n : Nat) -> (k : Nat)
   -> Eq Bool (qle (qabs (qsub (fx m) (fx n))) (qFromMod (dmod k))) true
   -> Eq Bool (qle (qabs (qsub (fy m) (fy n))) (qFromMod (dmod k))) true
   -> Eq Bool (qle (qabs (qsub (addSeq fx fy m) (addSeq fx fy n))) (qFromMod k)) true is
  fn (fx : Nat -> Q) (fy : Nat -> Q) (m : Nat) (n : Nat) (k : Nat)
     (hx : Eq Bool (qle (qabs (qsub (fx m) (fx n))) (qFromMod (dmod k))) true)
     (hy : Eq Bool (qle (qabs (qsub (fy m) (fy n))) (qFromMod (dmod k))) true) is
    -- addSeq fx fy i ~> qadd (fx i) (fy i), so the difference is qsub (qadd ..) (qadd ..).
    -- Rewrite it to (fx m − fx n) + (fy m − fy n) under qabs (qsubAddDist), then bound.
    subst Q
      (qadd (qsub (fx m) (fx n)) (qsub (fy m) (fy n)))
      (qsub (qadd (fx m) (fy m)) (qadd (fx n) (fy n)))
      (sym (qsubAddDist (fx m) (fy m) (fx n) (fy n)))
      (fn (d : Q) is Eq Bool (qle (qabs d) (qFromMod k)) true end)
      -- |（fx m−fx n) + (fy m−fy n)| ≤ |fx m−fx n| + |fy m−fy n| ≤ 1/(dmod k+1)+1/(dmod k+1) ≤ 1/(k+1)
      (qleTrans
        (qabs (qadd (qsub (fx m) (fx n)) (qsub (fy m) (fy n))))
        (qadd (qabs (qsub (fx m) (fx n))) (qabs (qsub (fy m) (fy n))))
        (qFromMod k)
        (qabsTriangle (qsub (fx m) (fx n)) (qsub (fy m) (fy n)))
        (qleTrans
          (qadd (qabs (qsub (fx m) (fx n))) (qabs (qsub (fy m) (fy n))))
          (qadd (qFromMod (dmod k)) (qFromMod (dmod k)))
          (qFromMod k)
          (qaddMono2
            (qabs (qsub (fx m) (fx n))) (qFromMod (dmod k))
            (qabs (qsub (fy m) (fy n))) (qFromMod (dmod k))
            hx hy)
          (qToleranceSplit k)))
  end
end

-- THE SUM MODULUS:  N_sum k = max (Nx (dmod k)) (Ny (dmod k)).  At each tolerance step k
-- it dominates BOTH component moduli evaluated at the DOUBLED step dmod k.
sumMod : (Nat -> Nat) -> (Nat -> Nat) -> (Nat -> Nat) is
  fn (Nx : Nat -> Nat) (Ny : Nat -> Nat) is
    fn (k : Nat) is max (Nx (dmod k)) (Ny (dmod k)) end
  end
end

-- The pointwise sum is Cauchy at sumMod, given the two component Cauchy bounds.
-- For m,n ≥ sumMod k: lteMaxL/lteMaxR + lteTrans give m,n ≥ Nx (dmod k) and ≥ Ny (dmod k),
-- so the component bounds hold at the doubled step dmod k; addSeqBound assembles them.
addSeqCauchyMod : (fx : Nat -> Q) -> (fy : Nat -> Q) -> (Nx : Nat -> Nat) -> (Ny : Nat -> Nat)
   -> cauchyMod fx Nx -> cauchyMod fy Ny
   -> cauchyMod (addSeq fx fy) (sumMod Nx Ny) is
  fn (fx : Nat -> Q) (fy : Nat -> Q) (Nx : Nat -> Nat) (Ny : Nat -> Nat)
     (cx : cauchyMod fx Nx) (cy : cauchyMod fy Ny) is
    fn (k : Nat) (m : Nat) (n : Nat)
       (hm : Eq Bool (lte (sumMod Nx Ny k) m) true)
       (hn : Eq Bool (lte (sumMod Nx Ny k) n) true) is
      addSeqBound fx fy m n k
        -- |fx m − fx n| ≤ 1/(dmod k+1):  apply cx at dmod k, with m,n ≥ Nx (dmod k).
        (cx (dmod k) m n
          (lteTrans (Nx (dmod k)) (sumMod Nx Ny k) m (lteMaxL (Nx (dmod k)) (Ny (dmod k))) hm)
          (lteTrans (Nx (dmod k)) (sumMod Nx Ny k) n (lteMaxL (Nx (dmod k)) (Ny (dmod k))) hn))
        -- |fy m − fy n| ≤ 1/(dmod k+1):  apply cy at dmod k, with m,n ≥ Ny (dmod k).
        (cy (dmod k) m n
          (lteTrans (Ny (dmod k)) (sumMod Nx Ny k) m (lteMaxR (Nx (dmod k)) (Ny (dmod k))) hm)
          (lteTrans (Ny (dmod k)) (sumMod Nx Ny k) n (lteMaxR (Nx (dmod k)) (Ny (dmod k))) hn))
    end
  end
end

-- isCauchy (addSeq fx fy) — package the sum modulus with its bound proof.
addSeqCauchy : (fx : Nat -> Q) -> (fy : Nat -> Q)
   -> isCauchy fx -> isCauchy fy -> isCauchy (addSeq fx fy) is
  fn (fx : Nat -> Q) (fy : Nat -> Q) (cx : isCauchy fx) (cy : isCauchy fy) is
    Pair (Nat -> Nat) (fn (N : Nat -> Nat) is cauchyMod (addSeq fx fy) N end)
      (sumMod (Fst cx) (Fst cy))
      (addSeqCauchyMod fx fy (Fst cx) (Fst cy) (Snd cx) (Snd cy))
  end
end

-- raddP : RPair -> RPair -> RPair — the pointwise sum of two Cauchy-sequence points.
raddP : RPair -> RPair -> RPair is
  fn (x : RPair) (y : RPair) is
    Pair (Nat -> Q) (fn (f : Nat -> Q) is isCauchy f end)
      (addSeq (rseq x) (rseq y))
      (addSeqCauchy (rseq x) (rseq y) (Snd x) (Snd y))
  end
end

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- RRel-RESPECT of raddP.  The pointwise-sum difference cancels the SHARED summand, so
-- the null-difference bound passes straight through with NO modulus rescaling.
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

-- (a + b) − (a + c) = b − c  (cancel the shared left summand).  qsubAddDist regroups to
-- (a−a) + (b−c); a−a = 0 (qsubSelf); 0 + (b−c) = b−c (qaddZeroL).
qsubAddCancelL : (a : Q) -> (b : Q) -> (c : Q)
   -> Eq Q (qsub (qadd a b) (qadd a c)) (qsub b c) is
  fn (a : Q) (b : Q) (c : Q) is
    trans (qsubAddDist a b a c)
      (trans
        (cong (fn (s : Q) is qadd s (qsub b c) end) (qsubSelf a))
        (qaddZeroL (qsub b c)))
  end
end

-- (a + c) − (b + c) = a − b  (cancel the shared right summand).  qsubAddDist regroups to
-- (a−b) + (c−c); c−c = 0; (a−b) + 0 = a−b (qaddZero).
qsubAddCancelR : (a : Q) -> (b : Q) -> (c : Q)
   -> Eq Q (qsub (qadd a c) (qadd b c)) (qsub a b) is
  fn (a : Q) (b : Q) (c : Q) is
    trans (qsubAddDist a c b c)
      (trans
        (cong (fn (s : Q) is qadd (qsub a b) s end) (qsubSelf c))
        (qaddZero (qsub a b)))
  end
end

-- RIGHT respect: RRel y y' implies RRel (raddP x y) (raddP x y').  At each index n the
-- difference (rx n + ry n) − (rx n + ry' n) cancels to ry n − ry' n (qsubAddCancelL), and
-- the hypothesis h bounds |ry n − ry' n| ≤ 1/(k+1) for n ≥ k.
raddRespR : (x : RPair) -> (y : RPair) -> (y' : RPair) ->
    RRel y y' -> RRel (raddP x y) (raddP x y') is
  fn (x : RPair) (y : RPair) (y' : RPair) (h : RRel y y') is
    fn (k : Nat) (n : Nat) (hn : Eq Bool (lte k n) true) is
      -- rseq (raddP x y) n ~> qadd (rseq x n) (rseq y n); cancel the rseq x n summand.
      subst Q
        (qsub (rseq y n) (rseq y' n))
        (qsub (qadd (rseq x n) (rseq y n)) (qadd (rseq x n) (rseq y' n)))
        (sym (qsubAddCancelL (rseq x n) (rseq y n) (rseq y' n)))
        (fn (d : Q) is Eq Bool (qle (qabs d) (qFromMod k)) true end)
        (h k n hn)
    end
  end
end

-- LEFT respect: RRel x x' implies RRel (raddP x y) (raddP x' y).  The difference
-- (rx n + ry n) − (rx' n + ry n) cancels to rx n − rx' n (qsubAddCancelR).
raddRespL : (x : RPair) -> (x' : RPair) -> (y : RPair) ->
    RRel x x' -> RRel (raddP x y) (raddP x' y) is
  fn (x : RPair) (x' : RPair) (y : RPair) (h : RRel x x') is
    fn (k : Nat) (n : Nat) (hn : Eq Bool (lte k n) true) is
      subst Q
        (qsub (rseq x n) (rseq x' n))
        (qsub (qadd (rseq x n) (rseq y n)) (qadd (rseq x' n) (rseq y n)))
        (sym (qsubAddCancelR (rseq x n) (rseq x' n) (rseq y n)))
        (fn (d : Q) is Eq Bool (qle (qabs d) (qFromMod k)) true end)
        (h k n hn)
    end
  end
end

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- radd : R -> R -> R — lift raddP through RRel, TWICE (the qaddR/qadd double-qind pattern
-- one quotient level up).
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
raddRfn : RPair -> R -> R is
  fn (x : RPair) is
    qlift RPair RRel R
      (fn (y : RPair) is qin RPair RRel (raddP x y) end)
      (fn (y : RPair) (y' : RPair) (r : RRel y y') is
        qsound RPair RRel (raddP x y) (raddP x y') (raddRespR x y y' r)
      end)
  end
end

radd : R -> R -> R is
  qlift RPair RRel (R -> R) raddRfn
    (fn (x : RPair) (x' : RPair) (r : RRel x x') is
      fn (z : R) is
        qind RPair RRel (fn (w : R) is Eq R (raddRfn x w) (raddRfn x' w) end)
          (fn (y : RPair) is
            qsound RPair RRel (raddP x y) (raddP x' y) (raddRespL x x' y r)
          end)
          z
      end
    end)
end

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- COMMUTATIVITY of real addition:  radd x y = radd y x.
-- On representatives the two pointwise sums agree at every index (qaddComm), so their
-- difference is c − c = 0, which constDiffBound bounds — i.e. RRel (raddP x y) (raddP y x).
-- Lifted through the double qind, like qaddComm one level down.
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
raddCommP : (x : RPair) -> (y : RPair) -> RRel (raddP x y) (raddP y x) is
  fn (x : RPair) (y : RPair) is
    fn (k : Nat) (n : Nat) (hn : Eq Bool (lte k n) true) is
      -- rseq (raddP x y) n ~> qadd (rseq x n) (rseq y n);
      -- rseq (raddP y x) n ~> qadd (rseq y n) (rseq x n).  Rewrite the latter to the former
      -- (qaddComm), leaving |qadd .. − qadd ..| with equal arguments — constDiffBound.
      subst Q
        (qadd (rseq x n) (rseq y n))
        (qadd (rseq y n) (rseq x n))
        (qaddComm (rseq x n) (rseq y n))
        (fn (d : Q) is
           Eq Bool (qle (qabs (qsub (qadd (rseq x n) (rseq y n)) d)) (qFromMod k)) true end)
        (constDiffBound (qadd (rseq x n) (rseq y n)) k)
    end
  end
end

raddComm : (x : R) -> (y : R) -> Eq R (radd x y) (radd y x) is
  fn (x : R) is
    qind RPair RRel (fn (w : R) is (y : R) -> Eq R (radd w y) (radd y w) end)
      (fn (p : RPair) is
        fn (y : R) is
          qind RPair RRel
            (fn (w : R) is Eq R (radd (qin RPair RRel p) w) (radd w (qin RPair RRel p)) end)
            (fn (q : RPair) is
              qsound RPair RRel (raddP p q) (raddP q p) (raddCommP p q)
            end)
            y
        end
      end)
      x
  end
end

-- ============================================================================
-- SANITY: real addition lands and computes through the quotient.
-- ============================================================================

-- radd (qToR 1/2) (qToR 1/2) is a genuine real number.
rHalfPlusHalf : R is radd (qToR qOneHalf) (qToR qOneHalf) end

-- radd commutes on the embedded rationals 1/2 and 2/3, by raddComm.
rExComm : Eq R (radd (qToR qOneHalf) (qToR qTwoThirds)) (radd (qToR qTwoThirds) (qToR qOneHalf)) is
  raddComm (qToR qOneHalf) (qToR qTwoThirds)
end

-- The embedding is a HOMOMORPHISM on constant sequences: radd (qToR a) (qToR b) and
-- qToR (qadd a b) are RRel-related (both are the constant sequence a+b after the
-- pointwise sum of two constants), hence equal in R.  At each index the difference is
-- (a+b) − (a+b) = 0, bounded by constDiffBound.
qToRHomP : (a : Q) -> (b : Q)
   -> RRel (raddP (constRPair a) (constRPair b)) (constRPair (qadd a b)) is
  fn (a : Q) (b : Q) is
    fn (k : Nat) (n : Nat) (hn : Eq Bool (lte k n) true) is
      -- rseq (raddP (constRPair a) (constRPair b)) n ~> qadd a b;
      -- rseq (constRPair (qadd a b)) n ~> qadd a b.  Difference (a+b) − (a+b) = 0.
      constDiffBound (qadd a b) k
    end
  end
end

qToRHom : (a : Q) -> (b : Q)
   -> Eq R (radd (qToR a) (qToR b)) (qToR (qadd a b)) is
  fn (a : Q) (b : Q) is
    qsound RPair RRel (raddP (constRPair a) (constRPair b)) (constRPair (qadd a b))
      (qToRHomP a b)
  end
end


-- ============================================================================
-- CHAPTER 124 — ℝ ORDER + ADDITIVE INVERSE.
-- Everything above is the ch121 construction + ch122 arithmetic (radd, qabsTriangle,
-- qToleranceSplit, the ℚ ordered field), redeclared verbatim.  Below is the NEW layer.
-- All definitions precede their use (Rune resolves names in source order).
-- ============================================================================

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- ℤ then ℚ NEGATION IS INVOLUTIVE:  −(−x) = x.
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
zNegNeg : (x : Z) -> Eq Z (zneg (zneg x)) x is
  fn (x : Z) is
    qind NatPair ZRel (fn (w : Z) is Eq Z (zneg (zneg w)) w end)
      (fn (p : NatPair) is
        -- pneg (pneg p) ~ p; ZRel obligation add (fst p)(snd p) = add (fst p)(snd p) — refl.
        qsound NatPair ZRel (pneg (pneg p)) p
          (refl (add (fst p) (snd p)))
      end)
      x
  end
end

qnegNegP : (p : QPair) -> QRel (qnegP (qnegP p)) p is
  fn (p : QPair) is
    -- Goal: zmul (zneg (zneg (qnum p))) (zden p) = zmul (qnum p) (zden (qnegP (qnegP p))).
    cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul s (zden p) end) (zNegNeg (qnum p))
  end
end

qnegNeg : (x : Q) -> Eq Q (qneg (qneg x)) x is
  fn (x : Q) is
    qind QPair QRel (fn (w : Q) is Eq Q (qneg (qneg w)) w end)
      (fn (p : QPair) is
        qsound QPair QRel (qnegP (qnegP p)) p (qnegNegP p)
      end)
      x
  end
end

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- |·| IS SIGN-SYMMETRIC:  |−q| = |q|.
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
qabsNegLE : (q : Q) -> Eq Bool (qle (qabs (qneg q)) (qabs q)) true is
  fn (q : Q) is
    qabsLUB (qneg q) (qabs q)
      (qabsUB2 q)
      (subst Q q (qneg (qneg q)) (sym (qnegNeg q))
        (fn (lhs : Q) is Eq Bool (qle lhs (qabs q)) true end)
        (qabsUB1 q))
  end
end

qabsNegGE : (q : Q) -> Eq Bool (qle (qabs q) (qabs (qneg q))) true is
  fn (q : Q) is
    subst Q (qneg (qneg q)) q (qnegNeg q)
      (fn (s : Q) is Eq Bool (qle (qabs s) (qabs (qneg q))) true end)
      (qabsNegLE (qneg q))
  end
end

qabsNeg : (q : Q) -> Eq Q (qabs (qneg q)) (qabs q) is
  fn (q : Q) is
    qleAntisym (qabs (qneg q)) (qabs q) (qabsNegLE q) (qabsNegGE q)
  end
end

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- SUBTRACTION / ABS SIGN LAWS.
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

-- qsub (qneg a) (qneg b) = qneg (qsub a b).  qsub (qneg a)(qneg b) is definitionally
-- qadd (qneg a)(qneg (qneg b)); qnegAdd a (qneg b) equates qneg (qadd a (qneg b)) to that.
qnegSubDist : (a : Q) -> (b : Q)
   -> Eq Q (qsub (qneg a) (qneg b)) (qneg (qsub a b)) is
  fn (a : Q) (b : Q) is
    sym (qnegAdd a (qneg b))
  end
end

-- |qsub (qneg a) (qneg b)| = |qsub a b|  — the negated difference has equal abs.
qabsNegSub : (a : Q) -> (b : Q)
   -> Eq Q (qabs (qsub (qneg a) (qneg b))) (qabs (qsub a b)) is
  fn (a : Q) (b : Q) is
    trans (cong (fn (s : Q) is qabs s end) (qnegSubDist a b))
      (qabsNeg (qsub a b))
  end
end

-- qneg (qsub a b) = qsub b a.
qnegSubSwap : (a : Q) -> (b : Q) -> Eq Q (qneg (qsub a b)) (qsub b a) is
  fn (a : Q) (b : Q) is
    trans (qnegAdd a (qneg b))
      (trans (cong (fn (s : Q) is qadd (qneg a) s end) (qnegNeg b))
        (qaddComm (qneg a) b))
  end
end

-- |a − b| = |b − a|.
qabsSubSym : (a : Q) -> (b : Q) -> Eq Q (qabs (qsub a b)) (qabs (qsub b a)) is
  fn (a : Q) (b : Q) is
    subst Q (qneg (qsub a b)) (qsub b a) (qnegSubSwap a b)
      (fn (s : Q) is Eq Q (qabs (qsub a b)) (qabs s) end)
      (sym (qabsNeg (qsub a b)))
  end
end

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- ℚ ADDITIVE-INVERSE / TOLERANCE HELPERS for the order.
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

-- (−b) + b = 0.
qAddNegL : (b : Q) -> Eq Q (qadd (qneg b) b) qzero is
  fn (b : Q) is
    trans (qaddComm (qneg b) b) (qAddNegR b)
  end
end

-- qadd (qsub a b) b = a.   (a + (−b)) + b = a + ((−b)+b) = a + 0 = a.
qsubAddBack : (a : Q) -> (b : Q) -> Eq Q (qadd (qsub a b) b) a is
  fn (a : Q) (b : Q) is
    trans (qaddAssoc a (qneg b) b)
      (trans
        (cong (fn (s : Q) is qadd a s end) (qAddNegL b))
        (qaddZero a))
  end
end

-- |a − b| ≤ t  ⇒  a ≤ b + t.
qleFromAbsSub : (a : Q) -> (b : Q) -> (t : Q)
   -> Eq Bool (qle (qabs (qsub a b)) t) true
   -> Eq Bool (qle a (qadd b t)) true is
  fn (a : Q) (b : Q) (t : Q) (h : Eq Bool (qle (qabs (qsub a b)) t) true) is
    subst Q (qadd (qsub a b) b) a (qsubAddBack a b)
      (fn (lhs : Q) is Eq Bool (qle lhs (qadd b t)) true end)
      (subst Q (qadd t b) (qadd b t) (qaddComm t b)
        (fn (rhs : Q) is Eq Bool (qle (qadd (qsub a b) b) rhs) true end)
        (qaddMono (qsub a b) t b
          (qleTrans (qsub a b) (qabs (qsub a b)) t (qabsUB1 (qsub a b)) h)))
  end
end

-- b ≤ b + 1/(k+1).
qleAddPosR : (b : Q) -> (k : Nat) -> Eq Bool (qle b (qadd b (qFromMod k))) true is
  fn (b : Q) (k : Nat) is
    subst Q (qadd qzero b) b (qaddZeroL b)
      (fn (lhs : Q) is Eq Bool (qle lhs (qadd b (qFromMod k))) true end)
      (subst Q (qadd (qFromMod k) b) (qadd b (qFromMod k)) (qaddComm (qFromMod k) b)
        (fn (rhs : Q) is Eq Bool (qle (qadd qzero b) rhs) true end)
        (qaddMono qzero (qFromMod k) b (qZeroLeMod k)))
  end
end

-- ============================================================================
-- THE ℝ ADDITIVE INVERSE  rneg : R -> R  (pointwise qneg).
-- ============================================================================

negSeq : (Nat -> Q) -> (Nat -> Q) is
  fn (f : Nat -> Q) is fn (i : Nat) is qneg (f i) end end
end

-- |(−f m) − (−f n)| ≤ 1/(k+1) from |f m − f n| ≤ 1/(k+1) — SAME modulus, qabsNegSub.
negSeqBound : (f : Nat -> Q) -> (m : Nat) -> (n : Nat) -> (k : Nat)
   -> Eq Bool (qle (qabs (qsub (f m) (f n))) (qFromMod k)) true
   -> Eq Bool (qle (qabs (qsub (negSeq f m) (negSeq f n))) (qFromMod k)) true is
  fn (f : Nat -> Q) (m : Nat) (n : Nat) (k : Nat)
     (h : Eq Bool (qle (qabs (qsub (f m) (f n))) (qFromMod k)) true) is
    -- negSeq f i ~> qneg (f i); rewrite |qsub (qneg fm)(qneg fn)| -> |qsub fm fn| (qabsNegSub).
    subst Q (qabs (qsub (f m) (f n))) (qabs (qsub (qneg (f m)) (qneg (f n))))
      (sym (qabsNegSub (f m) (f n)))
      (fn (e : Q) is Eq Bool (qle e (qFromMod k)) true end)
      h
  end
end

negSeqCauchyMod : (f : Nat -> Q) -> (N : Nat -> Nat)
   -> cauchyMod f N -> cauchyMod (negSeq f) N is
  fn (f : Nat -> Q) (N : Nat -> Nat) (cf : cauchyMod f N) is
    fn (k : Nat) (m : Nat) (n : Nat)
       (hm : Eq Bool (lte (N k) m) true) (hn : Eq Bool (lte (N k) n) true) is
      negSeqBound f m n k (cf k m n hm hn)
    end
  end
end

negSeqCauchy : (f : Nat -> Q) -> isCauchy f -> isCauchy (negSeq f) is
  fn (f : Nat -> Q) (cf : isCauchy f) is
    Pair (Nat -> Nat) (fn (N : Nat -> Nat) is cauchyMod (negSeq f) N end)
      (Fst cf)
      (negSeqCauchyMod f (Fst cf) (Snd cf))
  end
end

rnegP : RPair -> RPair is
  fn (x : RPair) is
    Pair (Nat -> Q) (fn (f : Nat -> Q) is isCauchy f end)
      (negSeq (rseq x))
      (negSeqCauchy (rseq x) (Snd x))
  end
end

-- RRel-respect: the negated difference has equal abs, so the null-diff bound passes through.
rnegRespects : (x : RPair) -> (x' : RPair) -> RRel x x' -> RRel (rnegP x) (rnegP x') is
  fn (x : RPair) (x' : RPair) (h : RRel x x') is
    fn (k : Nat) (n : Nat) (hn : Eq Bool (lte k n) true) is
      -- rseq (rnegP x) n ~> qneg (rseq x n); rewrite |qsub (qneg rx)(qneg rx')| -> |qsub rx rx'|.
      subst Q (qabs (qsub (rseq x n) (rseq x' n)))
              (qabs (qsub (qneg (rseq x n)) (qneg (rseq x' n))))
        (sym (qabsNegSub (rseq x n) (rseq x' n)))
        (fn (e : Q) is Eq Bool (qle e (qFromMod k)) true end)
        (h k n hn)
    end
  end
end

rneg : R -> R is
  qlift RPair RRel R
    (fn (x : RPair) is qin RPair RRel (rnegP x) end)
    (fn (x : RPair) (x' : RPair) (r : RRel x x') is
      qsound RPair RRel (rnegP x) (rnegP x') (rnegRespects x x' r)
    end)
end

rzero : R is qToR qzero end

rsub : R -> R -> R is
  fn (x : R) (y : R) is radd x (rneg y) end
end

-- THE ADDITIVE INVERSE LAW  rsub x x = rzero.
raddNegSelfP : (x : RPair) -> RRel (raddP x (rnegP x)) (constRPair qzero) is
  fn (x : RPair) is
    fn (k : Nat) (n : Nat) (hn : Eq Bool (lte k n) true) is
      -- rseq (raddP x (rnegP x)) n ~> qadd (rseq x n)(qneg (rseq x n)); rewrite to qzero (qAddNegR),
      -- rseq (constRPair qzero) n ~> qzero, leaving |qzero − qzero| ≤ 1/(k+1) — constDiffBound.
      subst Q qzero (qadd (rseq x n) (qneg (rseq x n))) (sym (qAddNegR (rseq x n)))
        (fn (d : Q) is Eq Bool (qle (qabs (qsub d qzero)) (qFromMod k)) true end)
        (constDiffBound qzero k)
    end
  end
end

raddNegSelf : (x : R) -> Eq R (radd x (rneg x)) rzero is
  fn (x : R) is
    qind RPair RRel (fn (w : R) is Eq R (radd w (rneg w)) rzero end)
      (fn (p : RPair) is
        qsound RPair RRel (raddP p (rnegP p)) (constRPair qzero) (raddNegSelfP p)
      end)
      x
  end
end

rsubSelf : (x : R) -> Eq R (rsub x x) rzero is
  fn (x : R) is raddNegSelf x end
end

-- ============================================================================
-- THE ORDER ON ℝ (representative level).  rleP x y — "x eventually ≤ y up to every
-- tolerance": ∀k, ∀ n ≥ k, rseq x n ≤ rseq y n + 1/(k+1).  Index-as-its-own-modulus,
-- kept a Prop in U0 (the RRel continuation form, NO Sigma).
-- ============================================================================
rleP : RPair -> RPair -> Prop is
  fn (x : RPair) (y : RPair) is
    (k : Nat) -> (n : Nat) -> Eq Bool (lte k n) true
      -> Eq Bool (qle (rseq x n) (qadd (rseq y n) (qFromMod k))) true
  end
end

-- REFLEXIVITY.
rleReflP : (x : RPair) -> rleP x x is
  fn (x : RPair) is
    fn (k : Nat) (n : Nat) (hn : Eq Bool (lte k n) true) is
      qleAddPosR (rseq x n) k
    end
  end
end

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- TOLERANCE / Nat MONOTONICITY for the doubled-step (dmod k) chaining.
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

-- n ≤ succ n.
lteSuccWeaken : (n : Nat) -> Eq Bool (lte n (succ n)) true is
  fn (n : Nat) is
    NatElim (fn (x : Nat) is Eq Bool (lte x (succ x)) true end)
      (refl true)
      (fn (j : Nat) (ih : Eq Bool (lte j (succ j)) true) is ih end)
      n
  end
end

-- k ≤ k + k.   lteAddBothR k zero k (lte zero k = refl true) : lte (add zero k)(add k k);
-- add zero k ~> k definitionally.
lteAddSelfR : (k : Nat) -> Eq Bool (lte k (add k k)) true is
  fn (k : Nat) is
    lteAddBothR k zero k (refl true)
  end
end

-- k ≤ dmod k  (dmod k = 2k+1).
lteDmod : (k : Nat) -> Eq Bool (lte k (dmod k)) true is
  fn (k : Nat) is
    subst Nat (succ (add k k)) (dmod k)
      (cong (fn (s : Nat) is succ s end) (sym (mulTwoL k)))
      (fn (d : Nat) is Eq Bool (lte k d) true end)
      (lteTrans k (add k k) (succ (add k k))
        (lteAddSelfR k)
        (lteSuccWeaken (add k k)))
  end
end

-- COMBINE:  ry ≤ ry2 + 1/(dmod k+1)  ⇒  ry + 1/(dmod k+1) ≤ ry2 + 1/(k+1).
rleRespCombineR : (ry : Q) -> (ry2 : Q) -> (k : Nat)
   -> Eq Bool (qle ry (qadd ry2 (qFromMod (dmod k)))) true
   -> Eq Bool (qle (qadd ry (qFromMod (dmod k))) (qadd ry2 (qFromMod k))) true is
  fn (ry : Q) (ry2 : Q) (k : Nat)
     (h : Eq Bool (qle ry (qadd ry2 (qFromMod (dmod k)))) true) is
    subst Q (qadd ry2 (qadd (qFromMod (dmod k)) (qFromMod (dmod k)))) (qadd ry2 (qFromMod k))
      (cong (fn (s : Q) is qadd ry2 s end) (qToleranceSplitEq k))
      (fn (rhs : Q) is Eq Bool (qle (qadd ry (qFromMod (dmod k))) rhs) true end)
      (subst Q (qadd (qadd ry2 (qFromMod (dmod k))) (qFromMod (dmod k)))
               (qadd ry2 (qadd (qFromMod (dmod k)) (qFromMod (dmod k))))
        (qaddAssoc ry2 (qFromMod (dmod k)) (qFromMod (dmod k)))
        (fn (rhs : Q) is Eq Bool (qle (qadd ry (qFromMod (dmod k))) rhs) true end)
        (qaddMono ry (qadd ry2 (qFromMod (dmod k))) (qFromMod (dmod k)) h))
  end
end

-- TRANSITIVITY at the DOUBLED step (the form that closes without the index wall).
-- From  rleP x y  and  rleP y z  evaluated at step (dmod k) — i.e. n ≥ dmod k for both —
-- the two half-tolerances 1/(dmod k+1) sum to 1/(k+1) (qToleranceSplitEq via rleRespCombineR),
-- giving  rseq x n ≤ rseq z n + 1/(k+1)  at every n ≥ dmod k.  This is the genuine transitive
-- content; the index discipline (n ≥ dmod k rather than n ≥ k) is exactly why the GLOBAL
-- packaged rle needs the existential-modulus / propext form (see the closing note).
rleTransAtP : (x : RPair) -> (y : RPair) -> (z : RPair)
   -> rleP x y -> rleP y z
   -> (k : Nat) -> (n : Nat) -> Eq Bool (lte (dmod k) n) true
   -> Eq Bool (qle (rseq x n) (qadd (rseq z n) (qFromMod k))) true is
  fn (x : RPair) (y : RPair) (z : RPair) (hxy : rleP x y) (hyz : rleP y z) is
    fn (k : Nat) (n : Nat) (hn : Eq Bool (lte (dmod k) n) true) is
      qleTrans (rseq x n)
        (qadd (rseq y n) (qFromMod (dmod k)))
        (qadd (rseq z n) (qFromMod k))
        (hxy (dmod k) n hn)
        (rleRespCombineR (rseq y n) (rseq z n) k
          (hyz (dmod k) n hn))
    end
  end
end

-- RRel-RESPECT of rleP at the DOUBLED step — the well-definedness certificate.
-- RRel y y' (at step dmod k, index n ≥ dmod k) gives ry n ≤ ry' n + 1/(dmod k+1) (qleFromAbsSub);
-- combined with rleP x y at step dmod k it yields rx n ≤ ry' n + 1/(k+1), for n ≥ dmod k.
rleRespRAtP : (x : RPair) -> (y : RPair) -> (y' : RPair)
   -> RRel y y' -> rleP x y
   -> (k : Nat) -> (n : Nat) -> Eq Bool (lte (dmod k) n) true
   -> Eq Bool (qle (rseq x n) (qadd (rseq y' n) (qFromMod k))) true is
  fn (x : RPair) (y : RPair) (y' : RPair) (hyy : RRel y y') (hxy : rleP x y) is
    fn (k : Nat) (n : Nat) (hn : Eq Bool (lte (dmod k) n) true) is
      qleTrans (rseq x n)
        (qadd (rseq y n) (qFromMod (dmod k)))
        (qadd (rseq y' n) (qFromMod k))
        (hxy (dmod k) n hn)
        (rleRespCombineR (rseq y n) (rseq y' n) k
          (qleFromAbsSub (rseq y n) (rseq y' n) (qFromMod (dmod k))
            (hyy (dmod k) n hn)))
    end
  end
end

rleRespLAtP : (x : RPair) -> (x' : RPair) -> (y : RPair)
   -> RRel x x' -> rleP x y
   -> (k : Nat) -> (n : Nat) -> Eq Bool (lte (dmod k) n) true
   -> Eq Bool (qle (rseq x' n) (qadd (rseq y n) (qFromMod k))) true is
  fn (x : RPair) (x' : RPair) (y : RPair) (hxx : RRel x x') (hxy : rleP x y) is
    fn (k : Nat) (n : Nat) (hn : Eq Bool (lte (dmod k) n) true) is
      qleTrans (rseq x' n)
        (qadd (rseq x n) (qFromMod (dmod k)))
        (qadd (rseq y n) (qFromMod k))
        -- rx' n ≤ rx n + 1/(dmod k+1):  |rx' n − rx n| = |rx n − rx' n| ≤ 1/(dmod k+1) (hxx).
        (qleFromAbsSub (rseq x' n) (rseq x n) (qFromMod (dmod k))
          (subst Q (qabs (qsub (rseq x n) (rseq x' n))) (qabs (qsub (rseq x' n) (rseq x n)))
            (qabsSubSym (rseq x n) (rseq x' n))
            (fn (e : Q) is Eq Bool (qle e (qFromMod (dmod k))) true end)
            (hxx (dmod k) n hn)))
        (rleRespCombineR (rseq x n) (rseq y n) k
          (hxy (dmod k) n hn))
    end
  end
end

-- THE EMBEDDING ℚ ↪ ℝ IS ORDER-PRESERVING.
qToRMonoP : (a : Q) -> (b : Q)
   -> Eq Bool (qle a b) true -> rleP (constRPair a) (constRPair b) is
  fn (a : Q) (b : Q) (h : Eq Bool (qle a b) true) is
    fn (k : Nat) (n : Nat) (hn : Eq Bool (lte k n) true) is
      qleTrans a b (qadd b (qFromMod k)) h (qleAddPosR b k)
    end
  end
end

-- ============================================================================
-- SANITY: the order + additive inverse land and compute through the quotient.
-- ============================================================================

rNegHalf : R is rneg (qToR qOneHalf) end

rSubHalfSelf : Eq R (rsub (qToR qOneHalf) (qToR qOneHalf)) rzero is
  rsubSelf (qToR qOneHalf)
end

rleHalfTwoThirdsP : rleP (constRPair qOneHalf) (constRPair qTwoThirds) is
  qToRMonoP qOneHalf qTwoThirds (refl true)
end

rleHalfReflP : rleP (constRPair qOneHalf) (constRPair qOneHalf) is
  rleReflP (constRPair qOneHalf)
end

-- ============================================================================
-- CHAPTER 124 — WHAT LANDED, AND THE NEXT STDLIB STEP.
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- FULLY PROVEN (no admits/holes/postulates), advancing ℝ toward an ORDERED FIELD:
--   • the ℝ ADDITIVE INVERSE: rneg : R -> R (pointwise qneg, Cauchy at the SAME modulus
--     via negSeqBound, RRel-respecting via rnegRespects — the negated difference has equal
--     absolute value), rzero = qToR qzero, rsub x y = radd x (rneg y), and the LAW
--     rsubSelf : rsub x x = rzero (raddNegSelf: pointwise b + (−b) = 0, bounded by
--     constDiffBound, lifted through qind).  The additive-group structure of ℝ.
--   • supporting ℚ analysis: qnegNeg (negation involution, via zNegNeg), qabsNeg (|−q|=|q|,
--     via qabsLUB + qleAntisym), qnegSubDist / qabsNegSub / qnegSubSwap / qabsSubSym (the
--     subtraction/abs sign laws), qleFromAbsSub (|a−b| ≤ t ⇒ a ≤ b + t), qsubAddBack,
--     qAddNegL, qleAddPosR.
--   • the ORDER rleP : RPair -> RPair -> Prop — "eventually ≤ up to every tolerance",
--     index-as-its-own-modulus, in Prop/U0 (the RRel continuation form, NO Sigma).
--     REFLEXIVE (rleReflP), and — at the DOUBLED tolerance step dmod k = 2k+1 — TRANSITIVE
--     (rleTransAtP) and RRel-RESPECTING in both arguments (rleRespRAtP/rleRespLAtP), each via
--     the dmod-step chain + rleRespCombineR + qToleranceSplitEq (the two half-tolerances
--     1/(2k+2) summing to 1/(k+1)).  qToRMonoP — ℚ ↪ ℝ is ORDER-PRESERVING.
--   • sanity: rsub (qToR 1/2)(qToR 1/2) = rzero; order-preserving on 1/2 ≤ 2/3; rleP refl.
--
-- WHY rleP is at the REPRESENTATIVE level, and why trans/respect carry the DOUBLED step
-- (the index-discipline + universe/propext note):
--   (1) The relation is "∀ n ≥ k, rx n ≤ ry n + 1/(k+1)".  Chaining two such (transitivity)
--       or absorbing a null-difference (respect) sums two tolerances; to keep the SUM at
--       1/(k+1) the pieces must be taken at the half-tolerance step dmod k = 2k+1, which
--       needs n ≥ dmod k — STRICTLY stronger than the given n ≥ k.  So rleTransAtP /
--       rleRespRAtP / rleRespLAtP are stated honestly at the doubled step (witness
--       lte (dmod k) n); the conclusion at the ORIGINAL step k for all n ≥ k is exactly the
--       content that requires an EXISTENTIAL modulus (∃N ∀n≥N), a Sigma that bumps the
--       relation out of Prop into U — the genuine obstruction, not a missing lemma.
--   (2) Packaging the order as a standalone  rle : R -> R -> Prop  by lifting rleP through
--       the quotient also requires the respect obligation Eq Prop (rleP x y)(rleP x y').  The
--       relations are logically equivalent (rleRespRAtP/rleRespLAtP) but NOT convertible, and
--       this kernel has proof-irrelevant Prop with UIP, NOT propositional extensionality
--       (Eq Prop from a biimplication is not derivable: `refl A : Eq Prop A B` fails to unify;
--       cong cannot bridge two non-convertible sequences).
--   So rleP + reflexivity + the doubled-step transitivity/respect + order-preservation are the
--   complete machine-checked order content reachable in Prop/U0; the packaged rle is one
--   existential-modulus-or-propext step away.
--
-- THE NEXT STDLIB STEP (precise):
--   • rle : R -> R -> Prop — either (a) reformulate rleP with an EXISTENTIAL modulus
--     (∃N ∀n≥N …, a Sigma, accepting the U0→U1 bump and lifting rle to U not Prop), which
--     makes transitivity/respect close at the original step k; or (b) add propositional
--     extensionality (Eq Prop A B from (A->B) and (B->A)) to the equality stratum and lift
--     rleP through the quotient, the doubled-step respect lemmas supplying the implications.
--     Then rleRefl/rleTrans/qToRMono lift from rleReflP/rleTransAtP/qToRMonoP.
--   • rleAntisymP / rleAddMonoP — the remaining ordered-field compatibility, rep-level and
--     propext-free.
--   • rmul : R -> R -> R — pointwise qmul, needing a BOUNDEDNESS lemma (a Cauchy sequence is
--     bounded, so the product modulus rescales by the bound) — completing the ORDERED FIELD ℝ.


-- ============================================================================
-- CHAPTER 126 — ℝ ORDERED-FIELD COMPATIBILITY: rleAddMonoP + rleAntisymP, and
-- the FIRST rmul BOUNDEDNESS substrate (telos-3 / M6 / D3).
-- Everything above is the ch121/122/124 construction (the Cauchy reals: radd, rneg,
-- the order rleP, the ℚ ordered field), redeclared verbatim.  Below is the NEW layer,
-- FULLY PROVEN (no admits/holes/postulates):
--   • rleAddMonoP : rleP x y  ⇒  rleP (raddP x z) (raddP y z) — the order RESPECTS
--     addition (rep-level, at the ORIGINAL step k — addition monotonicity is EXACT, no
--     tolerance doubling).  The "+ is order-compatible" axiom of an ordered field.
--   • rleAntisymP : rleP x y  ⇒  rleP y x  ⇒  RRel x y — ANTISYMMETRY collapses the
--     two-sided order into the null-difference equivalence (x ∼ y), rep-level and
--     propext-free (no Eq Prop needed — RRel is the Bool-valued tolerance bound).
--   • seqTailBound — the TAIL HALF of "a Cauchy sequence is bounded": for n ≥ N 0,
--     |f n| ≤ |f (N 0)| + 1/(0+1).  The first rmul substrate (rmul rescales the product
--     modulus by such a bound); the remaining finite-prefix max is the documented next step.
-- All new definitions precede their use (Rune resolves names in source order).
-- ============================================================================

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- (a + t) + c = (a + c) + t — move a summand past the tolerance.  Pure
-- commutative-monoid rearrangement (qaddAssoc + qaddComm).
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
qaddSwapTol : (a : Q) -> (c : Q) -> (t : Q)
   -> Eq Q (qadd (qadd a t) c) (qadd (qadd a c) t) is
  fn (a : Q) (c : Q) (t : Q) is
    trans (qaddAssoc a t c)
      (trans (cong (fn (s : Q) is qadd a s end) (qaddComm t c))
        (sym (qaddAssoc a c t)))
  end
end

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- rleAddMonoP : the order on ℝ respects addition on the RIGHT.  At each index n ≥ k,
-- rx n ≤ ry n + 1/(k+1) (hypothesis) gives, adding rz n to both sides (qaddMono) and
-- moving the tolerance past rz n (qaddSwapTol), (rx n + rz n) ≤ (ry n + rz n) + 1/(k+1).
-- rseq (raddP x z) n ~> qadd (rseq x n) (rseq z n) definitionally, so this IS the goal.
-- No tolerance doubling — monotone addition is exact, so the bound holds at step k.
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
rleAddMonoP : (x : RPair) -> (y : RPair) -> (z : RPair)
   -> rleP x y -> rleP (raddP x z) (raddP y z) is
  fn (x : RPair) (y : RPair) (z : RPair) (h : rleP x y) is
    fn (k : Nat) (n : Nat) (hn : Eq Bool (lte k n) true) is
      -- goal: qle (qadd (rx n)(rz n)) (qadd (qadd (ry n)(rz n)) (qFromMod k))
      subst Q
        (qadd (qadd (rseq y n) (qFromMod k)) (rseq z n))
        (qadd (qadd (rseq y n) (rseq z n)) (qFromMod k))
        (qaddSwapTol (rseq y n) (rseq z n) (qFromMod k))
        (fn (d : Q) is Eq Bool (qle (qadd (rseq x n) (rseq z n)) d) true end)
        (qaddMono (rseq x n) (qadd (rseq y n) (qFromMod k)) (rseq z n)
          (h k n hn))
    end
  end
end

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- (b + t) − b = t — cancel a summand against its negation (qaddSwapTol + qsubSelf).
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
qBPlusTMinusB : (b : Q) -> (t : Q)
   -> Eq Q (qadd (qadd b t) (qneg b)) t is
  fn (b : Q) (t : Q) is
    trans (qaddSwapTol b (qneg b) t)
      (trans (cong (fn (s : Q) is qadd s t end) (qsubSelf b))
        (qaddZeroL t))
  end
end

-- a ≤ b + t  ⇒  a − b ≤ t.  Add (−b) to both sides (qaddMono), then (b+t)−b = t
-- (qBPlusTMinusB).  The converse direction of qleFromAbsSub's add bound.
qleSubFromAdd : (a : Q) -> (b : Q) -> (t : Q)
   -> Eq Bool (qle a (qadd b t)) true
   -> Eq Bool (qle (qsub a b) t) true is
  fn (a : Q) (b : Q) (t : Q) (h : Eq Bool (qle a (qadd b t)) true) is
    subst Q (qadd (qadd b t) (qneg b)) t (qBPlusTMinusB b t)
      (fn (d : Q) is Eq Bool (qle (qadd a (qneg b)) d) true end)
      (qaddMono a (qadd b t) (qneg b) h)
  end
end

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- rleAntisymP : rleP x y AND rleP y x collapse to RRel x y (x ∼ y in ℝ).  At each
-- index n ≥ k the two one-sided bounds rx n ≤ ry n + 1/(k+1) and ry n ≤ rx n + 1/(k+1)
-- give rx n − ry n ≤ 1/(k+1) and −(rx n − ry n) = ry n − rx n ≤ 1/(k+1) (qleSubFromAdd
-- twice + qnegSubSwap), so |rx n − ry n| ≤ 1/(k+1) (qabsLUB).  Both bounds at the SAME
-- step k — antisymmetry needs no doubling.  Propext-free: RRel is a Bool tolerance bound.
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
rleAntisymP : (x : RPair) -> (y : RPair)
   -> rleP x y -> rleP y x -> RRel x y is
  fn (x : RPair) (y : RPair) (hxy : rleP x y) (hyx : rleP y x) is
    fn (k : Nat) (n : Nat) (hn : Eq Bool (lte k n) true) is
      -- goal: qle (qabs (qsub (rx n) (ry n))) (qFromMod k)
      qabsLUB (qsub (rseq x n) (rseq y n)) (qFromMod k)
        -- rx n − ry n ≤ 1/(k+1)
        (qleSubFromAdd (rseq x n) (rseq y n) (qFromMod k) (hxy k n hn))
        -- −(rx n − ry n) = ry n − rx n ≤ 1/(k+1)
        (subst Q (qsub (rseq y n) (rseq x n)) (qneg (qsub (rseq x n) (rseq y n)))
          (sym (qnegSubSwap (rseq x n) (rseq y n)))
          (fn (d : Q) is Eq Bool (qle d (qFromMod k)) true end)
          (qleSubFromAdd (rseq y n) (rseq x n) (qFromMod k) (hyx k n hn)))
    end
  end
end

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- rmul SUBSTRATE — the TAIL HALF of Cauchy boundedness.  For a Cauchy sequence f with
-- modulus N, every n ≥ N 0 sits within tolerance 1/(0+1) of the anchor f (N 0)
-- (the Cauchy bound at step 0, with m := N 0), so |f n| ≤ |f (N 0)| + 1/(0+1):
--   |f n| = |f (N 0) − (f (N 0) − f n)| ≤ |f (N 0)| + |f (N 0) − f n| ≤ |f (N 0)| + 1.
-- The chain: qabsSubBack rewrites f n as (f (N 0)) − ((f (N 0)) − f n); qabsTriangle splits;
-- qaddMono absorbs the Cauchy bound on the tail term.  This is the ANCHOR bound; the FULL
-- boundedness lemma maxes it against the finite prefix f 0 … f (N 0 − 1) (a Nat recursion,
-- the documented next step) to get a single bound valid at ALL n.
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

-- f n = (f (N 0)) − ((f (N 0)) − f n) — recover a value from an anchor + the difference.
-- (a) − (a − b) = b:  qsub a (qsub a b) = qadd a (qneg (qadd a (qneg b))); qnegAdd +
-- qnegNeg fold it to (−a) + b, then qadd a ((−a)+b) = b (qaddAssoc + qAddNegR + qaddZeroL).
qsubSubBack : (a : Q) -> (b : Q)
   -> Eq Q (qsub a (qsub a b)) b is
  fn (a : Q) (b : Q) is
    -- qsub a (qsub a b) = qadd a (qneg (qsub a b)); qneg (qsub a b) = qsub b a (qnegSubSwap)
    subst Q (qsub b a) (qneg (qsub a b)) (sym (qnegSubSwap a b))
      (fn (s : Q) is Eq Q (qadd a s) b end)
      -- qadd a (qsub b a) = qadd a (qadd b (qneg a)) = b:  swap to (a + (−a)) + b
      (trans (cong (fn (s : Q) is qadd a s end) (qaddComm b (qneg a)))
        (trans (sym (qaddAssoc a (qneg a) b))
          (trans (cong (fn (s : Q) is qadd s b end) (qAddNegR a))
            (qaddZeroL b))))
  end
end

-- THE ANCHOR BOUND.  |f n| ≤ |f (N 0)| + 1/(0+1) for every n ≥ N 0, given f Cauchy at N.
seqTailBound : (f : Nat -> Q) -> (N : Nat -> Nat) -> cauchyMod f N
   -> (n : Nat) -> Eq Bool (lte (N zero) n) true
   -> Eq Bool (qle (qabs (f n)) (qadd (qabs (f (N zero))) (qFromMod zero))) true is
  fn (f : Nat -> Q) (N : Nat -> Nat) (cf : cauchyMod f N)
     (n : Nat) (hn : Eq Bool (lte (N zero) n) true) is
    -- rewrite |f n| as |a − (a − b)| with a = f (N 0), b = f n (qsubSubBack), then
    -- triangle + the Cauchy tail bound |a − b| ≤ 1/(0+1).
    subst Q (qsub (f (N zero)) (qsub (f (N zero)) (f n))) (f n)
      (qsubSubBack (f (N zero)) (f n))
      (fn (v : Q) is
         Eq Bool (qle (qabs v) (qadd (qabs (f (N zero))) (qFromMod zero))) true end)
      (qleTrans
        (qabs (qsub (f (N zero)) (qsub (f (N zero)) (f n))))
        (qadd (qabs (f (N zero))) (qabs (qneg (qsub (f (N zero)) (f n)))))
        (qadd (qabs (f (N zero))) (qFromMod zero))
        (qabsTriangle (f (N zero)) (qneg (qsub (f (N zero)) (f n))))
        (qaddMono2
          (qabs (f (N zero))) (qabs (f (N zero)))
          (qabs (qneg (qsub (f (N zero)) (f n)))) (qFromMod zero)
          (qleRefl (qabs (f (N zero))))
          (subst Q (qabs (qsub (f (N zero)) (f n)))
                   (qabs (qneg (qsub (f (N zero)) (f n))))
            (sym (qabsNeg (qsub (f (N zero)) (f n))))
            (fn (v : Q) is Eq Bool (qle v (qFromMod zero)) true end)
            (cf zero (N zero) n (lteRefl (N zero)) hn))))
  end
end

-- ============================================================================
-- CHAPTER 126 — WHAT LANDED, AND THE NEXT STDLIB STEP.
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- FULLY PROVEN (no admits/holes/postulates), completing the ORDER half of the
-- ordered field ℝ and opening the rmul (multiplication) substrate:
--   • rleAddMonoP : rleP x y ⇒ rleP (raddP x z)(raddP y z) — "+ respects ≤", the
--     translation-invariance axiom of an ordered field, at the ORIGINAL step k
--     (monotone addition is EXACT — no tolerance doubling).  Via qaddMono on the
--     right + qaddSwapTol moving the tolerance past the shared summand.
--   • rleAntisymP : rleP x y ⇒ rleP y x ⇒ RRel x y — ANTISYMMETRY: the two-sided
--     order collapses to the null-difference equivalence (x ∼ y in ℝ).  Both bounds
--     at the SAME step k (antisymmetry needs no doubling); qleSubFromAdd extracts
--     a − b ≤ t and b − a ≤ t, qnegSubSwap identifies −(a−b) = b−a, qabsLUB packs
--     them to |a − b| ≤ t.  PROPEXT-FREE — RRel is the Bool-valued tolerance bound,
--     so no Eq Prop obligation arises (unlike the packaged rle, ch124 note).
--   • supporting ℚ algebra: qaddSwapTol ((a+t)+c = (a+c)+t), qBPlusTMinusB
--     ((b+t)−b = t), qleSubFromAdd (a ≤ b+t ⇒ a−b ≤ t), qsubSubBack (a−(a−b) = b).
--   • seqTailBound — the rmul SUBSTRATE: the TAIL HALF of "a Cauchy sequence is
--     bounded".  For n ≥ N 0, |f n| ≤ |f (N 0)| + 1/(0+1), via qsubSubBack +
--     qabsTriangle + the Cauchy bound at step 0 (anchor m := N 0).
--
-- So ℝ now has: an additive group (ch124), an order that is REFLEXIVE / doubled-step
-- TRANSITIVE (ch124) / TRANSLATION-INVARIANT (rleAddMonoP) / ANTISYMMETRIC into ∼
-- (rleAntisymP), and ℚ↪ℝ order-preserving (ch124).  The order-theoretic content of an
-- ordered field is machine-checked and propext-free; only the PACKAGED rle (ch124
-- existential-modulus/propext remainder) and MULTIPLICATION remain.
--
-- THE NEXT STDLIB STEP (precise):
--   • the FULL boundedness lemma — max the seqTailBound anchor against the FINITE PREFIX
--     f 0 … f (N 0 − 1).  A Nat recursion `seqMaxPrefix : (f)(m) -> Q` ( = max |f 0| …
--     |f m|, by NatElim) + its dominance `i ≤ m ⇒ |f i| ≤ seqMaxPrefix f m`, then
--     `seqBound f = max (seqMaxPrefix f (N 0)) (|f (N 0)| + 1)` bounds |f n| at ALL n
--     (split on n < N 0 vs n ≥ N 0 by lteTotal).  This is the only missing piece.
--   • qabsMul : |a·b| = |a|·|b| (sign-case analysis via qabs's BoolElim + the qmul
--     sign laws qmulNegL/qmulNegR) — so the product modulus rescales by the bound.
--   • rmul : R -> R -> R — pointwise qmul; mulSeqBound uses |fx m fy m − fx n fy n| ≤
--     B(|fx m − fx n| + |fy m − fy n|) (the bound B = max of the two seqBounds), modulus
--     rescaled by B (mulMod k = max moduli at a B-scaled step) — completing the FIELD ℝ.
-- ============================================================================


-- ============================================================================
-- CHAPTER 127 — ℝ MULTIPLICATION SUBSTRATE: the ℚ sign + product-difference
-- algebra that rmul consumes (telos-3 / M6 / D3).
-- Everything above is the ch121/122/124/126 construction.  Below is the NEW layer,
-- FULLY PROVEN (no admits/holes/postulates) — the pure-ℚ multiplicative kernel of
-- the rmul (real multiplication) bound:
--   • qmulNegL / qmulNegR — multiplication pulls a negation out of either factor,
--     lifted from the ℤ facts zNegMulL/zNegMulR through the quotient (qnegP touches
--     only the numerator, qmulP multiplies numerators, so the rep obligation is a
--     single cong over zNegMulL).
--   • qmulZeroL — 0·a = 0 (lifted from zmulZeroL).
--   • qmulSubDist — the PRODUCT-DIFFERENCE REGROUP:  a·b − c·d = (a−c)·b + c·(b−d).
--     This is the identity at the heart of the rmul Cauchy bound: it splits the
--     product difference into one factor's difference times the other, so the
--     boundedness of each sequence (seqTailBound, ch126) rescales the modulus.
--     Built from qmulDistR + qmulNegR + a subtraction-telescope (qsubTelescope).
-- All new definitions precede their use (Rune resolves names in source order).
-- ============================================================================

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- (−a)·b = −(a·b) on REPRESENTATIVES, then lifted.  qnegP keeps the denominator index
-- and negates the numerator; qmulP multiplies numerators and adds denominator indices.
-- So qmulP (qnegP p) q and qnegP (qmulP p q) share the SAME denominator index, and their
-- numerators zmul (zneg (qnum p))(qnum q) vs zneg (zmul (qnum p)(qnum q)) agree by
-- zNegMulL — the QRel obligation is one cong over that.
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
qmulNegLP : (p : QPair) -> (q : QPair)
   -> QRel (qmulP (qnegP p) q) (qnegP (qmulP p q)) is
  fn (p : QPair) (q : QPair) is
    cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul s (zden (qnegP (qmulP p q))) end)
      (zNegMulL (qnum p) (qnum q))
  end
end

qmulNegL : (a : Q) -> (b : Q) -> Eq Q (qmul (qneg a) b) (qneg (qmul a b)) is
  fn (a : Q) is
    qind QPair QRel
      (fn (wa : Q) is (b : Q) -> Eq Q (qmul (qneg wa) b) (qneg (qmul wa b)) end)
      (fn (p : QPair) is
        fn (b : Q) is
          qind QPair QRel
            (fn (wb : Q) is
               Eq Q (qmul (qneg (qin QPair QRel p)) wb) (qneg (qmul (qin QPair QRel p) wb)) end)
            (fn (q : QPair) is
              qsound QPair QRel (qmulP (qnegP p) q) (qnegP (qmulP p q)) (qmulNegLP p q)
            end)
            b
        end
      end)
      a
  end
end

-- a·(−b) = −(a·b) — by commuting into qmulNegL.
qmulNegR : (a : Q) -> (b : Q) -> Eq Q (qmul a (qneg b)) (qneg (qmul a b)) is
  fn (a : Q) (b : Q) is
    trans (qmulComm a (qneg b))
      (trans (qmulNegL b a)
        (cong (fn (s : Q) is qneg s end) (qmulComm b a)))
  end
end

-- 0·a = 0 on reps:  qnum (qpair zzero zero) = zzero, so the product numerator is
-- zmul zzero (qnum q) = zzero (zmulZeroL); the QRel obligation closes both sides to
-- zzero via zmulZeroL on the numerator and on the cross denominator.
qmulZeroLP : (q : QPair) -> QRel (qmulP (qpair zzero zero) q) (qpair zzero zero) is
  fn (q : QPair) is
    trans
      (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul s (zden (qpair zzero zero)) end)
        (zmulZeroL (qnum q)))
      (trans (zmulZeroL (zden (qpair zzero zero)))
        (sym (zmulZeroL (zden (qmulP (qpair zzero zero) q)))))
  end
end

qmulZeroL : (a : Q) -> Eq Q (qmul qzero a) qzero is
  fn (a : Q) is
    qind QPair QRel (fn (w : Q) is Eq Q (qmul qzero w) qzero end)
      (fn (q : QPair) is
        qsound QPair QRel (qmulP (qpair zzero zero) q) (qpair zzero zero) (qmulZeroLP q)
      end)
      a
  end
end

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- THE PRODUCT-DIFFERENCE REGROUP:  a·b − c·d = (a−c)·b + c·(b−d).
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

-- (a−c)·b = a·b − c·b.  qsub a c = qadd a (qneg c); commute, distribute, pull the
-- negation out of the second product (qmulNegR), commute it to c·b.
qmulSubDistR : (a : Q) -> (c : Q) -> (b : Q)
   -> Eq Q (qmul (qsub a c) b) (qsub (qmul a b) (qmul c b)) is
  fn (a : Q) (c : Q) (b : Q) is
    trans (qmulComm (qsub a c) b)
      (trans (qmulDistR b a (qneg c))
        (trans (cong (fn (s : Q) is qadd s (qmul b (qneg c)) end) (qmulComm b a))
          (trans (cong (fn (s : Q) is qadd (qmul a b) s end) (qmulNegR b c))
            (cong (fn (s : Q) is qadd (qmul a b) (qneg s) end) (qmulComm b c)))))
  end
end

-- c·(b−d) = c·b − c·d.  Distribute over the subtraction, pull the negation out.
qmulSubDistL : (c : Q) -> (b : Q) -> (d : Q)
   -> Eq Q (qmul c (qsub b d)) (qsub (qmul c b) (qmul c d)) is
  fn (c : Q) (b : Q) (d : Q) is
    trans (qmulDistR c b (qneg d))
      (cong (fn (s : Q) is qadd (qmul c b) s end) (qmulNegR c d))
  end
end

-- TELESCOPE:  (X − Y) + (Y − Z) = X − Z.  Associate, cancel (−Y)+Y = 0 (qAddNegL).
qsubTelescope : (x : Q) -> (y : Q) -> (z : Q)
   -> Eq Q (qadd (qsub x y) (qsub y z)) (qsub x z) is
  fn (x : Q) (y : Q) (z : Q) is
    trans (qaddAssoc x (qneg y) (qsub y z))
      (trans (cong (fn (s : Q) is qadd x s end) (sym (qaddAssoc (qneg y) y (qneg z))))
        (trans (cong (fn (s : Q) is qadd x (qadd s (qneg z)) end) (qAddNegL y))
          (cong (fn (s : Q) is qadd x s end) (qaddZeroL (qneg z)))))
  end
end

-- a·b − c·d = (a−c)·b + c·(b−d).  Rewrite each summand on the right by qmulSubDistR/L
-- to (a·b − c·b) + (c·b − c·d), then telescope through the shared c·b.
qmulSubDist : (a : Q) -> (b : Q) -> (c : Q) -> (d : Q)
   -> Eq Q (qsub (qmul a b) (qmul c d))
           (qadd (qmul (qsub a c) b) (qmul c (qsub b d))) is
  fn (a : Q) (b : Q) (c : Q) (d : Q) is
    sym
      (trans
        (cong2 (fn (u : Q) (v : Q) is qadd u v end)
          (qmulSubDistR a c b) (qmulSubDistL c b d))
        (qsubTelescope (qmul a b) (qmul c b) (qmul c d)))
  end
end

-- ============================================================================
-- CHAPTER 127 — WHAT LANDED, AND THE rmul ASSEMBLY PLAN.
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- FULLY PROVEN (no admits/holes/postulates) — the ℚ multiplicative substrate rmul needs:
--   • qmulNegL : (−a)·b = −(a·b),  qmulNegR : a·(−b) = −(a·b)  (lifted from zNegMulL/R).
--   • qmulZeroL : 0·a = 0  (lifted from zmulZeroL).
--   • qmulSubDist : a·b − c·d = (a−c)·b + c·(b−d)  — the PRODUCT-DIFFERENCE REGROUP,
--     via qmulSubDistR ((a−c)·b = a·b−c·b), qmulSubDistL (c·(b−d) = c·b−c·d), and
--     qsubTelescope ((X−Y)+(Y−Z) = X−Z).
--
-- WHY THIS IS THE rmul KERNEL.  The product modulus bound is, for m,n ≥ the modulus,
--   |fx m·fy m − fx n·fy n|
--     = |(fx m − fx n)·fy m + fx n·(fy m − fy n)|        (qmulSubDist, with a=fx m,
--                                                          c=fx n, b=fy m, d=fy n)
--     ≤ |fx m − fx n|·|fy m| + |fx n|·|fy m − fy n|       (qabsTriangle + qabsMul)
--     ≤ Bx·|fx m − fx n| + By·|fy m − fy n|               (seqTailBound, ch126, gives
--                                                          |fy m| ≤ By, |fx n| ≤ Bx once
--                                                          the modulus is floored at N0).
-- qmulSubDist (this chapter) supplies line 1; seqTailBound (ch126) supplies the bound.
--
-- THE NEXT STDLIB STEP (precise) — TWO remaining pieces, then rmul assembles:
--   • qabsMul : |a·b| = |a|·|b| — the ℚ absolute-value product law (sign-case analysis
--     on qle a 0 / qle b 0 via BoolElim, using qmulNegL/qmulNegR from THIS chapter to
--     fold the four sign branches; needs qmulZeroL for the degenerate a=0/b=0 edges).
--   • THE ARCHIMEDEAN MODULUS RESCALE (the research crux): given a positive rational
--     bound B and a target step k, find a modulus index j with B·(1/(j+1)) ≤ 1/(k+1),
--     i.e. j+1 ≥ B·(k+1).  Since B = p/q (q ≥ 1), the choice j := p·(k+1) works
--     (j+1 > p·(k+1) ≥ (p/q)·(k+1) = B·(k+1)) — but it requires EXTRACTING B's numerator
--     p from its QPair rep (a qnum/qdenN read) and a ℚ-vs-Nat inequality
--     `qle B (qFromNat (p)) `-style bound.  This Nat-extraction-from-a-rational is the
--     one genuinely new construction; everything else (qmulSubDist, seqTailBound,
--     qabsTriangle, qaddMono2) is in hand.
--   • THEN rmul : R -> R -> R — mulSeq (pointwise qmul), mulMod k = max of the two
--     component moduli at the B-rescaled step AND N0 (the floor that activates
--     seqTailBound), mulSeqBound (the chain above), mulSeqCauchy, rmulP, the RRel-respect
--     pair (product difference cancels the shared factor + the bound), rmul through the
--     double qind — completing the ORDERED FIELD ℝ.
-- ============================================================================


-- ============================================================================
-- CHAPTER 128 — Nat CROSS-MULTIPLICATION MONOTONICITY: the root of the qmul-order
-- tower (the deepest prerequisite of qmulNonneg ▸ qabsMul ▸ rmul; telos-3 / M6 / D3).
-- Everything above is the ch121–127 construction.  Below is the NEW layer, FULLY
-- PROVEN (no admits/holes/postulates):
--   • lteSelfAddR : x ≤ x + m  (from lteAddBothR + addComm).
--   • lteToAdd : lte a b ⇒ Σ k, b = a + k  (the order-to-witness extraction, by double
--     NatElim; the zero case is absurd via lteAbsurdNat).
--   • crossEq : (a·(c+j) + (a+k)·c) + k·j = a·c + (a+k)·(c+j) — the cross-term identity
--     (a·d + b·c) + (b−a)(d−c) = a·c + b·d with b=a+k, d=c+j (a 5-monomial commutative-
--     monoid rearrangement via mulDistL/R + interchange + addAssoc/addComm).
--   • addMulCrossLe : a ≤ b ⇒ c ≤ d ⇒ a·d + b·c ≤ a·c + b·d — cross-multiplication
--     monotonicity, the Nat heart of "product of nonnegatives is nonnegative" in ℤ
--     (zmulNonneg, next) and thence qmulNonneg / qabsMul / rmul's modulus bound.
-- All new definitions precede their use (Rune resolves names in source order).
-- ============================================================================

-- x ≤ x + m.  lteAddBothR x zero m (lte zero m ~> true) : lte (add zero x)(add m x)
-- = lte x (add m x); rewrite add m x to add x m (addComm).
lteSelfAddR : (x : Nat) -> (m : Nat) -> Eq Bool (lte x (add x m)) true is
  fn (x : Nat) (m : Nat) is
    subst Nat (add m x) (add x m) (addComm m x)
      (fn (s : Nat) is Eq Bool (lte x s) true end)
      (lteAddBothR x zero m (refl true))
  end
end

-- lte a b ⇒ Σ k, b = a + k.  Double NatElim: outer on a, inner on b; the (succ a', 0)
-- case is absurd (lte (succ a') 0 ~> false), discharged by lteAbsurdNat.
lteToAdd : (a : Nat) -> (b : Nat) -> Eq Bool (lte a b) true
   -> Sig Nat (fn (k : Nat) is Eq Nat b (add a k) end) is
  fn (a : Nat) is
    NatElim
      (fn (x : Nat) is
         (b : Nat) -> Eq Bool (lte x b) true
           -> Sig Nat (fn (k : Nat) is Eq Nat b (add x k) end) end)
      -- a = 0: witness b, since add zero b ~> b.
      (fn (b : Nat) (h : Eq Bool (lte zero b) true) is
         Pair Nat (fn (k : Nat) is Eq Nat b (add zero k) end) b (refl b) end)
      (fn (a' : Nat)
          (ih : (b : Nat) -> Eq Bool (lte a' b) true
                  -> Sig Nat (fn (k : Nat) is Eq Nat b (add a' k) end)) is
         fn (b : Nat) is
           NatElim
             (fn (y : Nat) is
                Eq Bool (lte (succ a') y) true
                  -> Sig Nat (fn (k : Nat) is Eq Nat y (add (succ a') k) end) end)
             -- y = 0: lte (succ a') 0 ~> false; absurd.
             (fn (h : Eq Bool (lte (succ a') zero) true) is
                Pair Nat (fn (k : Nat) is Eq Nat zero (add (succ a') k) end)
                  zero (lteAbsurdNat zero (add (succ a') zero) h) end)
             -- y = succ b': lte (succ a')(succ b') ~> lte a' b' = h; use ih.
             (fn (b' : Nat)
                 (ihy : Eq Bool (lte (succ a') b') true
                          -> Sig Nat (fn (k : Nat) is Eq Nat b' (add (succ a') k) end)) is
                fn (h : Eq Bool (lte (succ a') (succ b')) true) is
                  Pair Nat (fn (k : Nat) is Eq Nat (succ b') (add (succ a') k) end)
                    (Fst (ih b' h))
                    (cong {Nat} {Nat} (fn (s : Nat) is succ s end)
                      {b'} {add a' (Fst (ih b' h))} (Snd (ih b' h)))
                end
              end)
             b
         end
       end)
      a
  end
end

-- THE CROSS-TERM IDENTITY (with b = a+k, d = c+j):
--   (a·(c+j) + (a+k)·c) + k·j = a·c + (a+k)·(c+j).
-- Both sides expand (mulDistL/R) to the 5-monomial bag {a·c, a·j, a·c, k·c, k·j};
-- reach the common left-nested normal form add(add(add(add ac aj) ac) kc) kj.
crossEq : (a : Nat) -> (k : Nat) -> (c : Nat) -> (j : Nat)
   -> Eq Nat
        (add (add (mul a (add c j)) (mul (add a k) c)) (mul k j))
        (add (mul a c) (mul (add a k) (add c j))) is
  fn (a : Nat) (k : Nat) (c : Nat) (j : Nat) is
    trans
      -- LHS -> NF
      (trans
        (cong (fn (s : Nat) is add (add s (mul (add a k) c)) (mul k j) end)
          (mulDistL a c j))
        (trans
          (cong (fn (s : Nat) is add (add (add (mul a c) (mul a j)) s) (mul k j) end)
            (mulDistR a k c))
          (cong (fn (s : Nat) is add s (mul k j) end)
            (sym (addAssoc (add (mul a c) (mul a j)) (mul a c) (mul k c))))))
      -- NF -> RHS  (i.e. sym of RHS -> NF)
      (sym
        (trans
          (cong (fn (s : Nat) is add (mul a c) s end)
            (mulDistR a k (add c j)))
          (trans
            (cong (fn (s : Nat) is add (mul a c) (add s (mul k (add c j))) end)
              (mulDistL a c j))
            (trans
              (cong (fn (s : Nat) is
                 add (mul a c) (add (add (mul a c) (mul a j)) s) end)
                (mulDistL k c j))
              (trans
                (sym (addAssoc (mul a c) (add (mul a c) (mul a j))
                       (add (mul k c) (mul k j))))
                (trans
                  (cong (fn (s : Nat) is add s (add (mul k c) (mul k j)) end)
                    (addComm (mul a c) (add (mul a c) (mul a j))))
                  (sym (addAssoc (add (add (mul a c) (mul a j)) (mul a c))
                         (mul k c) (mul k j)))))))))
  end
end

-- CROSS-MULTIPLICATION MONOTONICITY:  a ≤ b, c ≤ d  ⇒  a·d + b·c ≤ a·c + b·d.
-- With b = a+k (ek), d = c+j (ej): the k-j-form is  X + k·j  where
-- X = a·(c+j) + (a+k)·c, so X ≤ X + k·j (lteSelfAddR), and crossEq rewrites X + k·j to
-- a·c + (a+k)·(c+j) = a·c + b·d.  Then substitute b, d back.
addMulCrossLe : (a : Nat) -> (b : Nat) -> (c : Nat) -> (d : Nat)
   -> Eq Bool (lte a b) true -> Eq Bool (lte c d) true
   -> Eq Bool (lte (add (mul a d) (mul b c)) (add (mul a c) (mul b d))) true is
  fn (a : Nat) (b : Nat) (c : Nat) (d : Nat)
     (hab : Eq Bool (lte a b) true) (hcd : Eq Bool (lte c d) true) is
    subst Nat (add c (Fst (lteToAdd c d hcd))) d
      (sym {Nat} {d} {add c (Fst (lteToAdd c d hcd))} (Snd (lteToAdd c d hcd)))
      (fn (y : Nat) is
         Eq Bool (lte (add (mul a y) (mul b c)) (add (mul a c) (mul b y))) true end)
      (subst Nat (add a (Fst (lteToAdd a b hab))) b
        (sym {Nat} {b} {add a (Fst (lteToAdd a b hab))} (Snd (lteToAdd a b hab)))
        (fn (x : Nat) is
           Eq Bool (lte (add (mul a (add c (Fst (lteToAdd c d hcd)))) (mul x c))
                        (add (mul a c) (mul x (add c (Fst (lteToAdd c d hcd)))))) true end)
        (subst Nat
          (add (add (mul a (add c (Fst (lteToAdd c d hcd))))
                    (mul (add a (Fst (lteToAdd a b hab))) c))
               (mul (Fst (lteToAdd a b hab)) (Fst (lteToAdd c d hcd))))
          (add (mul a c)
               (mul (add a (Fst (lteToAdd a b hab))) (add c (Fst (lteToAdd c d hcd)))))
          (crossEq a (Fst (lteToAdd a b hab)) c (Fst (lteToAdd c d hcd)))
          (fn (s : Nat) is
             Eq Bool (lte (add (mul a (add c (Fst (lteToAdd c d hcd))))
                               (mul (add a (Fst (lteToAdd a b hab))) c)) s) true end)
          (lteSelfAddR
            (add (mul a (add c (Fst (lteToAdd c d hcd))))
                 (mul (add a (Fst (lteToAdd a b hab))) c))
            (mul (Fst (lteToAdd a b hab)) (Fst (lteToAdd c d hcd))))))
  end
end

-- ============================================================================
-- CHAPTER 128 — WHAT LANDED, AND THE NEXT STDLIB STEP.
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- FULLY PROVEN (no admits/holes/postulates) — the Nat root of the qmul-order tower:
--   • lteSelfAddR : x ≤ x + m.
--   • lteToAdd : lte a b ⇒ Σ k, b = a + k  (order-to-witness, double NatElim; the
--     (succ a', 0) case absurd via lteAbsurdNat).  NOTE: the Sig projections Fst/Snd of
--     a bound-variable application are stuck neutrals, so cong/sym over them need their
--     implicits passed EXPLICITLY (the renamer cannot solve a meta that contains such a
--     neutral — the same `unknown neutral in rename` class as NNatLit; explicit implicits
--     sidestep it).
--   • crossEq : (a·(c+j) + (a+k)·c) + k·j = a·c + (a+k)·(c+j)  (5-monomial monoid
--     rearrangement to a common normal form via mulDistL/R + interchange + addAssoc/Comm).
--   • addMulCrossLe : a ≤ b ⇒ c ≤ d ⇒ a·d + b·c ≤ a·c + b·d  — cross-multiplication
--     monotonicity (witnesses b=a+k, d=c+j; lteSelfAddR gives X ≤ X+k·j, crossEq re-aims
--     the bound).  The Nat heart of "product of nonnegatives is nonnegative".
--
-- THE NEXT STDLIB STEP (precise) — the qmul-order tower, then qabsMul, then rmul:
--   • zmulNonneg : 0 ≤ x ⇒ 0 ≤ y ⇒ 0 ≤ x·y  in ℤ.  On NatPair reps, 0 ≤ (x1,x2) means
--     x2 ≤ x1; the product (x1,x2)·(y1,y2) is nonneg iff x1·y2 + x2·y1 ≤ x1·y1 + x2·y2,
--     which is EXACTLY addMulCrossLe (x2≤x1, y2≤y1) after a commute.  Then qmulNonneg
--     (0 ≤ x ⇒ 0 ≤ y ⇒ 0 ≤ x·y in ℚ) lifts via the numerator (0 ≤ q ⟺ 0 ≤ qnum q).
--   • qabsNonneg (0 ≤ x ⇒ qabs x = x) + qabsMul (|a·b| = |a|·|b|) — the latter via
--     qmulNonneg (|a|·|b| ≥ 0, so qabs of it is itself) + qmulNegL/qmulNegR (ch127, fold
--     the sign of a·b into |a|·|b|).
--   • THE ARCHIMEDEAN MODULUS RESCALE (still the research crux) — then rmul assembles
--     (mulSeq, mulMod floored at N0, mulSeqBound via qmulSubDist+qabsMul+seqTailBound,
--     mulSeqCauchy, rmulP, respect, rmul) → the ORDERED FIELD ℝ.
-- ============================================================================


-- ============================================================================
-- CHAPTER 129 — PRODUCT OF NONNEGATIVES IS NONNEGATIVE (ℤ then ℚ): the order-sign
-- bridge from addMulCrossLe up to ℚ, feeding qabsMul / rmul (telos-3 / M6 / D3).
-- Everything above is the ch121–128 construction.  Below is the NEW layer, FULLY
-- PROVEN (no admits/holes/postulates):
--   • zmulNonneg : 0 ≤ x ⇒ 0 ≤ y ⇒ 0 ≤ x·y  in ℤ.  On NatPair reps p=(x1,x2),
--     q=(y1,y2): 0 ≤ p means zleP (0,0) p = lte x2 x1, and 0 ≤ p·q means
--     lte (x1·y2 + x2·y1) (x1·y1 + x2·y2) — EXACTLY addMulCrossLe (x2≤x1, y2≤y1) after
--     two addComm, plus addZeroR to absorb the rep's `+ 0`.
--   • qmulNonneg : 0 ≤ a ⇒ 0 ≤ b ⇒ 0 ≤ a·b  in ℚ.  0 ≤ a ⟺ 0 ≤ qnum a (the denominator
--     is positive; zmulZeroL/zmulOneR collapse the cross terms), and qnum(a·b) =
--     qnum a · qnum b, so qmulNonneg is zmulNonneg on the numerators.
-- All new definitions precede their use (Rune resolves names in source order).
-- ============================================================================

-- 0 ≤ x·y in ℤ.  The rep method (after the two qinds) receives hx : 0 ≤ p, hy : 0 ≤ q,
-- which reduce to lte (snd p)(add (fst p) 0) / lte (snd q)(add (fst q) 0); strip the +0
-- with addZeroR, feed addMulCrossLe, commute the two products into the pmul fst/snd
-- positions, reintroduce the +0 (sym addZeroR) to match the goal's zleP shape.
zmulNonneg : (x : Z) -> (y : Z)
   -> Eq Bool (zle zzero x) true -> Eq Bool (zle zzero y) true
   -> Eq Bool (zle zzero (zmul x y)) true is
  fn (x : Z) is
    qind NatPair ZRel
      (fn (wx : Z) is (y : Z)
         -> Eq Bool (zle zzero wx) true -> Eq Bool (zle zzero y) true
         -> Eq Bool (zle zzero (zmul wx y)) true end)
      (fn (p : NatPair) is
        fn (y : Z) is
          qind NatPair ZRel
            (fn (wy : Z) is
               Eq Bool (zle zzero (qin NatPair ZRel p)) true
                 -> Eq Bool (zle zzero wy) true
                 -> Eq Bool (zle zzero (zmul (qin NatPair ZRel p) wy)) true end)
            (fn (q : NatPair) is
              fn (hx : Eq Bool (zle zzero (qin NatPair ZRel p)) true)
                 (hy : Eq Bool (zle zzero (qin NatPair ZRel q)) true) is
                -- strip the rep's `+ 0` from each hypothesis: lte (snd p)(fst p) etc.
                subst Nat (fst (pmul p q)) (add (fst (pmul p q)) zero)
                  (sym (addZeroR (fst (pmul p q))))
                  (fn (s : Nat) is Eq Bool (lte (snd (pmul p q)) s) true end)
                  -- core: lte (snd (pmul p q)) (fst (pmul p q)) = true, by addMulCrossLe.
                  (subst Nat (add (mul (snd p) (snd q)) (mul (fst p) (fst q)))
                             (add (mul (fst p) (fst q)) (mul (snd p) (snd q)))
                    (addComm (mul (snd p) (snd q)) (mul (fst p) (fst q)))
                    (fn (s : Nat) is
                       Eq Bool (lte (add (mul (fst p) (snd q)) (mul (snd p) (fst q))) s) true end)
                    (subst Nat (add (mul (snd p) (fst q)) (mul (fst p) (snd q)))
                               (add (mul (fst p) (snd q)) (mul (snd p) (fst q)))
                      (addComm (mul (snd p) (fst q)) (mul (fst p) (snd q)))
                      (fn (s : Nat) is
                         Eq Bool (lte s (add (mul (snd p) (snd q)) (mul (fst p) (fst q)))) true end)
                      (addMulCrossLe (snd p) (fst p) (snd q) (fst q)
                        (subst Nat (add (fst p) zero) (fst p) (addZeroR (fst p))
                          (fn (s : Nat) is Eq Bool (lte (snd p) s) true end) hx)
                        (subst Nat (add (fst q) zero) (fst q) (addZeroR (fst q))
                          (fn (s : Nat) is Eq Bool (lte (snd q) s) true end) hy))))
              end
            end)
            y
        end
      end)
      x
  end
end

-- 0 ≤ a·b in ℚ.  0 ≤ a reduces (rep p) to zle (zmul zzero (zden p)) (zmul (qnum p) zone)
-- = zle zzero (qnum p) after zmulZeroL/zmulOneR; the product's numerator is qnum p · qnum q,
-- so zmulNonneg on the numerators closes it.  The goal carries the same zmulZeroL/zmulOneR
-- collapse, reintroduced by sym.
qmulNonneg : (a : Q) -> (b : Q)
   -> Eq Bool (qle qzero a) true -> Eq Bool (qle qzero b) true
   -> Eq Bool (qle qzero (qmul a b)) true is
  fn (a : Q) is
    qind QPair QRel
      (fn (wa : Q) is (b : Q)
         -> Eq Bool (qle qzero wa) true -> Eq Bool (qle qzero b) true
         -> Eq Bool (qle qzero (qmul wa b)) true end)
      (fn (p : QPair) is
        fn (b : Q) is
          qind QPair QRel
            (fn (wb : Q) is
               Eq Bool (qle qzero (qin QPair QRel p)) true
                 -> Eq Bool (qle qzero wb) true
                 -> Eq Bool (qle qzero (qmul (qin QPair QRel p) wb)) true end)
            (fn (q : QPair) is
              fn (ha : Eq Bool (qle qzero (qin QPair QRel p)) true)
                 (hb : Eq Bool (qle qzero (qin QPair QRel q)) true) is
                -- goal (rep): zle (zmul zzero (zden (qmulP p q)))
                --                 (zmul (zmul (qnum p) (qnum q)) zone) = true.
                -- reintroduce zmul zzero _ on the left and zmul _ zone on the right.
                subst Z zzero (zmul zzero (zden (qmulP p q)))
                  (sym (zmulZeroL (zden (qmulP p q))))
                  (fn (s : Z) is
                     Eq Bool (zle s (zmul (zmul (qnum p) (qnum q)) zone)) true end)
                  (subst Z (zmul (qnum p) (qnum q))
                           (zmul (zmul (qnum p) (qnum q)) zone)
                    (sym (zmulOneR (zmul (qnum p) (qnum q))))
                    (fn (s : Z) is Eq Bool (zle zzero s) true end)
                    -- zmulNonneg on the numerators; hypotheses stripped of zmulZeroL/zmulOneR.
                    (zmulNonneg (qnum p) (qnum q)
                      (subst Z (zmul (qnum p) zone) (qnum p) (zmulOneR (qnum p))
                        (fn (s : Z) is Eq Bool (zle (zmul zzero (zden p)) s) true end)
                        (subst Z (zmul zzero (zden p)) zzero (zmulZeroL (zden p))
                          (fn (s : Z) is Eq Bool (zle s (zmul (qnum p) zone)) true end) ha))
                      (subst Z (zmul (qnum q) zone) (qnum q) (zmulOneR (qnum q))
                        (fn (s : Z) is Eq Bool (zle (zmul zzero (zden q)) s) true end)
                        (subst Z (zmul zzero (zden q)) zzero (zmulZeroL (zden q))
                          (fn (s : Z) is Eq Bool (zle s (zmul (qnum q) zone)) true end) hb))))
              end
            end)
            b
        end
      end)
      a
  end
end

-- ============================================================================
-- CHAPTER 129 — WHAT LANDED, AND THE NEXT STDLIB STEP.
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- FULLY PROVEN (no admits/holes/postulates):
--   • zmulNonneg : 0 ≤ x ⇒ 0 ≤ y ⇒ 0 ≤ x·y  (ℤ) — addMulCrossLe on the NatPair reps.
--   • qmulNonneg : 0 ≤ a ⇒ 0 ≤ b ⇒ 0 ≤ a·b  (ℚ) — zmulNonneg on the numerators.
--
-- THE NEXT STDLIB STEP (precise) — qabsMul, then the archimedean rescale, then rmul:
--   • qabsNonneg : 0 ≤ x ⇒ qabs x = x  (BoolElim on qle x 0; the true branch forces
--     x = 0 by qleAntisym, so qabs x = −x = −0 = 0 = x; the false branch is definitional).
--   • qmulMonoNonneg : 0 ≤ c ⇒ a ≤ b ⇒ c·a ≤ c·b  — c·b − c·a = c·(b−a) ≥ 0
--     (qmulNonneg with 0 ≤ b−a from a ≤ b, and qmulSubDistL/ch127); the rmul-bound's
--     "multiply a tolerance by a nonneg bound" step.
--   • qabsMul : |a·b| = |a|·|b|  — qmulNonneg gives |a|·|b| ≥ 0 so qabs fixes it
--     (qabsNonneg), and qmulNegL/qmulNegR (ch127) fold the sign of a·b through the four
--     BoolElim sign branches to match.
--   • THE ARCHIMEDEAN MODULUS RESCALE (the research crux) — then rmul assembles
--     (mulSeq, mulMod floored at N0, mulSeqBound via qmulSubDist+qabsMul+qmulMonoNonneg+
--     seqTailBound, mulSeqCauchy, rmulP, respect, rmul) → the ORDERED FIELD ℝ.
-- ============================================================================


-- ============================================================================
-- CHAPTER 130 — ℚ ABSOLUTE-VALUE PRODUCT LAW + NONNEG MONOTONICITY: the last
-- algebraic pieces before rmul's archimedean rescale (telos-3 / M6 / D3).
-- Everything above is the ch121–129 construction.  Below is the NEW layer, FULLY
-- PROVEN (no admits/holes/postulates):
--   • qabsGe0 : 0 ≤ |x|   and   qabsNonneg : 0 ≤ x ⇒ |x| = x.
--   • qmulMonoNonneg : 0 ≤ c ⇒ a ≤ b ⇒ c·a ≤ c·b — c·b − c·a = c·(b−a) ≥ 0
--     (qmulNonneg + qmulSubDistL); the "scale a tolerance by a nonneg bound" step.
--   • qabsMul : |a·b| = |a|·|b| — |a|·|b| ≥ 0 (qmulNonneg) so qabs fixes it (qabsNonneg),
--     and qmulNegL/qmulNegR pull each qabs off its factor under qabs (qabsMulL/R), so
--     |a·b| = |(±a)·(±b)| = |a|·|b| with NO case on the sign of the product itself.
-- All new definitions precede their use (Rune resolves names in source order).
-- ============================================================================

-- 0 ≤ |x|.  Branch on (qle x 0): true ⇒ |x| = −x ≥ 0 (qleNegFromNonpos); false ⇒ |x| = x
-- and 0 ≤ x (qleZeroFromFalse).
qabsGe0 : (x : Q) -> Eq Bool (qle qzero (qabs x)) true is
  fn (x : Q) is
    BoolElim
      (fn (p : Bool) is Eq Bool (qle x qzero) p
         -> Eq Bool (qle qzero (BoolElim (fn (z : Bool) is Q end) (qneg x) x p)) true end)
      (fn (hp : Eq Bool (qle x qzero) true) is qleNegFromNonpos x hp end)
      (fn (hp : Eq Bool (qle x qzero) false) is qleZeroFromFalse x hp end)
      (qle x qzero)
      (refl (qle x qzero))
  end
end

-- 0 ≤ x ⇒ |x| = x.  Branch on (qle x 0): false ⇒ |x| = x (refl).  true ⇒ x ≤ 0 and 0 ≤ x,
-- so x = 0 (qleAntisym); then |x| = −x = −0 = 0 = x.
qabsNonneg : (x : Q) -> Eq Bool (qle qzero x) true -> Eq Q (qabs x) x is
  fn (x : Q) (h : Eq Bool (qle qzero x) true) is
    BoolElim
      (fn (p : Bool) is Eq Bool (qle x qzero) p
         -> Eq Q (BoolElim (fn (z : Bool) is Q end) (qneg x) x p) x end)
      (fn (hp : Eq Bool (qle x qzero) true) is
         trans (cong (fn (s : Q) is qneg s end) (qleAntisym x qzero hp h))
           (trans qNegZero (sym (qleAntisym x qzero hp h))) end)
      (fn (hp : Eq Bool (qle x qzero) false) is refl x end)
      (qle x qzero)
      (refl (qle x qzero))
  end
end

-- a ≤ b ⇒ 0 ≤ b − a.  Add (−a) to a ≤ b (qaddMono); a + (−a) = 0 (qAddNegR), b + (−a) = b−a.
qleSubNonneg : (a : Q) -> (b : Q)
   -> Eq Bool (qle a b) true -> Eq Bool (qle qzero (qsub b a)) true is
  fn (a : Q) (b : Q) (h : Eq Bool (qle a b) true) is
    subst Q (qadd a (qneg a)) qzero (qAddNegR a)
      (fn (s : Q) is Eq Bool (qle s (qsub b a)) true end)
      (qaddMono a b (qneg a) h)
  end
end

-- 0 ≤ y − x ⇒ x ≤ y.  Add x; 0 + x = x (qaddZeroL), (y−x) + x = y (qsubAddBack).
qleFromSubNonneg : (x : Q) -> (y : Q)
   -> Eq Bool (qle qzero (qsub y x)) true -> Eq Bool (qle x y) true is
  fn (x : Q) (y : Q) (h : Eq Bool (qle qzero (qsub y x)) true) is
    subst Q (qadd qzero x) x (qaddZeroL x)
      (fn (s : Q) is Eq Bool (qle s y) true end)
      (subst Q (qadd (qsub y x) x) y (qsubAddBack y x)
        (fn (s : Q) is Eq Bool (qle (qadd qzero x) s) true end)
        (qaddMono qzero (qsub y x) x h))
  end
end

-- 0 ≤ c ⇒ a ≤ b ⇒ c·a ≤ c·b.  c·b − c·a = c·(b−a) ≥ 0, then qleFromSubNonneg.
qmulMonoNonneg : (c : Q) -> (a : Q) -> (b : Q)
   -> Eq Bool (qle qzero c) true -> Eq Bool (qle a b) true
   -> Eq Bool (qle (qmul c a) (qmul c b)) true is
  fn (c : Q) (a : Q) (b : Q)
     (hc : Eq Bool (qle qzero c) true) (hab : Eq Bool (qle a b) true) is
    qleFromSubNonneg (qmul c a) (qmul c b)
      (subst Q (qmul c (qsub b a)) (qsub (qmul c b) (qmul c a)) (qmulSubDistL c b a)
        (fn (s : Q) is Eq Bool (qle qzero s) true end)
        (qmulNonneg c (qsub b a) hc (qleSubNonneg a b hab)))
  end
end

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- THE ABSOLUTE-VALUE PRODUCT LAW  |a·b| = |a|·|b|.
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

-- Pull qabs off the LEFT factor under an outer qabs:  |(|a|)·X| = |a·X|.
-- Branch on (qle a 0): true ⇒ |a| = −a, and |(−a)·X| = |−(a·X)| = |a·X| (qmulNegL+qabsNeg).
qabsMulL : (a : Q) -> (x : Q)
   -> Eq Q (qabs (qmul (qabs a) x)) (qabs (qmul a x)) is
  fn (a : Q) (x : Q) is
    BoolElim
      (fn (p : Bool) is Eq Bool (qle a qzero) p
         -> Eq Q (qabs (qmul (BoolElim (fn (z : Bool) is Q end) (qneg a) a p) x))
                 (qabs (qmul a x)) end)
      (fn (hp : Eq Bool (qle a qzero) true) is
         trans (cong (fn (s : Q) is qabs s end) (qmulNegL a x)) (qabsNeg (qmul a x)) end)
      (fn (hp : Eq Bool (qle a qzero) false) is refl (qabs (qmul a x)) end)
      (qle a qzero)
      (refl (qle a qzero))
  end
end

-- Pull qabs off the RIGHT factor:  |Y·(|b|)| = |Y·b|.  Symmetric, via qmulNegR.
qabsMulR : (y : Q) -> (b : Q)
   -> Eq Q (qabs (qmul y (qabs b))) (qabs (qmul y b)) is
  fn (y : Q) (b : Q) is
    BoolElim
      (fn (p : Bool) is Eq Bool (qle b qzero) p
         -> Eq Q (qabs (qmul y (BoolElim (fn (z : Bool) is Q end) (qneg b) b p)))
                 (qabs (qmul y b)) end)
      (fn (hp : Eq Bool (qle b qzero) true) is
         trans (cong (fn (s : Q) is qabs s end) (qmulNegR y b)) (qabsNeg (qmul y b)) end)
      (fn (hp : Eq Bool (qle b qzero) false) is refl (qabs (qmul y b)) end)
      (qle b qzero)
      (refl (qle b qzero))
  end
end

-- |a·b| = |a|·|b|.  |a|·|b| ≥ 0 (qmulNonneg), so qabs(|a|·|b|) = |a|·|b| (qabsNonneg);
-- and qabs(|a|·|b|) = qabs(a·b) by pulling each qabs off its factor (qabsMulR then qabsMulL).
qabsMul : (a : Q) -> (b : Q)
   -> Eq Q (qabs (qmul a b)) (qmul (qabs a) (qabs b)) is
  fn (a : Q) (b : Q) is
    trans
      -- |a·b| = |(|a|)·(|b|)|  (sym of: pull both qabs off)
      (sym (trans (qabsMulR (qabs a) b) (qabsMulL a b)))
      -- |(|a|)·(|b|)| = |a|·|b|  (it is nonneg)
      (qabsNonneg (qmul (qabs a) (qabs b))
        (qmulNonneg (qabs a) (qabs b) (qabsGe0 a) (qabsGe0 b)))
  end
end

-- ============================================================================
-- CHAPTER 130 — WHAT LANDED, AND THE NEXT STDLIB STEP.
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- FULLY PROVEN (no admits/holes/postulates) — the ℚ abs/mono layer rmul needs:
--   • qabsGe0 (0 ≤ |x|), qabsNonneg (0 ≤ x ⇒ |x| = x).
--   • qmulMonoNonneg (0 ≤ c ⇒ a ≤ b ⇒ c·a ≤ c·b).
--   • qabsMul (|a·b| = |a|·|b|).
-- With ch127 (qmulSubDist), ch126 (seqTailBound), and these, the rmul Cauchy bound
--   |fx m·fy m − fx n·fy n| ≤ Bx·|fy m − fy n| + By·|fx m − fx n|
-- is now FULLY SUPPLIED at the ℚ level (regroup ▸ triangle ▸ qabsMul ▸ qmulMonoNonneg ▸
-- seqTailBound).  Only the modulus arithmetic remains.
--
-- THE NEXT STDLIB STEP (precise) — the ARCHIMEDEAN MODULUS RESCALE, then rmul:
--   • qFromNatBound : for a positive rational B = p/q, qle B (qFromNat p) (B ≤ its ceil),
--     and the archimedean choice: given B and target k, a modulus index j with
--     B·(1/(j+1)) ≤ 1/(k+1) — take j+1 = p·(k+1) (since B = p/q ≤ p when q ≥ 1).  Needs
--     reading qnum/qdenN off B's rep and a ℚ-vs-Nat inequality; the one genuinely new
--     construction (a Nat-extraction-from-a-rational + a qFromMod-product bound).
--   • THEN rmul : R -> R -> R — mulSeq (pointwise qmul); mulMod k = max of the two
--     archimedean-rescaled component moduli AND Nx0, Ny0 (the floor that activates
--     seqTailBound); mulSeqBound (the bound above, with the tolerances driven below
--     1/(k+1) by the rescale); mulSeqCauchy; rmulP; the RRel-respect pair; rmul through
--     the double qind — completing the ORDERED FIELD ℝ.
-- ============================================================================


-- ============================================================================
-- CHAPTER 131 — ARCHIMEDEAN BOUND at the REP level + the QUOTIENT-EXTRACTION WALL
-- (the rmul modulus crux; telos-3 / M6 / D3).
-- Everything above is the ch121–130 construction.  Below is the NEW layer, FULLY
-- PROVEN (no admits/holes/postulates), AND a load-bearing architectural finding.
--   • qFromNat : Nat -> Q  (n ↦ n/1).
--   • zfromMono : a ≤ b ⇒ zfrom a ≤ zfrom b  (the ℤ embedding is order-preserving).
--   • lteMulSelfR : k ≤ k·(d+1).
--   • zToNatBoundP : every integer REP (a NatPair) is ≤ zfrom n for some n — take
--     n = the rep's first component ((z1,z2) denotes z1−z2 ≤ z1, by lteSelfAddR).
--
-- *** THE QUOTIENT-EXTRACTION WALL (the finding that redirects rmul) ***
-- The archimedean bound "every rational q ≤ qFromNat n for SOME n" cannot be a Sig-valued
-- (DATA) function  qArch : (q : Q) -> Sig Nat (…)  on the quotient Q, for a STRUCTURAL
-- reason, not a missing lemma:
--   (1) `qind` (the quotient induction principle) eliminates ONLY into Prop motives
--       (proof-irrelevant) — a Sig (which lands in U) is rejected: `expected Prop, got U`.
--       (Verified: the qind-into-Sig version fails to check.)
--   (2) The same wall sits one level down: a Nat bound is NOT a well-defined function on
--       Z = Quot NatPair ZRel either — (3,1) ∼ (4,2) both denote 2, but the rep-first-
--       component bound gives 3 vs 4, so it does not RESPECT ZRel and cannot lift via
--       qlift.  There is no canonical section Z -> NatPair (or Q -> QPair).
-- So an integer/rational's Nat bound exists only at the REPRESENTATIVE level
-- (zToNatBoundP : NatPair -> …), never as a function on the quotient.  This is the
-- constructive "Cauchy reals need countable choice" obstruction in concrete form.
--
-- CONSEQUENCE FOR rmul (the redirect): rmul's product modulus is DATA (Nat -> Nat) that
-- must read a numeric bound off the sequence values |fx (Nx 0)|.  In ch121 the ℝ sequence
-- is `Nat -> Q` (QUOTIENT-valued), so that bound would need Q -> Nat — the wall above.
-- TWO sound exits, a design decision:
--   (a) thread RATIONAL-REP sequences: make RPair carry `Nat -> QPair` (concrete reps), so
--       the numerator/bound is available rep-level (zToNatBoundP applies); RRel compares via
--       the reps.  A ch121 refactor, but the principled constructive form.
--   (b) carry the BOUND as data: extend isCauchy with a `Sig Nat (∀n, |f n| ≤ qFromNat K)`
--       field, so rmulP reads K directly.  Smaller change, slightly redundant data.
-- Recommendation: (b) — additive, no ch121–130 rework, and the bound is exactly what the
-- product modulus consumes; the seqTailBound (ch126) anchor already proves the field's
-- content for the chosen modulus.  The archimedean rep lemmas here are the fuel either way.
-- All new definitions precede their use (Rune resolves names in source order).
-- ============================================================================

-- n ↦ n/1.
qFromNat : Nat -> Q is fn (n : Nat) is qfromZ (zfrom n) end end

-- a ≤ b ⇒ zfrom a ≤ zfrom b.  zle (zfrom a)(zfrom b) reduces to lte (add a 0)(add b 0);
-- strip the +0 (addZeroR) so the hypothesis lte a b lands directly.
zfromMono : (a : Nat) -> (b : Nat)
   -> Eq Bool (lte a b) true -> Eq Bool (zle (zfrom a) (zfrom b)) true is
  fn (a : Nat) (b : Nat) (h : Eq Bool (lte a b) true) is
    subst Nat a (add a zero) (sym (addZeroR a))
      (fn (s : Nat) is Eq Bool (lte s (add b zero)) true end)
      (subst Nat b (add b zero) (sym (addZeroR b))
        (fn (s : Nat) is Eq Bool (lte a s) true end)
        h)
  end
end

-- k ≤ k·(d+1).  mul k (succ d) = mul (succ d) k = add k (mul d k) ≥ k (lteSelfAddR).
lteMulSelfR : (k : Nat) -> (d : Nat) -> Eq Bool (lte k (mul k (succ d))) true is
  fn (k : Nat) (d : Nat) is
    subst Nat (mul (succ d) k) (mul k (succ d)) (mulComm (succ d) k)
      (fn (s : Nat) is Eq Bool (lte k s) true end)
      (lteSelfAddR k (mul d k))
  end
end

-- Every integer REP is ≤ some zfrom n.  On p=(z1,z2) (denoting z1−z2): take n = z1;
-- zle (qin p)(zfrom z1) reduces to lte (add z1 0)(add z1 z2) = lte z1 (z1+z2) (lteSelfAddR).
-- REP-LEVEL ONLY: this is NOT liftable to a function Z -> Nat (it does not respect ZRel).
zToNatBoundP : (p : NatPair)
   -> Sig Nat (fn (n : Nat) is Eq Bool (zle (qin NatPair ZRel p) (zfrom n)) true end) is
  fn (p : NatPair) is
    Pair Nat
      (fn (n : Nat) is Eq Bool (zle (qin NatPair ZRel p) (zfrom n)) true end)
      (fst p)
      (subst Nat (fst p) (add (fst p) zero) (sym (addZeroR (fst p)))
        (fn (s : Nat) is Eq Bool (lte s (add (fst p) (snd p))) true end)
        (lteSelfAddR (fst p) (snd p)))
  end
end


-- ====================================================================================
-- CHAPTER 145 — THE DETERMINANT of a 2×2 ℤ-matrix (telos-3 / linear algebra).
-- det M = M[0,0]·M[1,1] − M[0,1]·M[1,0] = ad − bc.  Built over the ℤ ring WITH NEGATION
-- (this base supplies zneg).  We prove det(I) = 1 and that the determinant is invariant
-- under TRANSPOSE (det Mᵀ = det M).  FULLY PROVEN, no postulate.  Matrix = Bool -> Bool -> Z.
-- ====================================================================================

-- −0 = 0.
zNegZero : Eq Z (zneg zzero) zzero is refl zzero end

Matrix : U is Bool -> Bool -> Z end

matId : Matrix is
  fn (i : Bool) (j : Bool) is
    BoolElim (fn (x : Bool) is Z end)
      (BoolElim (fn (y : Bool) is Z end) zone zzero j)
      (BoolElim (fn (y : Bool) is Z end) zzero zone j)
      i
  end
end

-- The transpose swaps the off-diagonal: Mᵀ[i,j] = M[j,i].
transpose : Matrix -> Matrix is
  fn (M : Matrix) is fn (i : Bool) (j : Bool) is M j i end end
end

-- The determinant: ad − bc, with subtraction as `+ (−)`.
det : Matrix -> Z is
  fn (M : Matrix) is
    zadd (zmul (M true true) (M false false))
         (zneg (zmul (M true false) (M false true)))
  end
end

-- det(I) = 1·1 − 0·0 = 1 − 0 = 1.
detMatId : Eq Z (det matId) zone is
  trans (cong (fn (s : Z) is zadd s (zneg (zmul zzero zzero)) end) (zmulOneR zone))
    (trans (cong (fn (s : Z) is zadd zone (zneg s) end) (zmulZeroR zzero))
      (trans (cong (fn (s : Z) is zadd zone s end) zNegZero)
        (zaddZeroR zone)))
end

-- det(Mᵀ) = det(M).  Transpose swaps b and c, so the cross term cb = bc (zmulComm); the
-- diagonal term ad is unchanged.
detTranspose : (M : Matrix) -> Eq Z (det (transpose M)) (det M) is
  fn (M : Matrix) is
    cong (fn (s : Z) is
      zadd (zmul (M true true) (M false false)) (zneg s) end)
      (zmulComm (M false true) (M true false))
  end
end

-- ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- CHAPTER 145 — WHAT LANDED.
-- FULLY PROVEN (no admits/holes/postulates): the DETERMINANT det = ad − bc of a 2×2 ℤ-matrix,
-- with detMatId (det I = 1) and detTranspose (det Mᵀ = det M).  Over the ℤ ring with negation.
-- THE NEXT STEP: the MARQUEE multiplicativity det(A·B) = det(A)·det(B) — redeclare matMul over
-- this neg-equipped base, expand both sides (product-of-sums via zmulDistL/R, product-of-
-- differences via the (X−Y)(U−V)=(XU+YV)−(XV+YU) identity), and normalize to the common form
-- (adeh+bcfg) − (adfg+bceh), the acef and bdgh cross terms cancelling — an 8-variable ℤ ring
-- normalization.  Then 2×2 ℤ-matrices stand as a fully worked verified noncommutative algebra.
-- ====================================================================================
